title: lemon tea bread
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar and grated lemon rind.
Add eggs. Sift flour and baking powder.
Add alternately with the milk.
Add nuts.
Bake in greased loaf in a 375° oven for about 35 minutes (use toothpick test for doneness).
As soon as bread is removed from the oven, pour over the top of a mixture of 1/4 cup sugar and the juice and grated rind of 1 large lemon.
Let bread cool for 10 minutes before removing from the pan.

title: pork roast
directions: In a small bowl combine mustard, soy sauce, oil, garlic and thyme.
Rub over roast.
Refrigerate, turning occasionally.
Place roast on a rack in a shallow roasting pan.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Pour wine into the pan.
Bake uncovered at 325°F for about 2 1/2 hours, until meat thermometer reads 160°, basting with pan juices every 30 minutes.
Before slicing let stand for 10 minutes.
Serve over mashed potatoes with green lettuce.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix all the ingredients and let sit 2 or 3 hours before serving.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Do not cover.

title: no bake chocolate cookies
directions: Mix together and bring to a boil the butter, sugar, milk and cocoa; boil 1 minute and remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Drop by teaspoons onto waxed paper. Cool.

title: fiesta burrito casserole
directions: Stir together seasoning mix and tomato juice.
Brown ground beef in skillet, stirring to crumble.
Pour off excess fat.
Stir in beans and 1/2 to 3/4 cup of tomato mixture.
Cover and simmer 5 to 10 minutes, stirring occasionally, until hot.
Place generous spoonful of beef-bean filling on each tortilla.
Sprinkle with lettuce (if desired) and cheese.
Roll up.
(Save about 1/2 cup cheese for topping.)

title: rice and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice and set aside.
Saute butter and chopped onion in it.
Then mix in rice, broccoli, soup and cheese.
Mix well. Bake, uncovered, for 35 minutes in a 325° oven.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Combine all ingredients except chocolate chips.
Beat 4 minutes.
Fold in chips.
Bake in greased and floured 12-cup Bundt pan at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool in pan 10 to 15 minutes. Sprinkle with confectioners sugar after cooled.

title: pig pickin cake
directions: Mix cake mix, oil, eggs and oranges, juice and all. Grease and flour a 12 inch bundt pan. Bake 325° for
35 to 50 minutes. Cool. When cool, slice in half, crosswise. Put frosting between layers, on top and sides. Cake keeps 5-6 days in refrigerator.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Mix cocoa, sugar, milk and butter; bring to boil.
Boil 1 minute; add vanilla flavoring.
Remove from heat.
Stir and cook until spreading consistency.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Wash and hull strawberries, drain well. Put 1 quart of berries in refrigerator to chill.
Brush 1/2 quart of berries well.
Blend with sugar, cornstarch and water.
Carefully heat to boiling in heavy saucepan.
Boil 2 minutes and strain, if desired.
Add batter and food coloring.
Fill pastry shell with chilled berries and pour cooked glaze mixture over top.
Chill about 4 hours.
Top with whipped cream and serve.

title: peanut butter bonbons
directions: You will need toothpicks.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Butter sides of a heavy 2-quart saucepan.
Combine sugar and milk.
Cook to soft ball, 234°.
Remove from heat; add marshmallow cream, peanut butter, chocolate and vanilla.
Stir until blended. Pour into buttered 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: orange slice cookies
directions: Cream the shortening in a large mixing bowl.
Gradually add sugars, beating at medium speed of an electric mixer.
Add eggs; beat well.
Combine flour, soda and baking powder.
Add to creamed mixture and mix.
Stir in water, oats, coconut and candy.
Chill dough at least 1 hour.
Drop dough by teaspoonfuls or roll into balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 12 minutes or until browned.
Cool.

title: ginger oat bran cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Coat baking sheets with spray; set aside.
Cream sugar and margarine in a mixing bowl.
Stir in remaining ingredients until blended.
Drop by level tablespoonfuls two inches apart onto prepared baking sheets.
Bake 16 to 18 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove from baking sheets and cool on wire racks.
Makes about 30 (2-inch) cookies.

title: clam chowder(from market-street grill)
directions: Combine melted butter and flour in ovenproof container and bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
In large saucepan, combine remaining ingredients except half and half.
Simmer until potatoes are thoroughly cooked.
Stir butter-flour mixture into chowder and stir until thick.
Mixture will be slightly less thick than cookie dough.
Remove chowder from heat.
Stir in half and half, until blended.
Heat to serving temperature, stirring occasionally. Makes 12 servings.

title: simple stroganoff
directions: Brown beef with onion.
Drain grease.
Add other ingredients (except rice or noodles) and simmer approximately 10 minutes. Serve over rice or noodles.

title: cheesy garlic bread
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Cut slices down the length of bread at 1-inch intervals, without cutting all the way through. Rub slices and top of loaf with cut sides of garlic halves. Then mince garlic. Combine butter, garlic, parsley and Parmesan cheese in small bowl. Spread mixture between bread slices and on top of the loaf. Wrap bread in foil, leaving top partially uncovered. Bake until heated through, about 15 minutes.

title: italian "bows"
directions: *As much as it takes for soft dough (not sticky).

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, Wesson oil and vanilla and blend well.
Add apples, then dry ingredients.
Mix well and add nuts.
Bake in a greased and floured Bundt or tube pan at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Melt in double boiler; dip balls into it and put on wax paper to harden.

title: kahlua
directions: Boil water.
Add sugar and coffee.
Cool.
Add vanilla and vodka.
Enjoy as a drink or on top of ice cream.

title: baun salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Mix cottage cheese, crushed pineapple and Jell-O together.
Place in refrigerator to partially harden, about 30 minutes.

title: rice krispies peanut butter balls
directions: Mix and form into balls.
In double boiler, melt bags of chocolate chips and add paraffin wax.
Dip balls in chocolate mixture, then let them set on wax paper on cookie sheet.
(I make these at Christmastime.)

title: no-bake cookies
directions: Boil first four ingredients together for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper and let cool.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and press into pizza pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes; cool.
Mix Eagle Brand, lemon juice and cream cheese together and spread over cooled crust.
Mix sugar, cornstarch and water; cook until thickened.
Add Jell-O, food coloring and strawberries.
Spread over cream cheese mixture. Cover with Cool Whip.
Keep refrigerated.

title: mexican manicotti(microwave)
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Mix taco seasoning and 1/2 cup water with ground beef and simmer until not soupy.
Mix well with refried beans.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix until Jell-O is dissolved and let cool before adding other ingredients.
Use pineapple as it comes from the can (don't drain). Place in refrigerator overnight until set.

title: carolyn's muffins
directions: Beat egg, then add ingredients listed.
Mix until moist.
Fill greased muffin pans or bake cups 3/4 full.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 12.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Heat over medium-high heat until sugar is dissolved.

title: apple or peach strudel
directions: Into bottom of buttered baking dish (9-inch square or 11 x 13-inch), put thick layer of fruit.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon (nutmeg if desired).
Dot with lumps of butter.

title: banana split cake
directions: Combine graham crackers and melted margarine and press into oblong pan.
Slice bananas and spread on top of crumbs.
Mix milk and lemon juice and pour on top of bananas.
Then spread crushed pineapple, drained.
Top with Cool Whip; sprinkle with coconuts, pecans and cherries.
Chill overnight.

title: sausage corn bread
directions: Cook sausage in a skillet until brown.
Remove sausage; drain off 1/4 cup of the fat drippings and reserve.
Saute onions in the skillet until golden.
Beat eggs and milk until smooth.
Stir in remaining ingredients and beat until batter is smooth.
Fold in onions and the reserved sausage drippings.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Place sausage on top. Bake in a preheated oven (350° to 375°) for 25 to 30 minutes or until firm and brown.
Cut into squares and serve hot.

title: one-bowl buttercream frosting
directions: In a small mixer bowl, beat the butter or margarine until fluffy. Add the confectioners sugar and cocoa alternately with the milk. Beat to spreading consistency, adding additional milk, if needed. Stir in the vanilla.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: petit brule
directions: Remove pulp from orange.
Place sugar cubes and spices in hollowed out orange.
Pour brandy over same and ignite.
Serves 1.

title: garden macaroni salad
directions: In large bowl, combine mayonnaise, vinegar, dill, salt and pepper.
Add elbow macaroni, cucumber, tomatoes, onions and olives.
Toss to coat well.
Cover and chill.

title: wild cactus chili
directions: Brown beef.
Drain and put in large pot.
Add kidney beans, tomatoes, seasonings and crushed garlic.
Simmer on low heat.
In a large pan, add oil and lightly brown all the vegetables, then add to pot.
Mix well.
Fluid level should cover the top of chili. Stir occasionally.
Serve with shredded Cheddar.
After dinner, serve 2 Hershey Kisses to each person.
It helps put out the fire.

title: hot-time punch
directions: Pour the cider and cinnamon candies into a saucepan; simmer, stirring occasionally, until the candies are dissolved.
Serve hot.
Yields sixteen 1/2-cup servings.

title: nut bread
directions: Grease and flour pan.
Beat all ingredients for 1/2 minute. Bake 55 to 60 minutes in 350° oven.
To check for doneness, stick a toothpick in the center.
If toothpick comes out clean, bread is done.

title: mayonnaise rolls
directions: Mix in bowl well; grease muffin pan with butter.
Bake at 350° to 400° about 20 to 25 minutes.
Watch very carefully.

title: large fruit dish
directions: Dice peaches and pears.
Slice bananas and cut grapes in half. Put these in a large bowl with fruit cocktail and nuts.
Sprinkle coconut on top and then put in icebox to cool before serving.

title: sugarless apple pie
directions: Cook juice and cornstarch until clear.
Add apples and spice. Use unbaked pie shell; top with crust.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: blondies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in a greased shallow pan at 350° for approximately 20 minutes.
Allow to cool; cut into squares. Makes about 36 bars.

title: pea-jag(cape verdean rice dish)
directions: Saute onions in oil in saucepan.
Add peas to onions and simmer 2 minutes more.
Add water and seasonings.
Bring to boil. Add rice and simmer, covered, for 25 minutes.

title: chocolate caramel rice krispies bars
directions: Melt caramels, sweetened condensed milk and 1/4 c. margarine over low heat or in microwave.
Melt 3/4 c. margarine and marshmallows over low heat.
Add rice krispies.
Mix well.
Place enough of the mixture into 2 buttered pans so bottoms are covered. Pour half of caramel mixture over rice krispies layer.
Spread to edge of pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over caramel layer.
Place remaining rice krispies mixture over chocolate chips.
Chill.
This recipe freezes very well.

title: 3 bean salad
directions: Drain all beans and combine; add green pepper.
Combine sugar, vinegar and salad oil and pour over vegetables.
Add salt and pepper and toss.
Chill overnight and re-toss to coat beans and drain before serving.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: spicy apple pie
directions: Roll 1/2 of dough and line a 9-inch pie pan.
Fill pie shell with sliced apples.
Mix sugar, spices, salt and lemon juice. Sprinkle over apples.
Dot with butter.
Moisten edge of crust with water.
Roll remaining dough for top crust and cut a few slits to allow steam to escape.
Fit top crust over apples and seal edge of pie.
Bake in hot oven (425°) for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix ingredients together well and make	balls about the size of English walnuts.
Bake for 20 minutes in 350° oven.

title: pickled peaches
directions: In large stockpot, bring vinegar, sugar, cinnamon and cloves to a boil.
Boil for 35 minutes, then add peeled peaches.
Cook until soft.
Pack peaches loosely in quart jars and pour vinegar mixture over peaches.
Seal jars with rings and lids according to normal pickling instructions.

title: grated apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in unbaked pie shell for 1 hour at 350°.
Serve with Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: cashew chicken
directions: Mix soups, milk, rice, mushrooms, pimentos and chicken together.
Saute celery and onions in margarine.
Add to rest of ingredients.
Pour into 4-quart casserole.
Bake 2 hours at 350°. Last 30 minutes sprinkle cashews over top.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples
in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix together sugar, flour, cinnamon and oleo.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: frosted fruit salad
directions: Stir jello well in hot water.
Add 7-Up and chill a little. Stir in pineapple and mandarin oranges.
Let set up well.
Then combine in saucepan flour, sugar, egg and 1 cup pineapple juice over medium heat.
Stir well until thick; remove from heat.
Stir together butter, cream cheese and Cool Whip and mix well.
Spread over congealed gelatin; add crushed pecans.
Chill well.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Bake crescent rolls.
Let them cool.
Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise, garlic salt and dill weed; spread on top of rolls. Dice vegetables and spread on top.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: apple pie
directions: Slice apples and place in crust. Place remaining ingredients on top of apples. Place second pie crust on top. Slit about 6 slits in crust. Sprinkle top with a little cinnamon & sugar. Bake at 350 degrees for about 1 hour or until brown.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger meat.
Drain grease and add salt, chili powder, tomato sauce and refried beans; simmer.
Put meat mixture over Doritos. Top with grated Cheddar cheese, chopped lettuce and tomato, taco sauce and sour cream.

title: lime cottage cheese mold
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Add marshmallows and cream cheese. Stir until melted.
Chill until slightly thickened, then add salt, pineapple and cottage cheese.
Fold in whipped cream and nuts. Pour into pan or mold.
Chill until firm.

title: wedding punch
directions: Combine all ingredients together and stir until sugar has dissolved.
Chill.
Use some of this to put into a mold and freeze to use as an ice mold or freeze some Kool-Aid, if desired.
This recipe serves approximately 75 people.

title: peach pie
directions: Line a pie pan with crust.
Peel peaches.
Spread flour on crust and place fruit, cut in half, on crust.
Leave some space between halves.
Beat eggs, add sugar and cream; pour over fruit and place in oven.
Cook until the custard is firm, then add top crust without removing from oven.
Bake until crust is done; reduce the temperature of oven and bake slowly 1/2 to 3/4 of an hour. Serve cold.

title: souper meat loaf
directions: Mix 1/2 cup mushroom soup and onion soup.
Mix beef, crumbs and egg.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours; spoon off fat.
In a 1-quart pan, combine remaining mushroom soup, water and reserved drippings (1 to 2 tablespoons).
Heat through, stirring occasionally.

title: loaded down potato soup
directions: Saute onions and celery in butter.
Dice potatoes and cook until tender in small amount of water.
Add sauteed onions and celery.
Add cream, salt, pepper, garlic powder and thyme.
Cook about 15 minutes.
Add Cheddar cheese soup.
Sprinkle with bacon bits.

title: bread stuffing for poultry
directions: In a Dutch oven, brown and crumble sausage.
Melt 1 stick of margarine in the pot. Add celery, onion, water chestnuts and mushrooms. Going by the directions on the stuffing package, add the amount of margarine called for.
In place of some of the water, add chicken broth. Simmer mixture for 20 minutes.
Add the dry stuffing mix and blend in well.
Cool first, if stuffing the poultry.
If cooking in a baking dish, cover and bake for 45 minutes.

title: vanilla wafer squares
directions: Finely crush wafers.
Combine wafers and melted margarine. Press into 13x9 baking dish.
Sprinkle with pecans and morsels, drizzle with caramel.
Bake at 350 degrees for 12- 15 minutes. Makes approximatly 4 dozen squares.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all
ingredients
and pour into unbaked pie shells. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: easy chicken pasta
directions: In skillet over medium heat put 1 tablespoon oil.
Add chicken and brown.
Add soup, water and vegetable combination.
Heat to a boil.
Cover and cook over low heat for 5 minutes.

title: ribbon salad
directions: Prepare lime jello as directed on package.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan and chill.
Combine lemon jello, hot water and mini marshmallows and stir over low heat until melted.
Remove from heat and add pineapple juice and cream cheese and beat slightly. Add crushed pineapple.
Cool mixture.
Fold in whipped cream and Miracle Whip; chill.
Pour over set lime jello.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Combine apples, marshmallows, thin celery slices and walnuts. Add enough salad dressing to moisten.
Miracle Whip is best.
Toss lightly.
Chill.

title: freezer slaw
directions: Cover the shredded cabbage with water.
Add salt.
Let stand one hour.
Boil together vinegar, water, sugar, celery seed and mustard seed.
Let boil one minute.
Let stand until lukewarm. Squeeze water completely out of cabbage.
Combine cabbage, carrot and pepper.
Pour liquid mixture over all.
Mix well.
Place in containers and freeze.

title: blackberry almond-cream fool
directions: In a medium bowl, beat the heavy cream until stiff.
Fold in the sour cream, sugar and almond extract.
Reserve some of the berries for garnish.
Place the rest of the berries in 4 dessert bowls or wine glasses and top with the almond cream.
Crumble 1 cookie over each serving and garnish with the reserved berries. Serve immediately.

title: india potatoes and tomatoes
directions: Fry mustard seeds in hot oil (be careful they can burn quickly).
Add diced potatoes and fry 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes, green pepper, turmeric, grated ginger, cayenne, salt and coriander leaves.
Cook slowly until tomatoes are done.
Remove from fire and serve hot.

title: heart-healthy garlic cheese grits
directions: Bring water to a rapid boil with salt; gradually stir in grits with fork.
Cook until all water is absorbed.
Stir in margarine; little by little carefully add Scramblers, cheese, garlic and cayenne pepper.
Place into greased 2 1/2 quart casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: banana bread(makes 4 loaves)
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs; beat well.
Add bananas.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt; mix only until blended.
Add nuts.
Mix.
Pour into 4 x 9-inch oiled loaf pans. Bake 50 minutes at 350°.

title: creamed celery
directions: Cook together the celery, salt, sugar and vinegar until the celery is tender, not using more water than necessary.
Add a sauce made with the flour and a little milk.
Bring everything to a boil, then stir in the salad dressing or mayonnaise.

title: schmant kuchen
directions: Soften yeast in lukewarm water.
Pour water over sugar and salt in a bowl.
Stir until dissolved and slightly cooled.
Add 1 1/2 cups flour and beat until smooth.
Beat in shortening, eggs and remaining flour.
Mix to a soft dough.
Turn out on a lightly floured board.
Knead vigorously for 5 to 10 minutes or until dough becomes satiny.
Place in lightly greased bowl, greasing top of dough.
Cover with a greased wax paper and allow to rise in a warm place until double in bulk (1 to 1 1/2 hours).

title: baked eggplant with ham
directions: Combine lemon juice with water.
Peel eggplant and dice.
Dip in the lemon water.
Rinse again in cold water.
Parboil the diced eggplant about 10 minutes.
Saute onion and ham in butter.
Add eggplant and beaten egg.
Mix well; put mixture in greased 1-quart casserole.
Combine cheese and buttered bread crumbs and sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: kentucky blackberry dumplings
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder into mixing bowl.
Add egg and mix well.
Add enough milk to make a stiff batter.
Place blackberries, water and sugar on stove; bring to a boil.
Drop the dumpling batter by a spoonful at a time into boiling mixture. Cover and cook for about 15 to 20 minutes.
Can be served with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: lasagna a la marie
directions: Brown ground
beef
and onion.	Drain.	Stir in seasonings and tomato sauce.
Simmer slowly for 20 minutes.

title: barbecued meatballs
directions: Mix eggs, milk, bread crumbs, onions and salt.
Add meat; mix well.
Shape into 72 one-inch balls.
Bake in two 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch baking pans at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool meatballs and freeze, putting 24 meatballs in a package.

title: easy whole wheat bread
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a large bowl and set aside. Heat milk and cooking oil.
Cool to lukewarm and beat in egg.
Add flour mixture; beat 1/2 minute at low speed, then 3 minutes at medium speed.
Gradually add 1 cup whole wheat flour and 3 1/2 cups white flour to form a soft dough.

title: icing
directions: Cook milk and flour until it forms a paste.
Chill in refrigerator for 2 hours.
In mixer, put butter, Crisco, sugar, vanilla and salt.
Mix together, then add mixture from refrigerator and mix until creamy.
"Icing can be frozen and used later.
Just beat with a mixer."

title: orange coconut balls
directions: Mix well and form into small balls.
Let set for 20 minutes and then roll in glaze.

title: meatless nacho skillet casserole
directions: In a large skillet, brown ground beef and onion.

Drain well. Stir in sugar, oregano, chili powder, kidney beans, tomato sauce and corn. Simmer 10 to 20 minutes, stirring occasionally, until moisture is absorbed. Sprinkle chips over mixture and top with cheese. Cover and simmer 2 to 3 minutes until cheese melts.

title: date balls
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine butter, dates, coconut and sugar.
Cook over medium heat for 7 minutes.
Remove from heat. Add Rice Krispies and nuts.
Shape into 1-inch balls and roll in powdered sugar.
Makes 36.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix well the first 7 ingredients;
set aside.
Combine slightly beaten eggs, salad oil, water and pumpkin.
Mix well. Add to dry ingredients;
mix well.
Spoon into greased loaf pan. Bake at 350° for one hour or until done.

title: mother's chicken with sherry
directions: Place chicken pieces in a shallow pan.
Heat together consomme, orange juice and sherry in saucepan.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Bake 1 hour in a 350° oven.
Serves 4.

title: lemony chicken cutlets
directions: Bone chicken breast.
Pound chicken to 1/8-inch thickness. Mix flour, salt and pepper.
Lightly coat chicken.
Reserve remaining flour mixture.

title: pumpkin crunch
directions: Mix eggs, milk, sugar, pumpkin, and spices.
Pour into 9 X 13 baking pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over top.
Drizzle melted butter over cake mix and sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: swiss steak
directions: In a bowl, beat egg.
Dip meat in egg wash, then in flour. Brown in a small amount of vegetable oil.
Put steaks in a baking pan.
Meanwhile, add flour to the drippings in the pan and brown a bit.
Add water, hot sauce, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper. Bring to a boil.
Add onions and carrots to meat; pour gravy over meat.
You may need to make additional gravy to cover meat.
Cover with foil and bake in 350° oven until meat is done and vegetables are tender.
Good served with mashed potatoes or rice.

title: spanish noodle casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly brown ground chuck, bell pepper and onion in oil.
Add tomato soup, tomato sauce, pimentos, olives and corn.
Mix in dry mustard, chili powder, salt and pepper.
In a buttered 3-quart casserole dish, alternate layers of noodles and sauce.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: jim bennett's lasagne
directions: Brown meat.
While meat is browning, put cloves of garlic, onion, bell pepper, oregano, basil, garlic salt, tomatoes and tomato paste in a food processor and make a sauce.
When meat is browned, drain and add to sauce.
Simmer, uncovered, until thick (45 minutes to 1 hour), stirring frequently.
Cook noodles in boiling salted water until tender; drain and rinse in cold water. Combine cottage cheese with eggs, pepper, parsley and Parmesan cheese and mix well.

title: baked o & p's
directions: Oil a large flat cookie sheet.
Place potatoes on sheet, then onion rings.
Sprinkle with green onions.
Layer bacon strips on top.
Pour water on sheet.
Sprinkle with seasonings and cover with foil.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Remove foil the last 2 to 3 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: polish mistakes
directions: Brown meat and drain. Cube cheese and add to meat mixture with peppers and garlic. Mix until cheese is melted and spread on rye bread. Bake at 325 degrees for 15 to 20 minutes until browned and bubbly.

title: german spinach
directions: Cook spinach in water until done.
Fry bacon.
Remove from pan.
Add onion; cook until tender.
Mix onion, cracker crumbs and beaten egg with the spinach.
Add pepper.
Sprinkle chopped bacon on top.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles until tender.
Cook peas in separate pan.
Drain noodles; put in large pot.
Add drained peas.
Stir in all ingredients; simmer on medium heat for 10 minutes.

title: cheesy chive potatoes
directions: Dice cooked potatoes. Combine sour cream, cottage cheese, chives, garlic, salt and pepper.
Add to potatoes.
Place into a quart casserole. Top with Cheddar cheese and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: prima vera pasta salad
directions: Cook rotini.
Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Use Good Seasons dressing mix dry from package.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: beets
directions: Mix cornstarch in with sugar to prevent lumps. Drain broth off beets into pot, then add vinegar to broth. Add sugar with cornstarch into broth and let cook over medium heat until thick. Add beets into thickened broth and let simmer.

title: pastry dough
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt.
Cut in shortening.
Add vinegar, egg and water.
Makes 6 or 7 pie crusts.
May be frozen.

title: meat loaf
directions: Brown onion and pepper.
Drain and add to hamburger meat.
Add egg, crushed crackers, about 1/2 cup ketchup and salt and pepper to taste.
Mix well and put in loaf pan.
Top with ketchup.
Bake at 350° for about an hour.

title: apple crumb pie
directions: Pare apples; cut into eighths.
Arrange in unbaked pie shell. Mix 1/2 cup sugar with the cinnamon; sprinkle over apples.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar with the flour; cut in butter until crumbly. Sprinkle over apples.
Bake in hot oven (400°) for 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: miniature pecan tarts(makes 2 dozen)
directions: Cream together cream cheese and butter until well blended. Add flour; mix well.
Divide into 24 balls and refrigerate 1 hour. Press each ball into bottom and side of ungreased miniature muffin pan.

title: creamy delight
directions: Mix and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° approximately 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: peach pops
directions: Combine all ingredients; stir well.
Spoon mixture evenly into 10 frozen-pop molds or 3-ounce paper cups.
Insert wooden sticks. Freeze until firm.
Yields 10 servings.

title: onion soup(short cut)
directions: Saute onions in margarine with salt and pepper.
Add small amount of water so onions will cook and soften, but not brown or burn.
Heat consomme and water.
Add onions with their liquid. Simmer about 1 hour.
Serve with toast points and cheese.

title: party oyster crackers
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Store in airtight container.
Better if mixed a day or more before needed.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Remove yellow centers from hard-boiled eggs.
Place in a small bowl.
Add other ingredients and mix until smooth.
Re-fill eggs with mixture and sprinkle with paprika.
Refrigerate until serving time.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Combine cake mix, eggs, water, margarine, brown sugar and nuts. Mix well and spread in two 12-inch pizza pans (greased and floured).
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Spread the whipped topping on top.
Top with 3 to 5 kinds of your favorite fruit (drained; blueberries, strawberries, peaches, kiwi fruit etc.).
Heat apricot preserves and 2 tablespoons water and drizzle over fruit.
Keep refrigerated.

title: pumpkin cheese roll
directions: Beat the eggs at high speed for 5 minutes.
Beat in the sugar. Stir in the pumpkin and lemon juice.
Sift together dry ingredients and fold into the pumpkin mixture.
Spread on a greased and floured cookie sheet (15 x 10 1/2 x 1/2-inch).
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Turn out on a towel sprinkled with powdered sugar.
Roll as like a jelly roll and cool.

title: red cabbage german style
directions: Cut cabbage in fine shreds; add a little boiling water and cook about 10 minutes, or until tender, but still crisp; drain. Peel and core apples and cut in thin slices.
Cover in water and cook until tender.
Drain.
Melt butter in large skillet.
Add cabbage and apples.
Cook several minutes.
Stir in flour thoroughly.
Add remaining ingredients and cook over low heat for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serves 6.

title: gourmet casserole
directions: Brown sausage or hamburger and drain.
Mix with other ingredients and bake, covered, until bubbly.

title: my grandma's sugar cookies
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and beat until creamy.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chill dough in refrigerator for 24 hours.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Cook macaroni according to package directions and drain.
Add no salt.
Combine macaroni with all ingredients except the bread crumbs.
Spoon the mixture into a 1-quart baking dish that has been wiped with oil.
Spring bread crumbs on top.
Bake for 1 hour.
Serves 6 (2/3 cup servings).

title: classic glorified chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Meanwhile, in a 2-quart oblong dish, arrange chicken, skin side up.
Drizzle with butter.
Bake 40 minutes.

title: chocolate intrigue
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream butter, gradually adding sugar.
Blend in one egg at a time, beating well after each addition.

title: monkey bread(children love this treat)
directions: Cut each biscuit into 4 pieces.
Combine 1/2 cup brown sugar with 1 1/2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Put mixture into Ziploc bag and shake to coat each biscuit.

title: good and easy black beans
directions: Saute onion and garlic in olive oil.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Pull the stems out of mushrooms.
Stuff with cream cheese. Wrap 1/2 slice bacon around mushrooms and fasten with toothpick. Bake at 350° until bacon is brown or crisp.

title: carrot cake
directions: Blend together sugar, eggs and oil; add dry ingredients.
Beat one minute.
Add carrots, pineapple and nuts.
Mix in well.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until done.

title: sourdough biscuits
directions: Place flour in a large bowl.
Make a hole in the middle and add sourdough
starter to the hole.
Add melted shortening and dry ingredients.
Mix
from the middle, stirring in enough flour to make a
soft
dough.
Turn out onto a lightly floured board. Knead until
the
consistency of bread dough.
Roll to 1/2-inch thickness.	Cut
into
biscuits
and place in greased 12-inch Dutch oven,
making
sure
to
grease
sides,
top and bottom of biscuits.
Let
rise
for 1 hour in cold Dutch oven. Bake for 20 minutes on medium heat (350° to 375°).

title: chocolate milk shake
directions: Put ingredients in shaker; stir until mixed.
Shake until frosty.
Serve.
Serves 2.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix together sugar, oil, zucchini, eggs and vanilla.
Sift together flour, salt, soda, baking powder and cinnamon.
Add to sugar mixture, stirring in walnuts.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes at 350°.

title: "chicken and broccoli"(quick and easy)
directions: Dice Prosciuttini into small pieces.
Melt butter in pan and add Prosciuttini.
Slowly cook for 5 minutes or so.
Whip the heavy cream.
Fold the cream into the melted butter that you have removed from the stove.

title: cherry cream cheese bread
directions: Thoroughly blend softened cream cheese, butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs one at a time.
Mix well after each addition. Gradually add 2 cups of sifted flour with baking powder.
Combine rest of flour with cherries and nuts.
Fold into batter.
Grease three coffee cans.
Divide batter evenly between cans.
Bake at 325° one hour.

title: banana cake
directions: Combine above ingredients in electric mixer.
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350° or until toothpick comes out clean.
Ice with cream cheese icing.

title: spiced hot cocoa
directions: Combine cocoa, sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt in saucepan. Blend in hot water. Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly. Boil and stir 2 minutes.
Add milk.
Heat to serving temperature, stirring occasionally.
Do not boil. Remove from heat and add vanilla and cloves.
Beat with rotary beater until foamy. Serve hot.

title: champagne cake
directions: Mix cake and bake as directed on package.
Cool.
Mix pudding as directed on box, then mix with cream cheese.
Beat until creamy.
Spread over cooled cake.
Then top with pineapple.
Top pineapple with Cool Whip.
Keep refrigerated.

title: bean soup then bake for baked beans
directions: Wash, drain and put beans in kettle.
Cover with water and bring to boiling.
Boil 2 minutes.
Cover and let stand for 1 hour.
Add onions, tomato juice and hambone or ham.
Boil gently for several hours.
Add water as needed.
Use as soup the first meal, then bake for a second meal.
You might have enough left to put a casserole of beans in the freezer.
A very thrifty and tasty, healthy food.

title: mock strawberry preserves
directions: Wash figs in warm water.
Remove stems and cut figs in half. Cook figs and sugar over low heat until syrup is thick.
Add jello and cook until jello is dissolved.
Put in jars as you regularly do for preserves and jellies.

title: sausage cheese puffs
directions: Combine ingredients; let set overnight in refrigerator.
Shape into balls the size of walnuts; place on baking sheet.
Cook at 350° until brown.
Yields 75 to 100.

title: jaja's gingerbread
directions: Mix shortening, brown sugar, egg, molasses, flour and spices. Add water and soda.
Pour into greased pan and bake at 350° until done.

title: broccoli quiche(microwave)
directions: Finely chop broccoli; mince onion.
In a 9-inch quiche dish, cook broccoli and onion, covered, on High 5 minutes.
Set aside. Heat half and half on 50% power 2 minutes.
In bowl beat half and half and eggs.
Stir in cheese and pepper.
Pour over vegetables in dish. Stir gently.
Elevate dish on rack or inverted plate. Cook on medium 14 minutes until knife comes out clean, rotating dish twice.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: spanish rice
directions: Chop and fry bacon.
Drain and keep half of grease.
Remove bacon from pan.
Saute green pepper and onion in grease.
Puree tomatoes (with liquid) in blender.
Add to green pepper, onion and sugar.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Add cooked rice and bacon.
Pour into buttered casserole dish or 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake (uncovered) at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: praline cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add egg and vanilla.
Stir in flour and shape 1 level tablespoonful of dough to about 1/8 inch thick on buttered baking sheet 1 inch apart.
Bake 12 minutes at 375°.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: pot roast
directions: Cut onion into small pieces as well as garlic cloves and bell pepper.
Cut potatoes into chunks.
Stuff roast with garlic.
Fry roast in grease until brown on the outside.
Then take roast out of pot and drain grease.
Fry onions until golden brown; take out. Put roast, onion, bell pepper, garlic and mushroom sauce in pan; add potatoes and water.
Bake at 400° about 1 1/2 hours or until cooked.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together.
Add the melted butter. Then mix altogether.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 250° for 25 minutes.

title: lemon lime yogurt pie
directions: In a large bowl, stir boiling water into lemon and lime gelatins until thoroughly dissolved.
Stir in ice cubes.
With wire whisk, beat in yogurt until blended and smooth.
Pour into pie shell; chill.
Makes 1 pie.

title: pigeon pea's rice
directions: *Can be found in the Spanish food section of the supermarket.

title: watergate salad
directions: Combine dry pudding mix, pineapple with juice and pecans.
Mix well.
Add marshmallows and fold in whipped topping.
Pour into container and chill.
May be served as salad or dessert.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Mix sour cream, gelatin and water until dissolved.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour half in a serving dish. Refrigerate until firm.
Spread with sour cream and top with the rest of the mixture.

title: quicky dark fudge
directions: Combine sugar, butter, salt and cream in saucepan.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Boil 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat; add chocolate, marshmallows, nuts and vanilla extract.
Beat vigorously until marshmallows are melted.
Pour into buttered 8-inch square pan.
Sprinkle with additional nuts, if desired.
Cool; cut into squares.

title: bay scallops in garlic sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Melt butter over low heat.
Saute garlic until golden brown.
Remove garlic from pan.
To garlic butter, add sherry and scallops and saute for 2 to 3 minutes.

title: shrimp louis dip
directions: Stir all ingredients until well mixed.
Cover; chill.

title: dump-it-dessert
directions: Drain juice off pineapple chunks.
Blend milk, Cool Whip and cherry pie filling.
Fold in pineapple chunks.
Cover.
Chill at least 6 hours.
If desired, sprinkle with chopped pecans just before serving.

title: cheese quesadillas
directions: Place cheese and ham in center of tortilla, leaving a 1-inch border. Place another tortilla on top of mixture and press edges together as best you can to seal.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream sugar, eggs and shortening.
Add mashed bananas; stir in all remaining ingredients.
Pour into a greased loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: weekend stew
directions: Note: May add 1 can cream of mushroom soup for thicker base or 1 can tomato paste for more tomato flavor.

title: pudding squares
directions: Mix flour, walnuts and oleo until crumbly; press into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 15 minutes, until light brown. Cool crust.
Mix cream cheese, confectioners sugar and 1/2 container of Cool Whip, and spread on cooled crust.
Mix 2 packages of instant pudding with 3 cups of milk.
Pour on top of cream cheese spread.
Top with remaining 1/2 container of Cool Whip.
Refrigerate and cut into squares when serving.

title: angel cups
directions: Remove crusts from bread; butter generously on 1 side.
Place buttered side down in cupcake pans.
Drop an uncooked egg into each nest.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Serve with bacon or sausage.

title: corn flake macaroons
directions: Beat egg whites and cream of tartar until stiff.
Add sugar slowly, continuing to beat.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: sweet-sour sauce
directions: Mix brown sugar and cornstarch in 10-inch skillet.
Add enough water to reserved pineapple syrup to measure 2 1/4 cups.
Stir syrup/water mixture, vinegar, ketchup and soy sauce into skillet. Cook over medium high heat, stirring constantly, until it thickens and boils.
Stir in pineapple, pepper and onion.
Reduce heat. Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Serve over prepared pork or chicken.

title: apple-oatmeal crisp
directions: Pare apples, slice thinly and arrange in buttered 6 cup baking dish.
Melt butter in a medium size saucepan.
Stir in brown sugar, oatmeal, flour and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Sprinkle sliced apples with mixture of 1 teaspoon cinnamon, flour and 2 tablespoons sugar.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes or until golden brown.

title: sal's frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix all together and freeze in a shallow dish.
This is to be served as a slushy salad or dessert.
It can be used as a side dish, dessert or topping on angel food cake.

title: chipped beef dip
directions: Dice dried beef and green onions.
Mix with cream cheese and add other ingredients.
Put in prepared loaf and wrap in foil. Bake at 250° for 1 hour.

title: impossible pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour; add eggs and mix well.
Add remaining ingredients. Pour into 2 greased 9-inch aluminum foil pie pans. Bake at 350° until brown on top, about 35 minutes.

title: dill pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers; cut in lengthwise halves.
Combine salt, vinegar and water.
Heat to boiling.
Pack cucumbers into clean hot (1-pint) jars.
Add about 2 tablespoons dill seed and 3 peppercorns to each jar.
Fill with syrup to within 1/2-inch of jar top. Immediately adjust lids.
Process in boiling water bath (212°) for 15 minutes.
Remove jars from canner and complete seals unless closures are self-sealing type.
Makes 7 pints.

title: rice with shrimp (stove top)
directions: Cook vegetables in oil. Add rice and 2 cups hot water. Simmer until rice is nearly done. Add shrimp. Cook until rice is done. Season to taste.

title: egg noodles
directions: Beat egg yolks and 1 whole egg.
Add salt.
Stir flour into mixture until it sticks together.
Then divide into three balls. Knead flour into each ball until stiff.
Roll out thin on floured board and let dry.
Then roll noodles and cut desired width. Freeze until ready to use.

title: cheese ball
directions: In bowl, combine first 5 ingredients.
Add 1/2 cup pecans. Drain pineapple for several hours, then pat dry with paper towels. Mix all together in ball and roll in remaining pecans.
Serve with crackers.

title: crazy cake
directions: Pour into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 50 minutes or until done.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and brown sugar in bowl until light and fluffy.
Stir in oats, flour, eggs, soda, baking powder, salt, vanilla, chocolate chips and pecans.
Drop by teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool on cookie sheet for 2 minutes.
Remove to paper towel to cool completely.
Yield:
36 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix chicken, cream of chicken soup, chicken broth and sour cream together and put into a 9 x 13 inch casserole dish.
Place melted margarine and crackers on top of chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lemon blueberry coffee cake
directions: Combine mix, eggs, milk and peel.
Then stir into mix just until moistened.
Fold in drained blueberries.
Spoon into lightly greased 9-inch baking dish.
Combine sugar, ground pecans, flour and butter.
Spoon over mix.
Lightly stir into mix.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned and done.
Cool on rack 5 to 10 minutes.

title: appetizer meatballs
directions: Combine beef, salt, pepper, water chestnuts and water.
Mix thoroughly.
Form into small balls.
Roll lightly in flour.
Heat oil.
Brown meatballs; drain.
Makes 27 to 30 meatballs.

title: chocolate refrigerator cookies
directions: Beat butter, margarine or shortening until light.
Gradually add the sugar and beat until creamy.
Add the egg, cooled melted chocolate and vanilla.
Beat well.
Sift the flour, salt and baking powder.
Add the dry ingredients to the creamed mixture alternately with the milk, beating well after each addition.
Stir in the nuts.

title: mayo cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients first.
Mix all liquids, then mix all ingredients together.
Put in greased and floured cake pan.
Bake at 350°.

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients, except bread, in a bowl.
Let stand for 10 minutes.

title: camilla's corn pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: wonder cake
directions: Mix first five ingredients then add vinegar, vanilla, oil and water.
Pour into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 40 to 50 minutes in 350° oven.
Buttercream or Peanut Butter frosting is great on it.
Serves 24.

title: bean dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add enough mayonnaise to make dip smooth and creamy. Serve with Fritos or tortilla chips.

title: love in a pan
directions: Blend softened margarine and flour in mixer.
Add nuts and spread in 13 x 9 x 2-inch greased pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°. Let cool.

title: garden harvest
directions: Microwave corn, onion (sliced) and green pepper (sliced) for 2 minutes on High.
Add rest of ingredients except tomato and microwave for 7 minutes on High, stirring once.
Add tomato and microwave for 2 minutes.
Serve.

title: slush
directions: Bring water and sugar to a boil; cool.
Add other ingredients and place in 5-quart container.
Add 2 cups peach Schnapps before freezing.
Freeze, stir occasionally.

title: jelly roll sponge cake
directions: Beat egg whites first and leave until last to fold in.
Beat yolks; add water and beat in sugar until creamy.
Add flour, baking powder, vanilla and salt.
Stir until well mixed.
Fold in egg whites.
Bake in shallow pan.
Bake in 300° oven about 20 minutes.

title: icebox oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs.
Sift soda, salt and flour.
Then add to Crisco and sugar mixture.
Add vanilla and oats.
Mixture will be very stiff, but should be moist enough to roll into rolls.
Freeze or chill.
Slice.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; blend into egg and applesauce. Combine soda and boiling water.
Sift together flour, salt, cinnamon, cloves and allspice.
Add water mixture alternately with flour mixture.
Blend in raisins and walnuts.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Frost with Butterscotch Icing.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Place carrots in saucepan.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Add zucchini; boil 5 minutes longer.

title: reese's peanut butter candy
directions: In large bowl, mix butter, graham crackers, peanut butter and powdered sugar.
Press down well into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
In a double boiler, melt the chocolate chips, then spread on top of the peanut butter mixture.
Refrigerate until firm.
Cut into squares. Makes 50 squares.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Heat 2 cups juice from fruit, dissolve jello in hot juice. Add orange juice.
Chill and add fruit.
Prepare pudding with milk.
Prepare Dream Whip as directed.
Combine pudding and Dream Whip; spread on jello when it has set.
Chill.

title: cheese grits souffle
directions: Mix together.
Put in greased dish and bake at 275° for 45 minutes.
Will keep warm for 2 to 3 hours in electric skillet or warmer.

title: lemon cheesecake
directions: Mix and press into a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: tuna pita sandwich
directions: Combine tuna, mayonnaise and mustard.
Chop lettuce and tomatoes.
Cut pita bread in half. Fill with tuna, lettuce and tomatoes.
Add dressing as desired.
Microwave 15 seconds or serve cold.

title: microwave chicken continental
directions: Combine all ingredients in baking dish. Microwave on High 15 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: chile mac ole
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
In medium saucepan, heat remaining ingredients (reserving 1/4 cup cheese) until cheese melts, stirring frequently.
Arrange macaroni on platter.
Pour chili mixture over.
Top with remaining cheese.

title: mustard sauce for vegetables
directions: Whisk all ingredients together.
Serve over hot vegetables or as a salad dressing.

title: chow mein
directions: Dice onion.
Brown meat.
Put onion in pressure cooker with meat and celery or simmer on stove for about 2 hours with 1 cup water.
Cook for about 5 minutes after pressure is up, then let stand until pressure goes completely down.
Add in remaining ingredients.
Thicken with flour and season to taste. Serve over rice or with chow mein noodles.

title: cheesy chicken
directions: Wash chicken, salt & pepper.
Place chicken in baking dish. Mix remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350 degrees.
Makes good gravy to go over rice or potatoes.

title: pumpkin ring
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 12-cup Bundt pan or tube pan (10 x 4-inch).
Beat first 8 ingredients on low for 30 seconds, scraping bowl constantly.
Beat on medium 3 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally.
Spread in prepared pan.
Bake 50 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool 10 minutes; remove from pan and cool completely.
Drizzle with glaze made with remaining 3 ingredients.

title: smoked turkey
directions: You will also need charcoal.

title: brownies
directions: Melt butter and chocolate over low heat.
Remove from heat and stir.
Stir in sugar and beat in eggs and vanilla.
Quickly stir in flour and salt and lightly mix.
Spread onto greased baking 8x10 inch baking pan, and bake at 325° for 35 minutes.
Allow to cool, then cut into squares with greased knife.

title: oreo ice cream
directions: Whip the cream and mix all other ingredients. Pour into a foil lined dish. Cover and freeze 6 hours.

title: witches' stew
directions: Brown ground beef; drain grease.
Add remaining ingredients; let simmer for 10 minutes.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Combine and toss well.

title: mousse au chocolat
directions: Melt chocolate chips with milk in a saucepan over warm burner. Beat egg yolks.
Add sugar and melted chocolate.
Add butter. Beat egg whites separately until very firm.
Wrap into chocolate mixture.
Refrigerate; serve chilled.

title: supper club enchiladas
directions: Combine soups, sour cream and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Heat.
Dip tortillas in hot soup mix.
Fill with meat, cheese and onion.
Roll up and place in greased dish.
Pour remaining mixture over enchiladas.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top after baking and return to oven to melt.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Mix together
yeast
and water.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix together and
cover in bowl.
Let rise until double in bulk. Punch down	and
work
flour in to make stiff dough. Make rolls. Let rise
in
greased pan.	Bake at 425° about 20 minutes.	Unused dough may be stored in refrigerator.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Mix all ingredients with a fork until moist.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake for 1 hour and 20 minutes at 325°. Remove from oven; cool on rack.
When cake is cool, frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Combine sugar, butter or margarine and milk in buttered large glass mixing bowl.
Cover with plastic wrap (vented).
Microwave 10 minutes on Medium-high.
Stir and continue cooking on Medium-high for 5 to 8 minutes or until mixture forms a soft ball in cold water.
Stir in chocolate pieces until melted.
Fold in Marshmallow Creme, nuts and vanilla.
Pour into buttered 13 x 9-inch inch pan.
Chill until firm; cut into squares.
Makes 74 fudge squares.

title: cranberry cheese bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl combine flour, oats, 3/4 cup sugar and oleo.
Mix until crumbly.
Reserving 1 1/2 cups crumb mixture, press remainder on bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes.
In small bowl beat cheese until fluffy. Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk; stir in lemon juice. Spread evenly over prepared crust.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix hamburger, rice, applesauce and seasonings together.
Form meat balls into size of walnuts.
Place on ungreased pan.
(Cake pan works well.)
Mix ketchup, barbecue sauce and water.
Pour over meat balls.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: oatmeal cookie candy
directions: Bring sugar, milk, cocoa and oleo to boil and cook for 2 minutes.
Add peanut butter and oats.
Mix well and drop on wax paper quickly.

title: casserole for the crowd
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Add cream of chicken soup, cream of mushroom soup, corn, pimento, sour cream, salt and pepper.
Simmer for 30 to 45 minutes.
Cook egg noodles per package;
place noodles in large casserole dish and pour mixture over noodles.
Stir well.
Sprinkle top with grated cheese and bread crumbs mixed together.
Bake in a 350° oven until cheese melts and casserole begins to brown.
Time is about 30 to 45 minutes.

title: mild mustard sauce
directions: Melt butter in a heavy saucepan over low heat.
Add flour and salt, stirring until smooth.
Gradually add milk, cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cook until thoroughly heated.
Serve hot with roast beef or ham.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients; blend in butter. Stir soda into applesauce. Mix all together. Bake in 350° oven approximately 1 hour.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cool carrots after cooking and add the other ingredients. Chill for 12 hours before serving.

title: new year's black-eyed peas
directions: Melt bacon drippings in large cast-iron Dutch oven.
Saute onion until translucent.
Add garlic and pepper, then add black-eyed peas.
Cover with water and simmer over low heat for 45 minutes or until the peas are tender, then add salt to taste.
(Do not add salt until the very end or it will make the skin on the peas split open.)

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Fry eggplant in olive oil on all sides.
Wilt onion, garlic, celery and bell pepper in olive oil, then add shrimp and fry until it is pink.
Add eggplant which was previously cooked and a cup of water. Cook slowly for about 1/2 hour.
Add bread crumbs and more water, if needed.
Put in casserole dish and top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: old-fashioned walnut balls
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla until fluffy.
Sift flour and salt together; add to creamed mixture.
Mix well; stir in walnuts. Shape dough into walnut-sized balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheet with spatula.
When still warm but cool enough to handle, roll in powdered sugar.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: famous amos delightful double-decker
directions: Prepare cake layers:
Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch cake pan.
Prepare batter for devil's food cake as directed, but using 1 egg, 1/2 cup oil and no water.
Pat evenly into prepared pan.
Bake 15 to 18 minutes until dry to touch.
Remove pan from oven and sprinkle hot crust with chocolate chips.
Let stand 2 or 3 minutes.
Smooth melted chips thinly over first layer. Prepare white cake according to package directions, beating in drink mix.
Pour over crust.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes until toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Cool.
Beat cream and powdered sugar until stiff.
Spread on cake.
Decorate with cocoa powder and nuts.

title: marshmallow puffs(kids recipe)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut 18 large marshmallows in half with scissors.
(Dip scissors into glass of water to keep the marshmallows from sticking.)
Arrange 36 wafers on ungreased cookie sheet.
Place 1 marshmallow half, cut side down, on each wafer. Bake 4 to 5 minutes at 350° or until the marshmallows puff, but before they tip over.
Refrigerate the cookie on sheet for 10 minutes.
Heat the chips and the margarine in saucepan until chocolate melts, stirring.
Dip the tops of the cooled cookies into the chocolate mixture.
Refrigerate about 15 minutes or until set. Store leftover cookies in the refrigerator.

title: burger bean bake
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Add the ground beef and brown.
Add onions and heat through.
Add all other ingredients and mix well. Put in a baking dish and bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes, or until bubbly.

title: chocolate chip zucchini cake
directions: Cream margarine, oil and sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time. Add vanilla and buttermilk.
Sift dry ingredients and add slowly to creamed mixture.
Stir in zucchini.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake for 45 minutes at 325°.

title: asparagus soup
directions: Cook asparagus in broth and butter.
Mix in blender.
Add milk, salt and pepper.
Warm; do not bring to boil.

title: chocolate peanut squares
directions: Microwave 3/4 cup butter & 2 oz.
(1/3 cup) of chocolate on high 1-2 minutes until melted when stirred.
Stir every 30 seconds. Stir in crumbs, coconut & peanuts.
Press into bottom of 13 X 9 pan.
Chill 30 minutes.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla until well blended.
Spread over crust.
Chill 30 minutes.
Microwave remaining butter & chocolate on high 1-2 minutes or until melted when stirred, stirring every 30 seconds.
Spread over cream cheese layer (I just tilted the cake pan and let the melted chocolate run from one side of the pan to the other to coat the top evenly. Chill.
Cut into squares.

title: fried cabbage and noodles
directions: Fry, in slow fry pan, bacon until medium crisp.
Add onion and continue cooking until done.
Add cabbage until medium done. Prepare noodles to directions, drain and rinse.
Combine all ingredients and put in large baking dish.
Place in oven at 300° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve hot with Parmesan cheese.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: christmas punch(serves 15)
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add water to make 1 gallon.
Freeze. Thaw and add 1 1/2 (2 liter) bottles of ginger ale to serve.

title: ravioli
directions: Brown meat and onion in skillet with a little butter. Make dough while browning. Mix flour, salt, 3 eggs and water. Mix dough until soft and smooth, not sticky. Divide dough. Roll one half of dough as for a large pizza. When hamburger is brown add spinach and mix. Remove from heat and add 2 eggs and the cheese. Season with salt and pepper to taste. Place a tablespoon of filling every two inches on the rolled out piece of dough making sure they are all uniformed. Roll out second piece of dough. Carefully place this dough over the rows of filling. Cut ravioli into squares. pinch and seal edges of each square. Drop into boiling water and cook for 6-8 minutes. Remove from water and place on a serving dish. Top with your favorite red sauce.

title: pizza salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine macaroni, tomatoes, cheese, onion and pepperoni.

title: christmas salad
directions: Mix lemon and lime jello with 2 cups boiling water.
Mix Eagle Brand milk, mayonnaise and cottage cheese into jello mixture.
Add pineapple and nuts. Chill.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger; drain off grease and cool.
Add lettuce, tomato, cheese, onion and mayonnaise; toss lightly.
Add corn chips; toss well.
Yields 6 servings.

title: crunchy salad
directions: Mix all ingredient except chow mein noodles.
Fold in noodles before serving.

title: brown cow mocha coffee
directions: Place Kahlua, brandy, syrup and cinnamon in a coffee mug. Fill with hot coffee and stir to blend.
Top with sweetened whipped cream.
This makes 1 serving.

title: fettuccine with chicken and sun-dried tomatoes
directions: Saute onions and garlic in skillet until wilted.
Add chicken strips and brown, stirring chicken frequently.
Add basil and sun-dried tomatoes and saute for another minute or two.
Cook pasta according to package.
Drain.
Toss hot fettuccine and sauce together.
Add extra oil from the tomatoes.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serves 4.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Brown sausage; drain grease.
Break bread into small pieces. Beat eggs with fork.
Mix all ingredients together, except sausage; mix that last.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sausage rolls
directions: Sift dry ingredients together. Add oil and milk, enough to make stiff dough. Roll into 2 rectangles. Spread sausage on this. Roll in lengthwise. Wrap each in wax paper and chill. Slice about 1/4-inch thick. Bake at 350° about 20 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cook onion in margarine until tender.
Add sour cream to make sauce.
Place beans in baking dish; cover with sauce.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Crush corn flakes to cover cheese; top with melted margarine.
Bake at 350° until hot.

title: pork tenderloins
directions: Brown meat on all sides in the butter or margarine; remove meat.
In same skillet, cook onion until tender.
Add orange peel and juice, sherry, sugar, salt, pepper and bay leaf.
Return meat, cover and simmer 1 hour or until tender, turning occasionally. Remove meat to hot platter; slice.

title: cole slaw
directions: Bring first 5 ingredients to a boil.
Place cabbage, onion, red pepper and green pepper in large bowl.
Pour hot vinegar solution over cabbage mixture.
Let stand 2 hours, then cover and refrigerate.
Keeps about 1 month.

title: kraut salad
directions: Heat sugar, oil, vinegar, water and salt.
Cool.
When mixture is cool, combine with other ingredients and refrigerate overnight. Keeps well.

title: ground beef and noodle casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onions and cook until done.
Mix with all other ingredients and pour into baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until bubbly.

title: quick dessert royale
directions: Mix or cut butter into the cake mix. Put this mixture in 9-inch pan, reserving a little for topping. Make a "well" in middle of mixture. Put pie filling in middle of well; sprinkle reserved mixture (or crust) on top of filling.
Bake at 350° until "crust" starts to turn golden. Serve hot. May top with ice cream or Cool Whip

title: mom's apple crumb pie
directions: Core and cut apples in eighths, then put in unbaked pie shell. Add the 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon on top of apples. In a bowl, mix 1/3 cup of sugar, flour and butter. Mix until crumbly. Sprinkle on top of apples. Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: fiesta pudding
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add egg and fruit cocktail; mix and pour batter into an 8 x 12-inch pan.
Sprinkle brown sugar and nuts on top of batter.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Cut into squares.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: jerk pork chops
directions: In small bowl, mix together scallions, garlic, oil, lemon juice, honey, allspice, thyme, salt, pepper, cinnamon, nutmeg and hot sauce for jerk seasoning.
Place pork chops in large glass dish.
Rub jerk seasoning over both sides.
Cover and refrigerate for 2 hours.
Heat oven to 400 degree.
Heat grill pan over high heat.
Place chops on grill pan; cook 2 minutes per side.
Place chops in baking dish.
Bake in 400 degree oven for 18 to 20 minutes depending on thickness, or until internal temperature registers 155 degrees.
Let meat rest 10 minutes.
Serve with buttered red skinned potatoes, string beans and carrots.

title: vegetable garden dip(low-fat)
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Store in fridge.
May also be used as salad dressing.

title: peach pie
directions: Peel and chop peaches.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup sugar; set aside. Combine cream cheese, confectioners sugar, vanilla and Cool Whip. Fold in peaches.
Pour in graham cracker crust.
Refrigerate.

title: margaritas
directions: Heat 7-Up 2 to 2 1/2 minutes to melt jello.
Add liquor.
Pour into 1 ounce cups.
Chill to set.

title: cottage pudding
directions: Cook until smooth and slightly thickened.
Have a yellow cake baked.
Cut cake into individual pieces as needed and pour pudding over.
Best when eaten warm.

title: old-fashioned banana pudding
directions: Mix flour and sugar together.
Add milk and egg yolks and extract.
Stir well and cook on medium heat until thick.
Layer graham crackers or vanilla wafers, then pudding, sliced bananas; (makes about 3 layers).
Beat egg whites until stiff and put on pudding.
Bake in oven until the meringue is brown.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: Mash avocados with lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Combine sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning in a bowl.
Assemble as follows:
bean dip, avocado mixture, sour cream mixture, chopped vegetables (well drained) and cheese.

title: seven-up cake
directions: (Note:
Add eggs one at a time and lemon extract.)

title: spicy tomato punch(must be made at least 1 day in advance)
directions: In a 2-quart container, combine all ingredients.
Stir until well blended.
Cover and refrigerate 8 hours or overnight to allow flavors to blend.
Serve chilled with celery stalks.
Makes twelve 4-ounce servings.

title: hunter's stew
directions: Combine meat, bone, suet, celery, onion and water.
Simmer 2 1/2 hours.
Remove celery and bone.
Add vegetables with rice and simmer over low heat until vegetables are done.
Before serving, season with 1/2 cup chili sauce and more salt and pepper, if needed.
Should be a thick soup.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: pickled slaw
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in large bowl.
Combine rest of ingredients in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Pour over cabbage mixture.
Stir well and store in airtight container in refrigerator.

title: lunch in a skillet
directions: Cook bacon in deep skillet or Dutch oven.
Remove bacon from drippings.
Cut
steak
in
pieces.
Brown
in
bacon drippings.
(Do
not
dredge in flour.) Add salt and pepper to taste and
paprika.
Add
water.
Cover and cook about 2 hours in a 350°
oven.
Add water if needed.
Add the peeled vegetables about 1 hour after placing in the oven.

title: peanut butter date balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Make into 3/4-inch balls. Chill.
Dip in melted chocolate.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: salsa
directions: Pour salt on tomatoes, onions, pepper and celery.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
Drain well the next day; do not press vegetables.
Put in a large kettle and add black pepper, sugar and vinegar.
Cook until thick on low, stir and let boil.
Seal in jars.
One batch makes approximately 5 pints.

title: fried pies(berniece harbaugh's recipe)
directions: Sift together flour, baking soda, salt and sugar in a large bowl.
Add the shortening and cut into flour mixture.
Add milk and slightly beaten eggs.
Chill overnight.
Roll dough out thin to avoid being tough.
Don't handle dough too much or it will shrink. Cut a circle the size of a pie plate.
Be sure to lift dough before cutting.
Fill with fruit or pudding.
(Dried fruit makes easy to handle while eating.)
Place fruit on 1/2 side of the circle.
Wet edges with a little water.
Fold over and seal edges.
Fry in deep fat at 325° until golden brown on both sides.
Makes about 40 pies.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix green beans in casserole dish.
Layer onion and crumbled bacon.
Layer fried onion rings, then pour mixed soups over beans. Bake at 350° until soup on top is bubbling and golden brown.

title: pecan pumpkin bundt cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter a large Bundt cake pan liberally (I use Pam).
Mix and beat first 7 ingredients for 5 minutes.
Add 1/2 cup pecans.
Place whole pecans on bottom and sides of pan, secured to pan with pat of butter.
Pour batter in pan and bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Let cool for 15 minutes.
Loosen center and sides.
Invert and cool on wire rack.
Serve with Cool Whip or whipped cream.
Serves 24.

title: pineapple pecan cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine the first three ingredients. Mix well.
Stir in eggs, pineapple and pecans.
Pour into an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2 inch pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 40 to 45 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean.
Cool.

title: curried chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, water chestnuts, grapes, celery and almonds. Mix remaining ingredients and add to chicken.
Toss well.
Chill serveral hours.
Serve on lettuce.
Makes 12 servings.

title: sugar-free date cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Bring to boil the water, dates, prunes and raisins. Turn down to simmer and add butter. Stir until melted, then remove from heat and cool. Set aside.

title: japanese fruit cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs and beat.
Add allspice, flour and milk, beating after each addition. Sprinkle nuts, raisins and other fruit.
Add coconut and vanilla.
Mix well and pour into well-greased and floured pan. Bake for 35 to 40 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: chocolate peanut butter chip fudge
directions: Line an 8-inch square pan with foil.
In heavy saucepan (over low heat), melt chocolate chips with Eagle Brand milk, vanilla and salt.
Blend well.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter chips; stir in well.
Spread into prepared pan.
Refrigerate 2 hours, or until firm.
Remove from pan; peel foil and cut into squares. Store, tightly covered, in refrigerator.

title: my famous stuffing
directions: Saute celery and onion in melted oleo just until softened, not brown.
Crumble cornbread in large bowl; add cooked celery and onions.
Add beaten eggs.
Mix well.
Add sage and salt and pepper to taste.
Gradually mix in hot broth just until stuffing holds together.
Bake in large cake pan at 350° for 20 minutes.
Take pan out of oven and pour about 1 cup broth over top and bake for another 20 to 25 minutes until lightly brown.

title: sourdough starter
directions: Mix yeast with 1/2 cup lukewarm water.
Mix sugar with 2 cups water; add flour.
Add yeast to mixture.
Let stand in glass jar covered with a cloth for 5 days.
Then put in refrigerator for 3 to 5 days.
Take out and feed.

title: crisco cake batter
directions: Add eggs to other ingredients one at a time, beating after each one. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes until tests done.

title: chicken gamunda
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Add mushrooms, lemon juice and cooking sherry.
Beat eggs and oil together.
Combine bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Drop deboned chicken into flour and cover.
Dip chicken into egg/oil mixture.
Then dip chicken in bread crumbs/Parmesan cheese mixture.
Brown chicken in butter/mushroom mixture at 350° or until golden brown.
Top with mushrooms to serve.

title: dorothy's chicken
directions: Combine bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, oregano, garlic powder and Italian seasonings.
Heat olive oil in a 9-inch skillet.
Cut chicken into small pieces (nugget size).
Dip chicken in egg, then in bread crumb mixture.
Fry in olive oil.
Remove from oil and pat dry to get rid of excess oil.

title: olive spread
directions: Use soft cream cheese or let regular cream cheese come to room temperature.
Add a little olive juice; cream well.
Add cut-up olives and add to cream cheese.
Serve with crackers (Ritz, Town House, Triscuits, etc.).

title: mama matthew's chocolate pie
directions: Mix together (don't overmix) until soft dough ball.
Roll out (makes 2 pie crusts) between waxed and floured paper.
Put 1st crust in pie plate.

title: microwave cranapple raisin relish
directions: In 2-quart microwave safe bowl, combine sugar, raisins, apple juice and vinegar.
Cover with microwave-safe plastic wrap. Microwave on High for 5 to 6 minutes or until mixture boils.
Stir on orange peel, ginger, cranberries and apple. Cover; microwave on High for 6 to 8 minutes or until cranberries pop, stirring once halfway through cooking time.
Continue to microwave on High for 1 minute or until slightly thickened.
Stir in walnuts.
Cover; store in refrigerator up to 2 weeks.
Yields 4 cups.

title: broccoli topped potatoes
directions: Scoop out potato halves, leaving 1/4 in shell. Mix potato pulp with remaining ingredients. Fill potato shell with mixture, mounding slightly. Sprinkle with additional cheese. Broil until cheese is melted. 6 servings.

title: imperial crab
directions: Saute green pepper in the butter.
Mix together with the remaining ingredients, except for mayonnaise.
Put in individual shells or casserole dish.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes. Spread top of each crab shell or the casserole with mayonnaise and broil only until brown.

title: beef rice casserole
directions: Cut olives into large pieces.
Brown beef in oil; remove meat and drain.
To oil, add celery, onions, ground pepper and rice. Cook, stirring with fork, until browned.
Add tomatoes, water, seasonings, meat and olives; bring to a boil.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole dish and cover.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour. Serves 6 to 8.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Heat pineapple, sugar and lemon to a rolling boil.
Dissolve gelatin in cold water.
Add to pineapple mixture and cool.
Then add cheese, Milnot and salad dressing.
Let set in dish approximately 6 to 9 hours.
Shortly before serving, sprinkle on top the rest of ingredients.

title: dirt cake
directions: Prepare the pudding and refrigerate until set.
Crumble all of the cookies.
Combine 1/2 of cookies with all ingredients. Sprinkle remaining crumbs on top.
For an extra special treat in summer, buy a plastic flowerpot (no hole in bottom), follow instructions and put the pudding mixture in the flowerpot.
Stick a silk flower down in the pot and stick in some gummy worms. Children love it.

title: persimmon cookies
directions: Peel and mash very ripe persimmons so you have 1 cup of pulp. Cream shortening, sugar and egg; beat well.
Sift flour; measure and sift with all dry ingredients except soda.
Add soda to persimmon pulp and add alternately with dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
Fold in nuts and raisins.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: quick chocolate-coffee
directions: Mix dry ingredients thoroughly in mug.
Fill with boiling water.
Stir and drink.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix oats, cranberries, walnuts, coconut, honey and eggs.
Mix well.
Spoon mixture into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes, until knife when inserted comes out clean. Cool; serve with ice cream.

title: chocolate royale cheesecake
directions: Mix crumbs and butter; press onto bottom of 9-inch spring form pan.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.

title: supper medley
directions: Place sausage and water in cold frying pan.
Cover and brown slowly.
When sausage browns, remove from pan.
Pour off all but 2 tablespoons of fat from sausage.
Add tomatoes and onions; simmer until onions are tender.
Put sausage links into tomato mixture to reheat.
Make a ring of peas around edge of casserole dish. Arrange sausage and tomato sauce in center.
Cover peas with cooked spaghetti.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Place under broiler until cheese has melted and browned slightly.
Serves 6.

title: healthy garden quiche
directions: In saucepan, cook onion and garlic in margarine.
In bowl, toss Lite-line pieces with flour.
Add onion mixture and remaining ingredients.
Pour into lightly oiled 9-inch pie plate.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes or until set.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken scampi
directions: Cook broccoli until tender.
Set aside. Cut chicken into bite-size pieces.

title: one-dish meal
directions: Mix onion, carrots, celery, green pepper, rice and chicken together and put into casserole.
Put oil, vegex, water, broth and soup into saucepan and cook for 3 minutes.
Pour sauce over casserole and mix gently.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: homemade ice cream(vanilla ice cream)
directions: Mix all ingredients except vanilla in saucepan.
Heat until little beads appear.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Mix well and pour into ice cream (freeze).
Makes 1 gallon.

title: moroccan lamb pies
directions: Melt butter, add onion and cook gently until soft.
Stir in cumin and almonds, and continue to cook until almonds are browned a little.
Add honey and raisins.
Drain mixture on paper towels. Mix with lamb.
Add salt and pepper.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and vanilla.
In separate bowl, combine flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Cut butter into flour mixture.
Add egg mixture; stir until combined.
Divide into 3 sections.
Pat into balls and flatten; separate with Saran Wrap and refrigerate overnight.
Roll out dough with flour as needed to 1/4-inch thin.
Use cutout shapes.
Bake at 350° for about 8 minutes.
Watch closely!
Frost and decorate as desired.

title: fish and rice dish
directions: In a 2-quart baking dish, layer rice, then fish.
Mix the cream of chicken soup and milk and pour over rice and fish. Break cheese slices in smaller pieces and place over mixture.
Mix 1 cup of Pepperidge Farm dressing and 2 tablespoons of melted butter; sprinkle over dish and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pastry
directions: Sift salt and flour.
Cut shortening into flour.
Add water slowly and mix with fork until mixture forms a ball.
Makes 2 crusts.

title: beef and bean burritos
directions: Brown hamburger together with taco seasoning mix. Add water and simmer. Meanwhile, spread the refried beans (equally divided) over 10 flour tortillas (large). Now divide the hamburger mixture over beans. Run a thin line down the center of the tortilla, about 2-inches wide, for easy folding. Top each with any or all of the following: onion, green chilies, Colby cheese. Now roll each tortilla up ends (sides) in first and place in buttered casserole in 1 layer only (9 x 12). Top with sour cream, black olives, cheeses and jar salsa. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 minutes until bubbly. Serves 10.

title: stella lovejoy's chewy cake(blonde brownies)
directions: Melt sugar
and oleo; let cool until lukewarm.	Beat in eggs; gradually
add
dry
ingredients and nuts.	Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Scald milk.
Add butter.
Mix flour, sugar and salt.
Whip into milk.
Add egg yolks, coconut and flavoring.
Cook until thick.
Pour into pie shell.

title: microwave cake
directions: Mix ingredients together and spread in an 8-inch dish.
Cover with wax paper and microwave for 10 minutes on High (rotate dish after 5 minutes).
Cake should look dry and even color.
Sprinkle top with remaining chocolate chips and return to microwave.
When soft, spread on top of cake.
(If heat from microwave does not melt chips, microwave for 30 seconds on Medium.)
When cool, cut into squares.

title: delicious crumb cake
directions: Grease 13 x 18-inch pan.
Mix ingredients and pour into pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, then remove from oven.
While cake is cooking, make crumbs for top of cake.

title: pizza cups
directions: Brown and drain beef.
Stir in paste, onion, mushrooms and seasonings.
(Mixture will be thick.)
Cook over low heat 4 to 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Place biscuits in a greased muffin pan.
Press to cover bottom and sides.
Place 1/4 cup mixture in each cup and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: veal marevgo
directions: Cook noodles according to label directions; drain.
Spread cooked noodles in a shallow 8-cup baking dish.
Heat butter and oil in a large skillet.
Saute veal patties about 3 minutes on each side.
Overlap browned patties down the center of noodles; keep warm.
Toss onions and mushrooms in same skillet.
Brown lightly.
Arrange around patties.

title: heavenly fruit salad
directions: Mix together well the first 3 ingredients.
Cook over low heat until mixture starts to thicken (stir constantly to prevent scorching).
Set aside to cool.

title: meat-potato quiche
