directions: In 9-inch pie pan, stir together oil and potatoes.
Press evenly into pie crust shape.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes. Remove from oven.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender in salt water, then chop up the broccoli.
You may use chopped broccoli.
Mix your eggs, cream of chicken soup, mayonnaise and cheese and then fold in broccoli. Pour in a casserole dish.
Top with 1 cup Ritz cracker crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake in a greased casserole dish at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: swedish butter cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar, then egg yolk, cream and vanilla. Mix well.
Add flour mixed with baking powder and then add nuts. Form into balls, dip in egg white and chopped nuts.
Make small indentions in center of each ball.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. When cool, fill with butter cream frosting or any desired preserves.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni; drain well.
Add the whites from boiled eggs, celery, carrot, onion and parsley.
Put in blender yolks from eggs, mustard, sugar, milk, vinegar and Miracle Whip.
Blend until smooth.
Add to salad.

title: cranberry sauce jello
directions: Add 1 1/2 cups boiling water to Jell-O.
Mix well.
Add 1 cup cold water and chill until soft set.
Stir in cranberry sauce and about 1/2 of the Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Add walnuts if you wish. Chill.

title: coconut pie and shell
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into 2 greased pie pans.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: refrigerator sweet pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers.
Make syrup.
Let stand in refrigerator 2 weeks before serving.
This is real good.

title: easy appetizer
directions: Mix cream cheese and horseradish and shape into log.
Pour preserves over cream cheese log.
Serve with crackers.

title: spice sauce for ham
directions: Place ingredients in pan over low fire.
Stir until jelly is smooth.
Remove from fire.
Sauce will jell when cold.
Reheat and serve over ham.

title: lasagne roll-ups
directions: Prepare lasagne noodles as package directs.
Drain and lay flat.
Meanwhile, heat oil in skillet and saute garlic 2 minutes or until tender.

title: fat free cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Line 2 baking sheets with baking parchment or
aluminum foil.
In a large bowl, beat egg whites until stiff
peaks.
Beat
in
sugar,
1 tablespoon at a time, then
vanilla.
Reduce
the
speed	to
low.
Beat in powdered cocoa.
With a rubber spatula, fold in chocolate chips.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream oleo and shortening, add sugar.
Beat until mixture is smooth.
Add egg yolks, one at a time and beat well.
Put soda in buttermilk.
Add flour and buttermilk alternately.
Add flour first and last.
Add coconut, nuts and vanilla.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour in 3 greased-floured pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: charlene's potato soup
directions: Peel and cut potatoes, add salt, nutmeg, onion, and chicken broth, start to cook.
Next cut celery and garnish carrots.
When potatoes are soft reduce heat to simmer.
Add butter and cheese. When cheese is melted, add cream and simmer.
Cook 5-10 minutes longer, stir soup often.
Half way you may want to add a couple cups of water.

title: bagel chips
directions: With sharp serrated knife, slice bagel into very thin slices. Arrange on nonstick baking sheet.
Brush lightly with olive oil or spray.
Sprinkle with oregano.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: yummie chicken drummies
directions: Combine ingredients and marinate overnight.
Bake at 375° for about 30 to 40 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: vanilla wafer fruit cake
directions: Crush vanilla wafers, chop fruit and nuts (reserve 4 cherries, 16 pecan halves and 2 slices pineapple).
Mix fruit, nuts and wafer crumbs.
Beat eggs, add sugar and milk.
Add previous mixture.
Mix well.
Let stand while preparing pan with waxed paper.
Pack mixture in pan, decorate with fruit and nuts.
Bake at 325° for one hour.
Remove from pan.
Store in tight container.

title: sweet potato-banana casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water to cover for 30 minutes. Drain.
Cool, peel and slice crosswise into 1/4-inch slices.
Set aside.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine sugar, Crisco oil and eggs.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to Crisco oil mixture.
Beat at low speed for 1 minute.
Add grated carrots and nuts.
Spread batter in greased and floured pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
When cool, spread with cream cheese frosting.

title: transparent pie
directions: Melt margarine, mix sugar and flour.
Add to margarine.
Add Karo syrup, salt, vanilla and milk.
Stir in beaten eggs and vinegar.
Mix well.

title: quick and easy parmesan chicken
directions: Rinse and pound cutlets until flat.
Spread each cutlet liberally with mayonnaise using a knife or spatula.
Evenly sprinkle Parmesan over the cutlets.
Lay them in a baking pan sprayed with Pam and bake in a preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: In large bowl, thaw and crumble potato patties.
Cook and crumble bacon, reserving drippings.
Using a wire whisk, stir flour into bacon drippings until smooth.
Add sugar, vinegar, water, salt, pepper and celery seed.
Stir mixture until well blended. Continue heating over medium heat until mixture boils and thickens. Pour mixture over crumbled hash brown patties.
Stir to blend all ingredients.
Make ahead and refrigerate to allow flavors to blend. Heat and serve.
Makes 8 (1-cup) servings.

title: one-dish taco supper
directions: Line a greased 13 x 9-inch pan evenly with biscuits; press to flatten biscuits and seal together, bringing biscuits 1-inch up sides of pan.
Bake at 375° for 5 to 6 minutes or until lightly browned.
Set aside.
Brown beef in a large skillet; stir in seasoning and water.
Spread beef mixture over biscuits; sprinkle cheese over top.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Spread sour cream over cheese.
Sprinkle with lettuce, tomatoes and olives. Cut into squares and serve immediately.

title: angel food cake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Have ready a tube pan, 10 x 4-inch, but do not grease.

title: sand dough
directions: This unique dough dries to look just like a sand sculpture.

title: cherry pudding
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt and Crisco.
Add soda in water and eggs.
Add cherry juice; mix well.
Fold in cherries and nuts. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: carrot cake frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients except for nuts and beat until fluffy. Stir in nuts. Frost cake.

title: cabbage and brussels sprouts
directions: About 45 minutes before serving:
Discard any tough outer leaves from cabbage.
Reserve a few large leaves from cabbage to line platter later; coarsely slice remaining cabbage.

title: chile verde
directions: Cover meat with cold water; bring to boil.
Cover and reduce to simmer for 1 hour.
Cool meat in its own broth until you can remove.
Cook garlic and green pepper until soft; add remaining ingredients; cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Garnish as desired. Serve over rice.
Serves 4.

title: grammy tyler's sweet tomato relish
directions: Grind tomatoes, cover with water and scald 15 minutes.
Drain well, even overnight.
Grind onions and peppers.
Mix onions, peppers and tomatoes with vinegar, sugar, salt and pickling spice. Cook 1/2 hour.
Pour in jars and seal.

title: veg-all stuffed meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients and set aside.

title: easter bunny bread
directions: Thaw frozen bread dough at room temperature for 3 hours or overnight in the refrigerator.
Lightly grease a large large cookie sheet.
Cut the dough into 2 equal pieces.
Shape one piece into a large, flat circle for the bunny's body.
Cut the other half into 3 sections.
Shape one section into a round ball for a head. Cut one section in half and shape into bunny ears.
Cut the last piece of dough into 4 equal pieces.
Make feet and front paws and attach them to the bunny's body.

title: cheese cake
directions: Press together to form to pan.

title: meatball soup
directions: In large pot, heat broth to simmer.

title: beef taco-mac
directions: Cut beef steaks lengthwise into 1-inch wide strips and then crosswise into 1-inch pieces. In Dutch oven, heat oil over medium-high heat until hot. Add beef and onion. Cook and stir 3 minutes. Season with salt. Stir seasoning mix, tomatoes, pasta and water into beef. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low. Cover tightly and simmer 20 minutes or until pasta is tender. Sprinkle cheese before serving.

title: vanilla cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add egg and beat well.
Add half of dry mixture, milk and vanilla.
Beat well, then add the rest of the dry ingredients.
Bake at 350° on ungreased tray for 8 to 10 minutes (add one raisin on top of each cookie, if desired, before baking).

title: chocolate crinkles
directions: Mix oil, chocolate and sugar.
Blend in one egg at a time until well mixed.
Add vanilla and dry ingredients.
Chill several hours.
Drop teaspoons of dough into confectioners sugar.
Roll and shape into balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake at 350°.

title: chicken almond appetizers
directions: Melt butter in a skillet.
Add flour and milk, stirring until smooth and thickened.
Stir in wine, salt, chicken, capers and almonds.
Spread on toast; top with cheese and broil until cheese melts.
Makes 16 canapes.

title: fruit ball
directions: Mix and chill in 2 balls or 1 roll overnight in refrigerator. The next day, roll in nuts.
This is so good!

title: cream cheese corn
directions: Drain corn.
Add cream cheese.
Heat in microwave until cheese is melted and corn is hot.
Add any amount of peppers desired to suit your own taste.
Corn and cheese mixture can be adjusted to your taste.

title: cottage cheese dip
directions: Cream cottage cheese until smooth, adding a little sour cream or yogurt if necessary.
Add remaining ingredients and blend well. Chill for several hours before serving.
May be used as a salad, sandwich spread or vegetable dip.

title: mustard butter pasta with broccoli
directions: Set out butter to soften, when soft blend in mustard.
Slice garlic and pound in a mortar with a health pinch of salt.
When pulpy, add parsley and chives and continue pounding a short while. Blend this mixture into butter with a little black pepper.
In a large pot, boil a generous amount of water with a teaspoon salt and tablespoon oil.
Fan the pasta into boiling water.
If using fresh pasta, add broccoli at the same time, if using dried pasta, add broccoli for last couple of minutes of cooking.
When done, scoop out pasta and broccoli and drain.
Put the pasta and broccoli into a large skillet, allowing some water to dribble in.
Add the prepared butter and over moderate heat, toss the pasta until it is evenly coated.
Keep heat low enough that butter does not bubble or fry.
Check seasonings and add salt and pepper if necessary.

title: almond joy cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to package.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan. In
medium
saucepan
combine
1 cup Pet milk and sugar, bring just to a boil and add marshmallows.
Stir until melted, then add coconut.
Pour over hot cake.
Melt together 1/2 cup Pet
milk, butter and milk chocolate chips.
When heated, add almonds.
Pour on
top
of
warm
cake.
Better
made the day before.

title: barbecued chicken
directions: Brown flour-coated chicken in fat in a skillet.
Place browned chicken in a casserole or baking dish.
Brown the onion lightly in the fat in the skillet.
Add rest of ingredients to the onion in the skillet and simmer 30 minutes.
Pour sauce over browned chicken in casserole.
Cover with foil and bake at 320° to 350° for 1 hour.

title: crab and noodles au gratin
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Pick over crab to remove any shell pieces. Melt 4 tablespoons of butter in a saucepan and add the flour, stirring with a wire whisk.
When blended, add the milk, stirring rapidly with the whisk.
Add salt and pepper to taste, nutmeg and cream.
Bring to a boil and simmer, stirring occasionally, for about 5 minutes.
Remove the sauce from the heat and add the egg yolk, stirring rapidly with the whisk.
Add the sherry.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Place beans in small casserole.
Add salt and pepper.
Pour mushroom soup over beans and mix lightly.
Cook at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cover with French fried onions.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add eggs one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Add buttermilk, soda and 2 cups of flour.
Cut candied fruits into small pieces and dredge pieces in 1 cup flour.
Mix in fruits and nuts; add grape juice.
Drop on cookie sheet with spoon.
Bake at 300 for 20 minutes.
Makes 4-5 dozen.

title: grandma feldmann's jumbles
directions: Mix sugar, shortening, eggs and vanilla.
Add baking powder, flour and salt.
Mix and knead just until blended well and dough holds together.
If dough crumbles, add 1 to 2 tablespoons of milk.
Roll to desired thickness and cut with cookie cutters. Decorate with colored sugar, if desired, before baking.
Bake in a 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until they begin to fluff.
Add sugar slowly. Beat until like divinity.
Add vanilla.
Fold in chips and pecans. Put on foiled lined cookie sheet by the spoonful.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Turn oven off.
Put cookies in oven on either or both racks. Leave in oven overnight.
Do not peek.

title: tuna fish salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Good on lettuce or on croissants.

title: inside-out ravioli casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and garlic in 1 tablespoon oil. Cook spinach according to package directions; drain, reserving liquid.
Add water to liquid to make 1 cup.
Stir spinach liquid, spaghetti sauce, tomato sauce, tomato paste, salt and pepper into meat mixture.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Combine spinach with macaroni, cheese, bread crumbs, eggs and oil.
Spread in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Top with meat sauce.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: cheesecake cupcakes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients except wafers.
Mix until smooth.
In bottom of each of 16 paper-lined muffin cups, place a vanilla wafer.
Spoon cream cheese mixture over vanilla wafers, filling each cup full.
Bake 20 minutes.
Let cool in tins for 10 minutes.
Remove from tins and refrigerate 1 to 2 hours or overnight.

title: easy chop suey
directions: Brown all meats in olive oil or other light oil.
Add all other ingredients and simmer for 30 minutes or until meat is tender.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: apricot crunch cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread pie filling in 9-inch square pan.
Beat cake mix, egg, extract and 1/3 cup water for 4 minutes. Pour over filling.
Sprinkle with coconut and pecans.
Drizzle with butter.
Bake for 40 minutes.
Serve warm.
Top with whipped cream.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Crush 1 1/2 cups berries.
Cook with water to boil 2 minutes. Put through sieve.
Blend sugar and cornstarch and blend into berry juice.
Cook over medium heat until thick.
Add color. Cover bottom of pie crust with thick juice.
Place berries, stem down, over juice.
Cover with remaining mixture.
Refrigerate.

title: kids' favorite casserole
directions: Prepare mashed potatoes as usual.
Stir in hot dogs.
Place in a casserole dish and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: cowboy supper
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Add pork and beans, margarine, sugar, mustard, ketchup, salt and pepper to hamburger.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Pour over toasted bread.
Top with shredded Cheddar cheese, diced tomatoes and shredded lettuce.
Optional:
Top with sour cream and taco sauce.

title: florentine salad mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling hot water.
Cool.
Just before gelatin sets, mix in everything listed. Pour into 2-inch deep pan or a mold and chill until set.
This is a tasty salad.

title: mexican chicken salad
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Mix all ingredients (except chicken and chips) together.
Melt cheese in microwave until smooth. Layer chicken and chips, then pour cheese mix over the chips and chicken.

title: vegetable paella
directions: About 1 1/2 hours before serving, cut zucchini into 1 1/2-inch chunks; cut tomatoes into 3/4-inch pieces.
Slice eggplant lengthwise in half, then cut each half crosswise into 1/2-inch thick slices.
Dice onion; cut each mushroom in half or quarters.

title: dessert salad
directions: Dissolve jello and sugar in boiling water.
Cool until slightly thickened.
Beat the cream cheese.
Add jello and Cool Whip; beat until thoroughly mixed.
Fold in nuts, cherries and pineapple.
Refrigerate until set, 4 hours or overnight.

title: green beans with potatoes
directions: Wash beans, trim ends and remove strings.
Cut beans into 1 1/2-inch pieces.
Combine beans and remaining ingredients in a Dutch oven.
Bring to a boil, cover, reduce heat and simmer 25 minutes or until beans are crisp-tender and potatoes are done.

title: egg rolls
directions: Use 1/4 cup filling.
Place diagonally across center; lift lower triangle and tuck under.
Bring end flaps up.
Roll the filled portion over.
Press down firmly with water.
Fill wok with 3-inches oil.
Heat to 375°.
Fry 4 or 5 at a time for 3 to 4 minutes.

title: harvard beets
directions: Drain beets, reserving 1/3 cup juice.
Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Stir dry ingredients in reserved beet juice, vinegar and butter (melted).
Cook and stir until mixture thickens.
Stir in beets and heat through.
Serves 5.

title: cheesy chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender.
Arrange spears in large 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Place chicken on top.
Combine soup and milk and pour over chicken and broccoli.
Mix Bisquick or Jiffy mix and milk.
Spread this mixture over the chicken, broccoli and cheese. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: baked sole
directions: Heat oven to 375° (moderately hot).
Thaw fish fillets enough to separate.
Arrange in a greased shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt.
Arrange mushrooms, carrot, onion and parsley on fish. Pour in cream.
Dot top with butter and sprinkle with cheese. Bake 20 to 30 minutes until fish is fork-tender
Serves 2.

title: oriental salad
directions: Combine ingredients.
Add chow mein noodles and shrimp last.

title: superb corn bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients, add shortening and boiling water. Mix thoroughly and let cool while whipping the eggs.
Whip the yolks; then whip the whites until stiff.
Fold yolks into whites, then into dry ingredients.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° to 375° until brown.

title: spice tea
directions: Mix together well.
Store in tin container or glass jar.
Use 2 teaspoons per cup of hot water.

title: french fried onion rings
directions: Peel onion and cut into 1/4-inch slices.
Separate into rings. Heat
oil
inch
deep) to 375° in a large skillet. Beat remaining
ingredients
with rotary beater until smooth. Dip each onion
ring
into batter, letting excess batter drip back into bowl.
Fry
a
few
onion rings at a time in hot oil about 2 minutes or until golden brown.
Drain.

title: green bean salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and let stand all night; drain.

title: crab cioppino
directions: Combine all ingredients, except crab, in a large pot.
Simmer 1/2 hour to 45 minutes.
Add crab halfway through simmering. Serves 4 to 6.
If using live crabs, boil 10 minutes, then add to sauce.

title: tea cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients in mixing bowl and beat until batter is smooth. Drop cookies on cookie sheet (teaspoonful) and bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chicken breast casserole
directions: Mix soups together (do not add water) in small bowl, then mix in milk.
Put 1 1/2 cups of soup mixture in casserole dish.
Add chicken, then add rest of soup from other bowl on top.
Cover and cook at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Sprinkle top with Parmesan cheese.
Cook for 15 more minutes, uncovered.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Set shrimp aside in ice water for 1/2 hour, then drain. Devein and crush.
Mix with cream cheese and form into a ball. Refrigerate for at least 3 hours before serving.
When ready to serve, put cocktail sauce on top.
Use Wheat Thins for dipping or spreading dip on.

title: lemon squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend butter, confectioners sugar and 1 cup flour.
Pat mixture gently into an 8-inch square pan.
Bake 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cherry dump cake
directions: Pour cherry pie filling into, and spread evenly on bottom of 8 x 11 1/2 inch baking dish.
Next pour pineapple (undrained) over cherry filling, spread well.
Pour yellow cake mix over mixture evenly,
then pour melted margarine over mixture.
Cover with pecans.
Bake in 305° oven for 1 hour,
or until firm on top.

title: life-line cookie dough
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs very well.
Mix eggs into batter, one at a time.
Add vanilla and dry ingredients.
Mix very well.

title: corn casserole
directions: Saute pepper and onions in oleo.
Add eggs to corn, then green pepper (diced) and onions.
Add muffin mix.
Mix well.
Spread in 9 x 12-inch casserole pan.
Then spread sour cream over top of this.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese over top.
Garnish with paprika.
Bake 40 minutes at 325°.
Remove and cover for a few minutes before serving.

title: soft peanut brittle
directions: Combine corn syrup and sugar.
Bring to a full boil.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter.
Mix well.
Pour this mixture over corn flakes.
Mix well.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: merry cranberry bread
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Pour into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes, or until edges pull away from edges of pan.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Remove from pan. Makes 1 loaf.

title: fig ice cream
directions: Combine figs, 1 cup milk, 1 cup sugar, lemon juice and creme de cacao in container of an electric blender.
Process until mixture is pureed.
Combine eggs, fig puree, remaining 3/4 cup sugar, 3 cups milk and whipping cream in a large bowl; mix well. Pour into freezer can of a 4-quart, hand-turned or electric freezer.
Freeze according to manufacturer's instructions.
Let ice cream ripen about 1 hour.
Yields 3 quarts.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake cake as directed. Make holes in cake with a fork. Mix milk, sugar and 1/2 cup coconut together in saucepan. Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer 1 minute. Pour over cake and let cool. Mix 1/2 cup coconut with Cool Whip and spread over cake. Sprinkle with remaining coconut. Chill overnight.

title: supper pot potluck
directions: In a large skillet, brown meat.
Place potatoes, celery, carrots and onion in crock-pot. Sprinkle peas over top. Spoon browned meat over vegetables.

title: willy cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in greased and floured tube pan or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix together well and refrigerate overnight.

title: angel buns
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in warm water in medium bowl.
Mix in Bisquick and milk until dough forms.
Gently smooth into a ball on surface dusted with Bisquick.
Knead 10 times.
Roll dough 1/2 inch.
Cut with 2 inch cutter, dipped in dry mix.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Let rise in warm place 30 minutes or until soft and puffed.
Heat oven to 425°.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 9 to 11 buns.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple.
Save 3 tablespoons of juice.
Combine flour and sugar; stir this into juice.
Add cheese and pineapple.
Put in 1-quart casserole. Top with cracker crumbs and melted butter. Bake for 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: sardine salad
directions: Mix sardines and onions well in a small dish.
Add in mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Continue to mix.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Combine first 10 ingredients in a small saucepan.
Bring to a boil and cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Place chicken in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake an additional 30 minutes, basting occasionally.

title: cinnamon nut rolls
directions: Butter Bundt pan. Sprinkle nuts evenly in pan. Place rolls around pan. Sprinkle 1/2 box pudding over rolls. Melt butter and combine with sugar and cinnamon. Spoon over rolls. Let sit out all night. Bake the next morning 20 minutes at 350° on low rack.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Slice apples.
Cut each biscuit in half horizontally, making 20 biscuits.
Melt margarine in baking dish.
Wrap apple slices in biscuits and put in the margarine.
Heat sugar, cinnamon and water until dissolved.
Pour over biscuits and bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: fudge sauce for ice cream(microwave)
directions: Place baking chocolate in a 4-cup glass measuring cup. Microwave at 100% power for 1 minute.
Add water, butter, corn syrup and sugar.
Cover and microwave at 100% for 2 minutes. Uncover and whisk ingredients together.
Cover and microwave another 2 minutes at 100% power.
Add semi-sweet chocolate pieces and whisk well.
Add cream and whisk again.

title: crusty corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Place butter in a 9 x 5-inch pan and place in oven to melt.
Mix together dry ingredients in large bowl.
Add milk, honey and egg and beat well.
Pour into hot pan of butter.
Bake 25 to 35 minutes.

title: green rice(broccoli casserole)
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Cook rice.
Fry onion and celery in butter.
In large bowl, mix soup, cheese, onion/celery combination, rice and broccoli.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Precook celery and carrots in microwave.
Add all ingredients into slow cooker.
Mix well.
Cover and cook on low 4 - 6 hours.

title: cucumbers dill
directions: Mix mayonnaise, dill, mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Chill well.
Wash and rinse cucumbers. Cut into 1/8-inch thick slices and chill in ice water for about 1 hour.
Drain.
Serve with dill sauce.
Yields about 2 cups sauce.

title: hot chocolate
directions: Heat chocolate and water over low heat, stirring until chocolate melts.
Add sugar and salt.
Cook 4 minutes, stirring constantly.
Stir in milk gradually; heat slowly just to boiling. Beat with rotary beater.
Serve.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly in a small bowl with mixer at medium speed. Beat in corn syrup, sugar, vanilla, margarine and salt.
Cover pastry with pecans.
Pour filling into pastry shell.
Bake in a 350° oven for 55 to 65 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean. Cool.

title: onion flavored pretzels
directions: Melt butter; stir in soup mix.
Pour over pretzels and mix well.
Put onto cookie sheet and bake at 200° for 2 hours stirring every 15 minutes.
When time is over, take out of oven and cool. Store in plastic bag, sprinkling with all leftover spices from pan.

title: rolls
directions: In a
mixing bowl, put warm water and dissolve yeast in it. Add
sugar, shortening and salt.
Then mix in the flour a little at	a
time.
Put
in
a greased bowl and set in a warm place and let
double
in size.
Work down again and make out into rolls
or put in loaves.
Bake in oven that is turned on as you
put
your bread in.
Turn over to 400° and bake for 15 minutes.
Do not preheat oven.

title: jam cake with caramel icing
directions: Mix liquid ingredients well with wooden spoon.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to other mixture.
Bake in tube pan at 325° for one hour.
Cool.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and green pepper.
Add salt and tomato sauce and chili powder.
Mix sour cream and half of Cheddar cheese with beaten egg, then add ground beef mixture.
Put biscuits on top of hamburger mixture in casserole dish and sprinkle with rest of Cheddar cheese.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 375°.

title: dutch pot pie
directions: Put in baking dish, layer by layer.
Top layer potatoes. Sprinkle with parsley, salt and pepper.
Dot with butter.
Add 2 cups of water.
Bake 3 hours at 350°.

title: tomato aspic
directions: Heat 1/2 cup tomato sauce.
Dissolve jello.
Add rest of liquid, celery, etc.
Pour into small molds.

title: pinwheel snacks
directions: Mix all the ingredients and spread evenly on tortillas.
Roll tightly (each tortilla) and wrap in plastic and freeze until needed.
Leave out about 30 minutes, then slice while still frozen.

title: herbed turkey casserole
directions: Place turkey and onions in a nonstick, microwave-safe casserole dish. Cover and microwave on High for 5 minutes, stirring once. Drain. Stir in remaining ingredients and cover with vented plastic wrap. Microwave on High for 8 minutes or until rice is tender. Let stand for 5 minutes before serving. Garnish with fresh oregano sprig if desired. Makes 4 servings.

title: mini cheese pizzas
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
Open the can of biscuits.
Gently spread (stretch) without tearing them apart on a cookie sheet. Spread the sauce on each biscuit and spread the cheese over the sauce.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Set for 5 minutes and then serve.

title: spiced hot tea
directions: In a saucepan, boil water, cloves and cinnamon.
Remove from heat and add tea bags.
Let stand 4 minutes.
Add sugar and juices. Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Serve hot.
Can be reheated.

title: creme de menthe cake
directions: Mix all ingredients for 2 minutes with an electric mixer. Fold in 6 ounces of chocolate bits.
Grease and flour a tube Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 55-60 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Add milk and mix.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with dry cake mix.
Press down lightly.
Sprinkle on nuts.
Drizzle melted oleo on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as per instructions.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool 15 minutes and poke holes in cake with a straw.

title: barbecued string beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together except beans. Simmer for 30 minutes. Let stand for one hour. Add sauce to beans, heat and serve.

title: creamy barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Serve warm or cold with smoked or grilled meats or as a dipping sauce for fried vegetables.

title: banana milk shake
directions: Mash
banana to pulp.
Combine with milk and flavoring. Mix well.
Makes 1 serving.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute the onions and add soup, egg, cheese and salad dressing. Mix in broccoli and place mixture in a casserole dish. Top with crushed crackers.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine first five ingredients; make a well in the center. Combine remaining ingredients and pour into center of dry ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 350° for one hour in two greased loaf pans.	Cool in pans for 10 minutes, then remove.

title: plum cake
directions: Mix sugar, margarine, salt and eggs together until creamy.
Add milk and flour alternately with baking powder and soda mixed in the flour.
Add vanilla last and beat about 200 strokes.
Grease and flour 9-inch pans.
Put just 4 tablespoons of batter into 9-inch pans.
This makes a thin layer of batter over the bottom.
Put fruit on top until about 1/2-inch from top of pan.
Pour 2 tablespoons of melted butter over top of fruit; sprinkle 2 or 3 tablespoons sugar over all.
Top with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes and dust with powdered sugar.
Makes 3 to 4 cakes.

title: mock apple pie
directions: Bring to boil sugar, water and butter.
Add cream of tartar, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Pour over crackers.
Will fill 8-inch pie pan.
Dot with butter and bake to golden brown.

title: mema's oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix dry ingredients together in mixing bowl.
Mix softened butter and room temperature egg together.
Add to dry ingredients. (Option:
Use your favorite chocolate chips, M&M's or dried fruit instead of pecans or raisins.)
Drop by teaspoon on Pam sprayed cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: fruit sauce(low-fat topping for pancakes and waffles)
directions: Mix all ingredients in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until sauce thickens.
Cool and serve over pancakes, waffles or French toast.
Has 0 g fat.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients; make in balls and put in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Mix next 2 ingredients well in double boiler until melted.
Roll balls in chocolate; put on wax paper to cool.

title: orange nut squares
directions: Dredge orange slice candy pieces in flour and salt.
Add remaining ingredients.
Grease and line 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with waxed paper.
Pour mixture in pan.
Bake at 350° until done.
Cut into squares.

title: german cheese schnitzel
directions: Pound meat to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut into 6 to 8 pieces to form cutlets.
Sprinkle meat on both sides with salt, pepper and lemon juice; let stand 30 minutes.
Blend eggs, water and oil; set aside.
Combine bread crumbs and cheese.
Coat cutlets in flour, then dip in egg mixture.
Let drip off.
Coat with cheese mixture. Let stand 15 minutes.
Melt butter in skillet.
Brown on each side.
Serve with noodles or potatoes.
Sprinkle meat with additional Parmesan cheese and paprika.
Garnish with lemon slices.

title: chili and rice
directions: Cook rice.

Brown hamburger. Grease a 3-quart casserole dish. Line bottom of dish with rice. Cover with green chilies, then put half of cheese, then hamburger, then sliced tomatoes. Combine sour cream, green pepper and seasonings.
Pour over casserole and put rest of cheese on.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: apricot salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
When cold, add remaining ingredients.

title: horseradish mustard cream
directions: In saucepan combine onion, thyme, pepper, wine and clam juice. Bring to a boil; reduce heat to medium-high and cook until reduced to 1 cup.
Add cream and cook until reduced to 1 1/2 cups.
Strain through a sieve.
Add mustard and horseradish.
Makes 1 1/4 cups. This goes great with pan-fried fish or crab legs.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Mix first three ingredients.
Spoon over chicken and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: spicy stuffed peppers(microwave)
directions: Arrange peppers in 8-cup micro-proof ring mold or 10-inch micro-proof pie plate.
Combine remaining ingredients except tomato sauce and cheese.
Blend thoroughly.
Divide meat mixture among peppers.
Pour tomato sauce over peppers.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Cook on High for 20 to 22 minutes or until peppers are tender and beef is no longer red.
Remove plastic wrap; top each pepper with cheese slice.
Return plastic wrap.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: honey lemon marinade
directions: Combine all ingredients.
This marinade can be used for meat, chicken or seafood.

title: sugar basted baked ham with a pecan gravy glace
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Score the fatty area of the ham in diamond shapes.
Place ham in a baking pan. Blend all the basting ingredients and pat all over the ham.
Bake ham 60 to 90 minutes, adding water to the pan to prevent scorching of the sugar.
Baste the ham every 20 minutes and finish with a basting of the thick honey sugar glaze.
Remove the ham to a platter to cool for 15 minutes before slicing.
Add a little water to the baking pan, heating over a medium heat, stirring up the drippings, making a sauce.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and cook until thickened.

title: easy lasagne
directions: Brown off hamburger; drain grease.
Add spaghetti sauce.
Boil lasagne noodles until flexible.
Mix cottage cheese, eggs, oregano and 1/3 of Mozzarella cheese.
Start layers:
meat sauce, noodles, meat sauce, cottage cheese, Mozzarella, noodles, meat sauce, Mozzarella.
Sprinkle top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes before serving.

title: greek spinach pie(spanakoppittes)
directions: In a mixer bowl, combine the egg, onion and Feta cheese.
Beat to combine.
Add the cheese and combine well.
Add the spinach and seasonings and mix just until blended.
Chill 1 hour.

title: braised swiss steak
directions: Combine bread crumbs, salt and pepper.
Trim fat from steak; wipe meat with damp cloth.
Sprinkle one side with half of crumb mixture; pound into steak.
Repeat other side.
Brush both sides with butter; place under broiler, turning once, until brown on both sides.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: In large bowl, blend sugar and cream cheese well.
Add thawed strawberries, drained pineapple and sliced bananas.
Lastly, add Cool Whip, blending it all well together.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan and freeze.
Cut in squares and serve.

title: cornbread casserole
directions: Mix all together and put in greased casserole (2-quart). Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: wassail bowl
directions: Keep your heart free from hate.

title: yummy chicken wings
directions: Mix ingredients until light boil.
Pour over chicken. Cook 1 hour at 350°.
Easy!

title: mango layer cake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease a baking pan, 8 x 12 x 2-inches. Beat egg slightly and mix with milk.
Now stir in 3 tablespoons sugar and biscuit mix smoothly.
Spread over bottom of baking pan. Arrange a layer of drained mango slices over dough and spoon a mixture of remaining sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg, flour and melted butter over the mango slices.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes, until nicely browned.

title: ham or chicken loaf
directions: Mix everything, except gelatine and mayonnaise.
Soak gelatine in 1/2 cup of cold water for 3 minutes.
Dissolve over hot water. Add to mixture, then add mayonnaise.
Pack in greased loaf pan. Refrigerate.

title: scallops and tartar
directions: Cut scallops to 1-inch size and bread with gravy mix.
Fry in oil over hot flame until medium brown.
Mix rest of ingredients for scallop dip.

title: baked squash casserole
directions: Slice and boil squash until tender; drain well.
While hot, stir in butter or margarine, onion, soup, sugar, pimentos and egg. Place in a large casserole dish and top with corn flake crumbs. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: zesty baked chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix crumbs with cheese, parsley, pepper and salt.
Combine margarine and garlic and dip chicken pieces in the margarine.
Then roll each piece thoroughly in the bread crumb mixture.
Place chicken pieces in a single layer in a shallow baking pan.
Sprinkle with remaining bread crumb mixture.
Bake until tender 50 minutes.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: cheese danish
directions: Roll out 1 can croissants into buttered 9 x 13-inch dish.
Mix next four ingredients plus 1 egg yolk.
Place on 1st layer.
Roll out 2nd can of croissants and place on top of mixture.
Brush egg white on top layer.

title: orange-romaine salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a jar.
Cover tightly and shake vigorously until well blended; set aside.
Combine next 5 ingredients in a large bowl.
Pour dressing over lettuce mixture immediately before serving; toss gently.
Sprinkle with crumbled bacon.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: homemade spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown and drain meat and onions. Add tomato sauce and diced vegetables. Add spices. Stir gently and simmer for at least 20 minutes. Sauce will thicken. Add water, if needed. Serve with any type of spaghetti or firm pasta and garlic cheese bread.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Combine all ingredients and heat until almost boiling.

title: instant spiced tea
directions: Mix well.
Use 3 level teaspoons per cup of boiling water.

title: make ahead lettuce salad
directions: In a 6-quart bowl, layer half of the lettuce, onion, celery, green pepper, water chestnuts and peas.

title: pork soup
directions: Take the broth from ribs you parboil for barbecuing or take 21 pounds of neck bones and boil saving broth.
Remove ribs or neck bones.
Add the other ingredients and cook until tender.
Barley may be added instead of noodles.
Pork flavored Ramen noodles may be added for added flavor.

title: caramel corn
directions: Boil 2 minutes.
Take from heat.
Add a pinch of soda and cream of tartar. Stir.
Pour over popped corn.
Stir well until well coated.
Put on cookie sheets.
Put in a 250° oven for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: marmalade sauce
directions: On low, melt marmalade with sherry. Remove and fold in nuts. Serve over pudding.

title: prune cake
directions: Cook butter, milk and sugar until thick; add raisins and nuts. Spread on Prune Cake.

title: souper chicken
directions: Mix the can of soup, water and rice together in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Add washed chicken.
Sprinkle onion soup (dry) on top. Cover tightly and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: listy or "nothings"
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well, then knead for a few minutes.
Place on bread board and cover with bowl (warm if possible).
Let stand a few minutes; knead a little and then cut into 4 or 5 pieces.
Let stand again for about 30 minutes or less. Roll quite thin and cut up into 3-inch squares or 2 x 3-inch rectangles.
Cut an inch or so slit in each.
Fry in hot fat until light brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, cinnamon and nutmeg. Cream shortening and sugar.
Thoroughly mix in egg.
Stir in sifted dry ingredients alternately with pumpkin mixture.
Stir only until smooth after each addition.
Do not beat.

title: chocolate mint snow top cookies
directions: In bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt; set aside. Over hot (not boiling) water, melt 1 cup mint morsels, stirring until smooth.*
In bowl, beat butter and sugar until creamy.
Add melted mint morsels and vanilla.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually beat in flour mixture.
Stir in remaining 1/2 cup mint morsels.
Wrap dough in plastic wrap; freeze until firm.
Preheat oven to 350°. Shape dough into 1-inch balls; coat with confectioners sugar. Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes, until tops appear cracked.
Let stand 5 minutes on cookie sheet.
Cool completely.

title: icebox fruitcake
directions: Crush wafers and mix thoroughly with coconut, pecans and raisins.
Add milk and mix with hands.
Place wax paper in a loaflike container and put dough in, pressing together firmly. Place in refrigerator with a heavy weight on top overnight.
Then slice as needed, keeping in refrigerator while not in use.

title: "putting on the ritz" congealed salad
directions: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees.
Combine the cracker crumbs, margarine and 3 tablespoons sugar.
Press on the bottom of a 9x13x2-inch baking pan or dish.
Bake for about 10 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: easy sugar cookies
directions: Mix in large mixing bowl the sugar, shortening and eggs. Beat until creamy. Add vanilla, lemon juice, baking powder and salt. Whip again, then gradually add flour. Mix well. Drop on lightly greased cookie sheet. Press with bottom of glass and sprinkle with sugar. Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: mexican wedding cakes
directions: Cream together the butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Add flour, pecans and vanilla.
Roll dough in 1-inch balls.
Place on greased baking sheet and flatten slightly.
Bake in 300° oven for 34 minutes.
Roll in additional sugar while warm.
When cool, roll again in sugar.
Yields 25 to 40 cookies.

title: easy sausage quiche
directions: Trim bread crust to fit bread in bottom of greased 9x13 inch pan.
Brown sausage in pan and drain.
Stir in mustard.
Spoon mixture over bread and sprinkle on the shredded cheese.
Combine rest of ingredients and pour over the bread and sausage.
This can be made ahead and refrigerated.
Bake at 350 degrees for 25 to 30 minutes or until puffed and stiff.
Makes 8 servings.

title: never fails me pie crust
directions: Mix together salt & flour.
Cut in 1/3 c. lard.
Cut in remaining 1/3 c. lard.
Adding water 1 Tbsp. at a time, mix lightly with fork until all flour is moistened.
Gather dough up into ball.	Roll out one half at a time for each crust.

title: supper bread
directions: Cook onions in bacon grease until tender.
Combine egg and milk; add to buttermilk baking mix.
Stir until just moistened. Add onion and 1/2 of cheese.

title: easy key lime pie
directions: Beat sweetened condensed milk and Cool Whip together well.
Add lime juice; continue to beat until smooth.
Pour into pie shell; cool for an hour or two and eat.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil chicken breasts until done and flaky.
Add cream of celery soup, salt and pepper to taste and bouillon cubes.
Bring to a boil.
Flake chicken; stir celery soup around mixture and pinch off pieces of biscuits to drop in mixture.
Make sure mixture is boiling when adding biscuit pieces.
Stir occasionally. Cook until dumplings settle in mixture by simmering.
Usually takes 10 to 15 minutes simmering time.

title: frozen peanut butter pie
directions: Whip cheese until light and fluffy.
Beat in sugar and peanut butter.
Slowly add milk, blending thoroughly into mixture.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into pie shell and freeze.

title: tutti-frutti ice cream
directions: *Or use 6 cups half and half.

title: old-fashioned fruit cobbler
directions: Mix flour and sugar well.
Add fruit and juice of small lemon. Put
all ingredients into deep dish and add top crust. Bake
for
30 minutes;
turn down to 350° and finish baking approximately 30 minutes longer.
Crust should get nice and brown and juice bubble through top crust holes.
(Make few cuts with knife in top crust before putting on pie.)

title: june's broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter. Add soup, cheese, and milk. Put in baking dish. Add rice and broccoli. Stir thoroughly but carefully. Add layer of cracker crumbs over top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: zucchini muffins
directions: Mix together zucchini and oil.
Add sugar, eggs and flour (gradually).
Add rest of ingredients until well blended.
Turn into greased or paper lined muffin cups.
Makes 24 muffins and 2 small loaves or 36 muffins.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes for muffins or about 45 minutes for loaves; check on loaves before 45 minutes.

title: easy coconut cake
directions: Mix cake as directed in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Take cake out of oven and while still hot, make holes through it with wooden spoon handle.
Pour entire can of cream of coconut over warm cake. After cake has cooled, spread with Cool Whip.
Finish by sprinkling with coconut.
Better after sitting in fridge for day or two.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Place in casserole dish. Pour melted oleo over top.
May cover with crushed cornflakes mixed with oleo.
Bake 1 hour at 375°.

title: lemon cheese chiffon
directions: Combine jello, sugar and boiling water in blender.
Cover and blend at low speed until jello is dissolved, about 1 minute.
Add ice and stir until partially melted.
Add cheese, cover and blend at high speed until smooth, about 1 minute.
Pour into individual glasses or serving bowl.
Chill until set, about 30 minutes.
Top with canned pie filling or fresh or drained canned fruit, if desired.

title: four layer dessert
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Blend next 3 ingredients well and spread on top of first layer.
Mix pudding and milk and pour over second layer.
Spread the rest of 9-ounce carton of Cool Whip on top.
Garnish as desired.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Melt peanut butter and butter over low heat.
Add brown sugar. Mix until gooey but do not boil.
Take off heat and add powdered sugar.
Press in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with melted chocolate chips.

title: green bean salad
directions: Mix beans, onions, parsley and celery seed.
Pour dressing over them.
Sweeten to taste.

title: crock-pot tuna noodle
directions: In a large bowl, thoroughly combine soup, milk, parsley, vegetables and tuna.
Fold in noodles.
Pour into greased crock-pot.
Top with almonds.
Cover; cook on low 7 to 9 hours (high for 3 to 4 hours).

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Cook 45 minutes at 350°.
Easy! Easy!

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix all together; top with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry slush
directions: Put in blender or just add 1 quart clear vodka (optional).
Add water to fill an ice cream pail.
Put in freezer and stir once in a while.
Freeze overnight.

title: easy broccoli salad
directions: Combine all and chill well.

title: good chocolate pie
directions: Mix flour, cocoa, Nestle Quik and salt; mix well.
Add scalded milk, stirring until thickened.
Add beaten egg yolks. Cook until thickened.
Add butter and vanilla, then pour into cooked pie shell.

title: cajun chicken
directions: In a large resealable bag combine first 6 ingredients and shake. Add chicken a few pieces at a time and shake to coat. In a large skillet cook chicken until juices run clear--8 to 10 minutes. Yield: 4-6 servings.

title: blue cheese salad dressing
directions: Blend Blue cheese and buttermilk.
Next, add all remaining ingredients and mix.
Store in sealed container in refrigerator.

title: chicken surprise
directions: Grease bottom of pan.
Mix 2 cans of cream of mushroom soup with 1/2 cup mayonnaise.
Coat bottom of pan with soup mixture (about 1/4 cup soup).

title: fried fruit pies
directions: Add just enough water to the fruit to cover and cook until thick.
Add sugar to taste.
Roll out each biscuit into a round circle.
Put about 1 tablespoon of fruit on one side of crust. Moisten edge of crust and fold top crust over fruit.
Press down to seal edges well.
Fry in Crisco shortening or oil on both sides until golden brown.

title: freezer coleslaw
directions: Mix cabbage and salt; let stand 1 hour.
Heat sugar, vinegar, water and celery seed to boiling in 1-quart saucepan.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Cool to lukewarm.
Drain cabbage; stir in celery, green pepper, carrot and onion.
Stir vinegar mixture into cabbage mixture.
Spoon into 3 (1-pint) freezer containers.
Cover and label; freeze up to 1 month.

title: flaky biscuit casserole
directions: Brown meat in skillet.
Add mushrooms (sliced) and 3/4 can onion rings.
Cook several minutes.
Place in greased casserole. Heat mushroom soup (undiluted); stir in 1/2 cup sour cream and pour over meat.
Cut each biscuit in half and arrange cut side down around edge of casserole.
Place remaining onion rings in center.
Beat egg.
Add 1/2 cup sour cream, celery seed and salt. Spoon over biscuits.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: israeli doughnuts(hanukkah)
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder.
Cut in margarine and add sugar.
Mix to a light dough with beaten egg and milk.
Turn onto a floured board.
Roll out 1/4-inch thick.
Cut into small rounds. Put 1/2 tablespoon of jam on half the circles, brush other half with milk and pinch together.
Fry in oil for 6 to 8 minutes (deep-fry).
Toss in sugar and cinnamon mixture.

title: texas salad
directions: Mix altogether, except for dressing and Fritos.
Put these on before serving.

title: cranberry waldorf salad
directions: Grind cranberries and combine with marshmallows and sugar. Cover and chill overnight.
Add rest of ingredients and fold in whipped cream.
Chill in bowl or individual cups.

title: melon spicy dip
directions: Put cottage cheese, honey, cinnamon and nutmeg in blender; whirl until smooth.
Serve with melon cubes.

title: homemade biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.	Cut in shortening until mixture resembles
coarse meal.
Add milk all at once and stir just until	mixture
clings
together.
Knead gently.
Roll to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut
and place on ungreased baking sheet. Bake at 450°
for
10 to 12 minutes until golden brown.
Makes 10 to 12 biscuits.

title: raspberry delight
directions: Mix raspberries, water, sugar, lemon juice and cornstarch mixed with water. Cook and stir until thick and clear; let cool. Melt marshmallows with milk and let cool. Combine vanilla cookie crumbs with nuts and butter. Press into 9 x 13 pan. Add prepared Dream Whip to marshmallow mixture. Spread over crumb crust in pan. Drop fruit mixture by spoonfuls onto Dream Whip and marshmallow mixture. Refrigerate.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook onion and celery in chicken stock.
Mix together chicken, rice, onion, celery, mayo, soup and lemon juice.
Crumble Ritz crackers and sprinkle over mixture.
Melt butter and pour over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or microwave on High for 15 minutes.

title: chili
directions: In skillet brown chopped meat.
Add chopped up onion and 1 package chili mix.
When cooked and broken up, drain fat.

title: orange salad
directions: Use a large bowl.
Mix all ingredients in order given.
Chill.

title: triple-citrus margaritas
directions: Rub rims of 4 cocktail or champagne glasses with cut side of lime half.
Pour small pile of salt on a plate and dip moistened glass rims in salt to coat.
Fill a cocktail shaker with ice.
Add tequila, Triple Sec and citrus juices.
Shake well and strain into prepared glasses.
Makes 4 servings.

title: highland house salad dressing
directions: Combine and mix well.
Excellent for use on Greek salads.

title: coconut oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream Crisco, sugar, eggs and vanilla and fold in all other ingredients well.
Drop by large teaspoonful on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for about 8 to 10 minutes.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix ingredients together thoroughly.
Chill and serve.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients. Stir just until moistened.
(There will be a few lumps.)
Bake on hot, lightly-greased griddle.
For uniform cakes, use 1/4 cup measure.
Turn cakes when bubbles on surface break.
Serve with Whipped Orange Butter and syrup.
Makes about 1 1/2 dozen 4-inch cakes.

title: cheesecake
directions: Combine cracker crumbs, sugar and margarine.
Press in a 10-inch spring-form pan.
Bake for 10 minutes at 325°.
Cool.
Mix the cream cheese, sugar and flour.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well.
Blend in sour cream and vanilla; pour over crust.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then at 250° for an hour.
Loosen cake from rim.
Cool before removing rim.
Chill; top with berries.

title: trash
directions: Melt margarine.
Add Worcestershire sauce, garlic salt and garlic clove.
Mix together and boil for 20 minutes and pour over listed ingredients.
Bake in 200° oven for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: pumpkin dessert
directions: Mix canned pumpkin as directed on can for pie.
Pour in oblong dish.
Pour one box dry cake mix over pumpkin.
Sprinkle nuts on top as desired.
Melt oleo and pour over top.
Bake at 250° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: elephant stew
directions: After cleaning elephant meat, cut into cubes.
Add enough vegetable stock or beef broth to cover.
Cook 4 weeks over charcoal fire.
Serves 3000.
If more guests are expected, add the two rabbits.
Only add as last resort as most people don't like hare in their stew.

title: oreo delight
directions: Take all but 8 Oreos and crush.
Melt butter and mix with crushed Oreos and chopped pecans.
Line bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with mixture.
Mix pudding as per box and with softened cream cheese.
Spread mixture over Oreos.
Top with Cool Whip.
Crush remaining Oreos and sprinkle over Cool Whip.

title: pimento and cheese
directions: Mix egg, sugar, flour and evaporated milk in saucepan and warm over low heat; pour over cheese and stir.
Add pimento and vinegar and mix well.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in loaf pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken and noodle casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Cook noodles as directed; drain.
In medium saucepan, melt margarine; blend in flour.
Stir in cream, salt and broth.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Combine chicken, mushrooms and noodles in casserole.
Pour mixture over casserole.
Sprinkle with bread cubes and Parmesan cheese.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour or until center is bubbly and top is browned (lightly).

title: apricot tarts
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Shape in ball and chill.
Roll dough very thin.
Cut out with biscuit cutter.
Put 1 teaspoon apricot preserves in center of each.
Fold over and crinkle edges with fork.
Bake at 400° for about 10 minutes.
Do not let brown. Remove immediately from cookie sheet and sprinkle with confectioners sugar while still hot.

title: broccoli corn muffins
directions: Saute onion and broccoli in margarine.
Mix muffin mix with other ingredients.
Fold in sauteed mixture.
Bake in greased muffin tin or 7 x 11-inch baking dish for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: paulette's pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients, except 1 cup of the pecans.
Chill thoroughly.
Form into a ball.
Roll ball into the 1 cup finely chopped pecans.
Allow to come to room temperature before serving. Serve with crackers.

title: white bean tuna salad
directions: In a large bowl, add tuna; reserve the olive oil in a small bowl. Break up tuna in smaller pieces with a fork. Add beans and capers. In the bowl of olive oil, add red wine vinegar. (Should be 1 part vinegar to 2 parts oil; add more olive oil, if necessary.) Season with salt and pepper. Pour dressing on the tuna mixture. Add onion and tomatoes and toss gently. Put arugula on a platter and top with tuna mixture. Tear basil leaves over the top and serve immediately.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients except cocktail sauce together and spread on plate.
Refrigerate several hours.
Before serving, pour cocktail sauce on top.
Serve with Triscuits crackers.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix all together.
Add 2 teaspoons to an 8-ounce cup or glass of cold or hot water.

title: peanut butter silk pie
directions: Beat cream cheese, sugar, peanut butter, butter and vanilla in large mixer bowl, until creamy.
Gently fold in half the beaten cream, then fold in remaining cream until blended.
Spread filling in crust, smooth top.

title: ham fondue
directions: In medium saucepan or fondue pot, mix together ingredients. Cook and stir over medium-low heat until cheese is melted.
Keep warm over low heat.
Serve with vegetables, crackers or toasted pita bread wedges for dipping into fondue.

title: persimmon cookies
directions: Add soda to pulp.
Stir in quickly all other ingredients.
Drop teaspoonful on baking sheet.
Bake in slow oven (350°) until brown.

title: quick rolls
directions: Spoon into greased muffin tin.
Bake at approximately 350° for 12 to 15 minutes, according to your own oven.

title: quick cocoa cake
directions: Sift
first 5 ingredients
into
mixing
bowl.	Add
to rest, then beat well.
Bake in
2 layers or oblong pan at 350° for 40 minutes.
Frost with favorite frosting.

title: parmesan bread sticks
directions: Cut each biscuit in half.
Roll with hands until pencil shaped, 4 inches long.
Roll stick in butter, then in Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 18 minutes, until golden brown.

title: christmas punch
directions: Chill all the ingredients (except sherbet) and mix in large punch bowl.
Add Braum's lime sherbet, mix and serve.
Makes about 32 servings.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix sugar, flour, salt and cocoa.
Pour in milk; heat on stove until thick.
Add margarine and vanilla.
Serve with hot biscuits.

title: cheese ball
directions: Hand mix all ingredients and roll in pecans.
Serve with crackers.

title: caramel pie
directions: Fill a heavy 3-quart saucepan with water and bring to a boil. Remove
from
heat.
Place
unopened
can of Eagle condensed cream into the hot water.
Remove the label.
Turn heat to low, cover loosely, and cook for 4 hours.
Water must cover top
of
can during cooking.
Remove can from water, open and pour
into
a ready made chocolate graham cracker crust.
Mix together
Cool Whip
and
cream
cheese, spread on top of pie filling
and sprinkle
with
chocolate
chips.
Refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Beat eggs and cream with sugar. Add oil, pumpkin, flour, salt, soda, baking powder and cinnamon. Blend well, then stir in coconut and pecans. Pour batter into 3 well-greased and floured pans. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Cool.

title: deluxe casserole
directions: Mix together and refrigerate overnight.
Take out 1 hour before putting in oven.
Fill casserole or a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pineapple cheese bake
directions: Mix pineapple, cheese, sugar and flour together.
Pour into a greased baking dish.
Cover top with crushed Ritz crackers.
Pour melted butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: marinade for pork tenderloin
directions: Combine all ingredients. Place pork tenderloin in marinade and marinate 2 to 3 hours. Place pork and marinade in roasting pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Add water as needed while baking. Serve with applesauce.

title: cheesy corn spread
directions: Mash cheese into small bits. Blend in remaining ingredients, adding the corn last.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Makes 3 1/2 cups.

title: sparkle fruit punch
directions: Take some morning sunshine

title: daffodil cake
directions: Mix undrained pineapple and contents of pudding in saucepan (use no milk).
Cook over low heat just until it thickens.
Let cool.
Beat cream until thick and fold into pineapple mix.
Cut cake into 4 layers.
Put layers together with pineapple mix and frost top and sides.
Garnish with cherries and mint leaves.

title: stuffed eggplant
directions: Cut eggplant in 1/2 lengthwise.
Scoop out inside of eggplant, leaving outsides in which to put stuffing.
Cut meat of eggplant in 1-inch cubes.
Cook in boiling, salted water until tender, about 10 to 15 minutes; drain.
Mash with fork.
Saute onions, peppers and celery in oil until tender, but not brown; add meat.
Brown lightly.
Add mashed eggplant; stir.
Add salt, pepper, garlic powder, tomatoes and corn bread; mix thoroughly.
Stuff mixture into eggplant hulls.
Bake at 300° for about 45 minutes.

title: fresh apple nut cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into tube pan.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes at 350° (or until done).

title: health salad
directions: Shred all together the green and red cabbage, carrot, turnip, zucchini squash, apples and cheese.
Add radishes and green onions.
Tumble together evenly.
You may also add pineapple.

title: snack crackers
directions: Mix spices and oil.
Stir to blend, especially the dressing mix (it won't dissolve thoroughly).
Place crackers in a Ziploc bag with oil mixture.
Seal.
Turn occasionally to coat, about three hours.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix together last 6 ingredients; put in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Lay bacon on top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 2 hours.

title: stuffed tomatoes
directions: Slice tops off tomatoes and set aside.
Scoop out tomatoes and turn empty cases upside down to drain.
Mix mayo, lemon and cream. Stir in crabmeat and pepper. Fill tomato cases with crabmeat mixture and replace tops.
Chill before serving.
Serves 4.

title: annie's special salad
directions: Layer ingredients in order given.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Refrigerate until served.

title: dream frosting
directions: Combine margarine, cocoa and milk in a saucepan.
Heat slowly and bring to a boil.
Add remaining ingredients.
Beat well and spread over cake while still warm.
Leave cake in pan until ready to serve.
Cut in squares.

title: potato and cheese casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling salted water for 15 minutes or until done; drain well.
Saute garlic, green peppers and onions in butter for 2 minutes, until softened.
Mash potatoes.
Beat in garlic butter mixture, cream cheese, half and half, salt and pepper.
Fold in Camembert cheese.
Place in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes or until top begins to lightly brown.
Garnish with thyme or parsley.
Serve at once.

title: snicker bar dessert
directions: Mix pudding as directed on box.
Add peanut butter and mix before it sets up and fold in Cool Whip and softened ice cream and pour into square Pyrex dish and freeze.

title: date nut log
directions: Cook oleo, eggs, sugar and milk for 2 minutes.
Add pecans. Cook 2 more minutes.
Add dates; remove from the stove.
Add vanilla.
Stir in Rice Krispies.
Cool, then roll in a log and roll in coconut.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries and apples together.
Mix the cranberries, apples, marshmallows and sugar together.
Cover and refrigerate overnight or for several hours.
Add nuts and heavy cream.
Place in an 11 x 13-inch Pyrex dish or cupcake liners and freeze. Remove from freezer just before serving.
Return leftovers to freezer.

title: four layer dessert squares
directions: In a small mixing bowl, mix crackers, sugar and 1/2 cup butter.
Press lightly into a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix refried beans with taco seasoning.
Heat in microwave 2 minutes. Spread on round plate. Top with salsa, lettuce, tomato, cheese, sour cream, olives and onions. Chill. Serve with nacho chips.

title: basic buttermilk biscuits
directions: *Note:
Two cups sifted self-rising flour may be used in place of the plain flour.
Omit all of the dry ingredients, except the sugar if self-rising flour is used.

title: never fail meringue
directions: Blend cornstarch and cold water in a pan. Add boiling water and cook until clear.
Let stand until completely cool. Beat egg whites until foamy. Add sugar and beat until stiff, not dry.
Turn mixer on low speed and gradually add cold cornstarch mixture, salt and vanilla. Turn mixer to high speed and beat well. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: flavored oil
directions: Peel lemon from top to bottom in 3/4-inch strips.
Use yellow part only; trim out all of the white you can.
Peel garlic cloves.

title: tortilla for 1
directions: Heat beans, salsa and onion.
Serve on tortilla.
Top with sour cream.

title: corn bread
directions: Sift together cornmeal, flour, soda and salt; add buttermilk. Generously grease skillet with butter or margarine and place in hot oven until skillet is hot.
Sprinkle bottom of skillet with cornmeal and pour in batter.
Cook at 375° to 400° oven until brown.
Remove from oven and turn out on plate to cool or serve hot.
This is good eaten in a glass of milk.

title: tomato jam
directions: Combine sugar, tomatoes and jello.
Cook 12 minutes.
Pour into jars.
Cool and enjoy.
Freezes well.

title: sweet potato pound cake
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add sweet potatoes; beat well.
Combine flour, baking powder, soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt; gradually add to sweet potato mixture, beating well after each addition (batter will be stiff).
Stir in vanilla, coconut and pecans.
Spoon batter into a well-greased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes; remove from pan and let cool completely.
Yield:
One 10-inch cake.

title: cardboard box cake
directions: Completely cover
soda	box
x

2 1/4-inch)
with heavy-duty aluminum foil.
Spray with nonstick spray.
In	a
large
bowl,
combine cake mix, water and eggs. Pour into cardboard box.
Bake for 1 hour, or until done, in a 350° oven.	Cool cake completely.
Prick holes, about 1/2-inch apart,
with
chopstick.
Spoon cooled jello and water mixture over cake.	Chill
for 4 hours or more.
Cut cake, then spread Cool Whip on top.

title: sour cream snap string bean casserole
directions: Cook beans in juice for 25 minutes and drain.
Place in buttered casserole.
Mix all together in casserole. Bake in oven 15-20 minutes at 350 degrees.
Makes 6-8 servings.

title: lemon delight
directions: Mix crumbs, margarine and sugar.
Press into glass baking dish (save 10% to sprinkle on top).
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes. Dissolve jello with 1 cup boiling water and set aside.
Do not chill to set.
Cream together granulated sugar and cream cheese, lemon juice, rind and vanilla.
Add jello and combine well.
Beat evaporated milk.
Pour in prepared crust.
Sprinkle with balance of crumbs.
Chill to set.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Place a layer of white sauce in bottom of casserole, thin layer of asparagus, grated cheese, grated egg and cracker crumbs.
Repeat process until casserole is filled.
Put cracker crumbs on top and dot with butter.
(Can use 5 eggs.)
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: "the" chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream sugar, shortening and eggs.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake 30 minutes in a well-greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: vidalia onion pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix crackers and 4 tablespoons butter until blended.
Press mixture on bottom and up 1-inch on sides of 8-inch pie plate.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter and saute onions over medium heat until tender.
Arrange onions on cracker crust.
Beat eggs and milk until blended and pour mixture over onions. Sprinkle cheese over filling.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Baker until knife comes out clean, about 35 minutes.
Garnish with parsley.

title: batter-way bread
directions: Pour the warm water into a large mixing bowl and add the yeast.
Let stand a few minutes, then stir to dissolve.
Add about half the flour, sugar, salt and shortening.
Start the mixer on medium speed (or beat by hand ) and beat 2 minutes or until smooth.
Stop mixer.
Add the rest of the flour and stir in by hand until flour disappears.
Beating in this recipe will take the place of kneading.
Scrape down batter from sides of bowl.
Cover bowl with waxed paper and let rise in warm place until doubled, about 30 minutes.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Grate enough dill pickle to equal 1/2 cup. (I start out with whole pickles; they are easier to grate.) Save any leftovers for another time.

title: zucchini cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
When cool, ice with cream cheese frosting.

title: pineapple drop cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Drop on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until brown.

title: cheese broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli in 3 cans of broth until partially tender, then put through blender to chop a little finer and then melt butter in another pan and add flour (don't brown flour).
Then add the milk and then put the remaining chicken broth and broccoli in the milk and cook (over medium heat) 1/2 hour or 45 minutes.
Then add cheese and stir well until melted and serve hot.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: Bring 2 cups water to a boil; pour over oats and let stand at least 15 minutes.
When oats are lukewarm, add the honey, molasses, butter and salt.
Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water; let stand 5 minutes, then add to oat mixture.
Stir in enough of the flour to make an easy to handle dough.

title: cheese dip
directions: Saute onion and garlic in butter.
Add tomatoes and chilies. Pour into an electric fondue pot.
Add cubed cheeses and milk. Stir continually until cheeses are melted.
Add summer sausage. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: not just another potato casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes well and combine with 1/2 cup melted margarine in a large bowl.
Stir in sour cream, soup, onion, cheese, salt and pepper.
Place in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Combine cracker crumbs with margarine and sprinkle over top. Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Uncover and continue baking for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 12 servings.

title: jiffy corn pudding
directions: Mix together in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
All ingredients can be halved and poured into an 8 x 8-inch dish.

title: cheese, pasta and beef bake
directions: Cook pasta as directed on package; drain.
In skillet, brown meat.
Salt and pepper to taste; drain.
Add tomatoes.
Cook, uncovered, until slightly thickened.
Stir in onions and cream cheese.
Toss with remaining ingredients.
Cover 2 minutes to melt cheese.
Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: maple glazed chicken wings
directions: Combine ingredients.
Marinate wings for 4 hours.
Grill or broil, basting frequently.
Serves 4.

title: bourbon balls
directions: Grind pecans and wafers through fine food chopper.
Mix with remaining ingredients thoroughly.
Pinch off enough mixture to roll into balls the size of big cherries.
Dust with sugar.
May also be shaped into thin roll and ends dipped in colored icing.
Bourbon Balls keep indefinitely in an airtight container.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: rocky road
directions: Melt chips and oleo with milk.
Remove from heat.
In large bowl, combine nuts and marshmallows.
Stir in chocolate mixtures. Spread in buttered pan; chill.
Cut into squares.

title: kisses
directions: Stir peanut butter, sugar and eggs until well blended. Batter will be sticky. With floured hands, roll approximately 1 tablespoonful of mixture into a ball and place on ungreased cookie sheet about 1 1/2-inches apart. Bake in preheated 350° oven 12 to 14 minutes until cookies look dry and tops are cracked. Remove from oven and immediately press a chocolate kiss into the center of each cookie. Let cool 2 to 4 minutes on the cookie sheet before removing to a cooling rack.

title: sugarless cookies
directions: Mix dates, raisins and oleo in 1 cup water.
Boil for 3 minutes and let cool.
Mix other ingredients and add to raisin mix.
Test and cook like brownies at 350°.

title: coconut joys
directions: Melt butter in a saucepan.
Remove from heat.
Add powdered sugar and coconut.
Mix well.
Shape rounded teaspoonfuls of mixture into balls and make indentation in center of each.
Place on cookie sheets.
Fill centers with melted chocolate and chill until firm.
Store in refrigerator.
Set out at room temperature 10 to 15 minutes before serving.

title: beef pot roast
directions: Trim fat from meat and place in skillet on top of stove.
Heat until fat is melted.
If there is not sufficient fat, use 2 tablespoons of oil or shortening.
Dredge roast in flour and brown slowly on both sides.
Season with salt and pepper.
Place meat in 3-quart ovenware casserole dish.
Add onions and carrots plus 1/2 cup hot water or enough water to cover meat and vegetables.
Cover dish with lid.
Cook in microwave for about 1 1/2 hours.
Meat and vegetables should be tender.

title: maple mustard salmon
directions: Blend mustard, maple syrup, lemon juice, salt and pepper. Brush salmon with melted butter. Cook on outside grill and baste with maple mustard marinade. Salmon is done when inner flesh is light pink.

title: squash patties
directions: Cook squash until tender.
Drain well.
Combine squash with remaining ingredients.
Drop by spoon into hot oil.
Brown on both sides.
Serve while hot.

title: crazy cake
directions: In
a
large
bowl,
sift together flour, sugar, cocoa, soda and
salt.	Make
wells.
Place vanilla in one, oil in the second and vinegar in the third.
Pour water over all; mix with a fork.
Pour
the
batter
into
a 9 x 14-inch cake pan (greased and
floured
or sprayed with Pam).
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: homemade rolls
directions: Mix yeast in warm water in a large bowl.
Add shortening and stir to melt.
Mix in salt and sugar.
Stir in flour gradually. Mix thoroughly with wooden spoon or dough hook.
Put into a greased bowl to raise.
Cover and set in warm place until double in bulk. Punch down and shape into desired type rolls.
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Brush with butter.
Bake at 375°.

title: sweet 'n sour onions
directions: Rinse and drain onions.
Mix water, vinegar, brown sugar, tomato paste and cumin in large skillet.
Stir in onions and raisins.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and boil gently, uncovered, stirring 3 or 4 times, for 15 to 20 minutes or until liquid is syrupy.
Pack in jars.
Cool, cover and refrigerate.
Serve with roast meats, deli meats or poultry.

title: super dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350° and grease 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Pour pie filling on bottom, smooth out.
Add undrained, crushed pineapple.
Add cake mix, then nuts and coconut.
Melt margarine and pour evenly over top.
Bake 1 hour.
Enjoy hot with ice cream.

title: pork chop ole
directions: Brown chops in oil.
Meanwhile, season them.
Combine rice, water, tomato sauce and taco season.
Mix well.
Arrange chops over rice mixture in casserole dish.
Add onion; cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Uncover and put cheese on top.
Melt the cheese, then serve.

title: wild blueberry pancakes
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt in a mixing bowl.
Beat eggs, sour cream and milk together and add to flour mixture, beating until smooth.
Heat griddle over medium heat.
Lightly coat with oil.
Pour a scant 1/2 cup batter onto griddle; spread batter to make a 5 to 6 inch circles.
Sprinkle a few blueberries over.

When bubbles form and break on top and edges lose their wet and shiny look (about 1 minute), flip pancake. Cook second side until brown and baked through (about 1 minute). Continue until all batter is used.
Serve pancakes with warm blueberry sauce.

title: banana drop cookies
directions: In a mixer bowl, beat 1/2 cup oleo for 30 seconds.
Add 1 cup white
sugar
and beat until fluffy.
Add 2 eggs and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla;
beat
well.
Add
dry ingredients and 1 cup mashed bananas

bananas)
alternately
to
beaten mixture, beating after each addition.
Stir in 1/2 cup chopped walnuts. Drop
from

teaspoon
2 inches apart onto a well-greased cookie sheet.
Bake
in
a 375°oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove
from cookie
sheet
immediately.
Cool on wire rack.
Frost with Banana Butter Frosting.

title: layered beef and zucchini
directions: Grease 8-inch square baking dish.
Cook and stir ground beef in 10-inch skillet until brown; drain.

title: chicken and chilies casserole
directions: In a large bowl, combine sour cream, light cream, onion, chilies, salt and pepper.
Stir in potatoes, chicken and 2 cups of cheese.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until golden brown. Sprinkle with remaining cheese before serving.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: biscuits
directions: Mix flour, salt and baking powder.
Measure oil into 1/2 cup of milk.
Stir into flour.
Add 1 cup of milk to rest of dough. Pat out lightly on floured board.
Cut with metal biscuit cutter. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.

title: iced tea punch
directions: Brew tea bags in hot water.
Add sugar, orange juice and lemonade; mix well.
Place in clean gallon container.
Fill the rest of container with water.
Chill.
Serve with lemon and orange slices as a garnish.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix together the cake mix, milk, oil and eggs.
Add dry jello and strawberries.
Pour into prepared 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Punch holes in cake for icing.

title: 8-layer chocolate cake
directions: Cream margarine, oil and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, alternating with milk and flour, beating at low speed of mixer until all are mixed.
Add vanilla.
Use 1 cup batter per layer. Bake at 350 degrees until done.

title: bread pudding
directions: Crumble bread and cover with milk.
Add sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla flavoring to taste.
Melt butter.
Put in pan.
Add mix to fill pan about 1/3 full.
Preheat oven to 300° and cook until knife comes out clean.

title: stuffed potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes and let cool.
Scoop out the inside of potato, leaving shell.
Mix potato, cottage cheese, mayonnaise, mustard, Cheddar cheese and spices together and fill potato shells with mixture.
Top with a tomato slice and sprinkle with cheese and paprika.
Bake in 375° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
