Enjoy!

title: molded beet salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin with hot juice from can of beets (1 cup). Add 1 cup of applesauce and diced or chopped beets (1 to 1 1/4 cups).
Chill.

title: dutch fried cheese
directions: Beat egg whites slightly with water.
Dip cheese slices into egg whites, then into crumbs.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Saute in skillet in butter or margarine until golden brown on both sides. Serves 8.

title: pizza
directions: Mix
mayonnaise
and Parmesan cheese.
Spread on 1 side of French bread.
Add pepperoni and Mozzarella.
Bake at 350° until Mozzarella melts.

title: apple muffins
directions: Put together in a bowl flour, 1/4 cup sugar, salt, baking powder, beaten egg, milk and shortening; just stir enough to mix ingredients.
Don't beat.
Mix 1/4 cup sugar with apples and fold into batter.
Grease muffin tins and fill 2/3 full.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes a dozen nice muffins.
Set oven at 400°.

title: salmon rice au gratin
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Melt butter in saucepan. Add celery and onions and cook until onion is transparent. Add flour and seasonings. Add milk and soup, stirring until sauce is smooth. Blend sauce with remaining ingredients and pour into buttered casserole dish. Top with bread or cracker crumbs and dots of butter. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add seasoning mix and water as directed on package.
Simmer until liquid is absorbed.
Crumble chips onto plate; add lettuce, ground beef and tomatoes.
Top with cheese and sour cream.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: death by chocolate
directions: In large bowl place 1/2 of cake broken into small pieces.
Mix pudding with 2 cups milk and the 8 ounces Cool Whip.
Spoon 1/2 over cake, then spoon 1/2 of 12 ounce Cool Whip.
Sprinkle candy over Cool Whip.
Repeat: rest of cake, then rest of pudding/Cool Whip mix, rest of regular Cool Whip and candy.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt 1 stick margarine in Pyrex dish.
Add 2 cups graham cracker crumbs.
Mix well.
Press into dish to form crust.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Drain tuna.
Break into bite-size pieces.
Mix together soup, water and soy sauce.
Combine tuna and all remaining ingredients except 1 cup noodles which are sprinkled on top at time of baking. Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: spicy bean dip
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine all ingredients.
Heat thoroughly over medium-high heat until cheese is melted and mixture is smooth, stirring frequently, approximately 5 to 7 minutes.
Serve warm with nacho chips.

title: easter eggs
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in large bowl with hands.
Shape into form of eggs.
Dip into dipping chocolate melted together with paraffin wax.
Keep hot while dipping eggs.
Cover eggs well with chocolate.
Put on wax paper to cool.
Makes about 40 eggs.

title: hot chicken or turkey salad
directions: Mix together and put in baking dish.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.
Top with shoestring potato sticks and bake 10 minutes more.

title: stefado
directions: Season meat with salt and pepper.
Melt butter in a Dutch oven; add meat and coat with butter (but do not brown).
Arrange whole onions over meat.
Mix tomato paste, wine, red wine vinegar, sugar, garlic and cumin and pour over meat and onions.
Add bay leaf.
Place a plate over onions to hold them down while cooking. Cover and simmer for 3 hours or until meat is very tender; do not stir ingredients while cooking!
As you serve, stir sauce gently to blend.

title: green pea salad
directions: Drain peas; add to medium bowl.
Dice boiled eggs and dice onion.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add Miracle Whip; mix all together.
Top with grated cheese.
Cover and refrigerate for approximately 1 to 2 hours.

title: linguine with white clam sauce
directions: Heat oil and 2 tablespoons butter in saucepan over low heat. Add garlic, parsley, pepper and oregano.
Simmer 5 minutes.
In another pan, melt remaining butter over low heat.
Add flour and, stirring constantly, cook about 2 minutes.
Slowly add clam juice while stirring.
Combine the contents of both saucepans and simmer for 5 minutes.
Add clams and simmer for an additional 5 minutes. Serve over linguine.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together cheese, salt, red pepper, garlic powder and pecans.
Form into 2 balls.
Then pour some chili powder and paprika on wax paper and roll the cheese in this to cover it. Wrap in paper and refrigerate about an hour.

title: microwave parmesan potatoes
directions: Peel and cut potatoes into 1-inch cubes.
Place first 6 ingredients in blender or food processor container. Cover and process to make fine crumbs.
Transfer crumb mixture to plastic bag.
Set aside.
Place butter in an 8-inch round microproof baking dish. Cook at 100% for 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove from oven; add potatoes and stir to coat.
Drain and reserve any remaining butter.
Add potatoes, a few t a time, to crumb mixture in plastic bag. Shake to coat evenly.
Arrange potatoes in single layer in shallow microproof baking dish or pie plate just large enough to accomodate.
Cover with plastic wrap and place in oven.
Cook at 100% power for 5 minutes. Remove from oven.
Stir in reserved butter. Do not cover.
Return to oven and cook at 100% power for 4 minutes. Sprinkle with remaining 1 tablespoon cheese and garnish with parsley before serving.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate a few hours before serving.

title: haluski
directions: In frying pan, over low heat, place the Polish sausage, onion, margarine, garlic salt and onion powder.
Cook until sausage is browned and the onion is sauteed.
Put the egg noodles into boiling water; cook until tender and strain.
Add margarine to hot noodles; cover to keep warm.
When sausage is brown, add kraut to frying pan and stir slowly until kraut browns on the ends.
Remove from heat and add the cooked noodles.

title: orange sherbet salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add orange sherbet.
When partially set, add other ingredients, folding in the whipped cream last.
Chill until firm.
Yield: about 12 servings.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Mix jello and water; let jell partly, but still soft.
Mix other ingredients with the jello with a mixer.
Place marshmallows on top and place in refrigerator and let jell until firm.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown meat.
Drain.
Mash tomatoes real fine.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes or until noodles are done.

title: never fail broccoli souffle
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Beat eggs and add mayonnaise.
Add butter, flour and milk.
Blend all ingredients in blender, until smooth.
Bake a 2 1/2 quart casserole at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.
You may wish to place dish in a pan of water while baking.
Serves 4.

title: hot cheesy crabmeat
directions: Combine crab, cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Add lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce and onion to taste.
Put in a shallow baking dish (quiche dish works well).
Top with Mozzarella cheese and bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until cheese is lightly golden brown.
Serve hot with crackers.

title: angel food dessert
directions: Break into pieces in 9 x 9-inch baking dish, 1 angel food or orange chiffon cake.
In a large stew pan, combine orange juice and 7-Up or ginger ale.
Bring to a boil and remove from heat. Add marshmallows.
Mix well and let cool completely.
Whip the cream and add to mixture.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour over cake pieces and top with coconut.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: open-face ham sandwiches
directions: Blend cream cheese and butter; stir in cheese, paprika, oregano and garlic powder.
Spread 2/3 of mixture over English muffins.
Top each with a ham and tomato slice.
Spoon remaining cheese mixture on center of each tomato slice.
Place on baking sheet and broil until golden brown.

title: sour cream chicken enchilada bake
directions: Oil a large casserole.
Place flour tortillas on bottom of pan (I tear mine up and cover bottom; it makes it easier to remove in serving).
Mix soup and sour cream.
Place 1/2 on tortillas. Place 1/2 of chopped chicken, onion and green chilies on soup mix. Sprinkle 1/2 cheese over this.
Repeat to make a second layer. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let set for 10 minutes before serving.
You can use canned chicken.

title: zucchini pizza appetizers
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Pour into 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut into squares.
(Freeze, if desired.)

title: under the sea salad
directions: Make pudding as directed, then add in all ingredients; chill.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In
a large bowl, stir together chili, salsa, mushrooms, Parmesan cheese and parsley flakes.
Layer noodles, cottage, cheese, chili mixture and Mozzarella in a 9 x 9-inch baking dish coated with Pam.
Repeat layers.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until lasagna is thoroughly heated.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: cuban picadillo(ground beef skillet dinner)
directions: Brown beef in skillet.
Drain off excess fat.
Add onion and green pepper and cook until onion is transparent.
Add raisins, olives, garlic and bay leaf.
Cook 15 minutes over low heat. Serve over rice.
Serves 4 people.
Meat and rice may be mixed together before serving.

title: buttered baked chicken and gravy
directions: Dip chicken in milk.
Roll in seasoning and flour.
Bake in butter at 425° for 30 minutes.
Turn chicken.
Mix soup, 3/4 cup milk and water.
Pour over chicken.
Bake 30 minutes or until tender.
Serve with rice.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Chill milk.
Wash, cap and slice berries.
Add sugar to berries; set aside.
Beat milk in a large bowl until foamy.
Add glaze.
Beat until mixed.
Fold in strawberries.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Combine cranberries, apple juice, sugar and allspice in medium sized nonreactive saucepan.
Bring to boiling.
Lower heat; simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes.
Add chopped apple.
Cook 5 more minutes.
Serve warm or chilled.

title: fried bananas
directions: Fry bananas in pan for 3 to 5 minutes.
When in a frypan, sprinkle sugar and cinnamon over bananas.
Fry for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes more.

title: bourbon slush
directions: Combine 1 1/2 water and sugar in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil to make a syrup.
Add 2 cups water, orange juice, lemonades, instant tea, bourbon and cherries.
Store in freezer until ready to serve.
Add Sprite or Ginger Ale to make slushy.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add bananas and mix well.
Fold in flour a little at a time.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into greased loaf pan and bake at 350° for about an hour.

title: nancy's fish fantastic
directions: Spread fish fillets in a buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle with lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Layer with onions, then mushrooms, then cheese and finally concentrated mushroom soup.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Bake at 350 degrees for 25 minutes.

title: italian spaghetti
directions: Cook and stir ground beef, onion and green pepper until meat is browned and onion is tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Cover; simmer for 1 1/2 hours, stirring sauce occasionally.

title: blueberry buckle
directions: Mix 3/4 cup sugar, shortening and egg.
Stir in milk.
Add 2 cups flour and baking powder; blend until smooth.
Fold in berries.
Pour into a 9-inch square pan which has been greased.

title: zucchini with cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish. Slice zucchini crosswise into 1/4-inch slices.
In medium bowl, combine flour with 1/2 teaspoon salt, 1/2 teaspoon oregano and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
Toss zucchini slices in seasoned flour to coat well.
Slowly heat oil in a large skillet.
Saute zucchini until golden brown.
Drain.
Cover bottom of dish with zucchini.
Top with tomato slices.
Combine sour cream and remaining salt, oregano and pepper.
Spread evenly over tomatoes.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Serves 6.
Recipe can be doubled.

title: deluxe pecan pie
directions: In medium bowl, beat eggs slightly.
Beat in next 5 ingredients.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake in 350° oven for 55 minutes.

title: pecan jumbles
directions: Beat first 4 ingredients until smooth. Stir in next 4 ingredients; mix well. Drop on greased cookie sheet. Top each with pecan half.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: quick pizza casserole
directions: Cook ground beef or turkey until brown; stir to crumble. Drain.
Spoon meat into an 8-inch baking dish.
Top with jar of sauce and cheese.
Combine biscuit mix, milk and eggs.
Beat until smooth and pour over casserole, covering evenly.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: deviled eggs with chives
directions: Remove yolks from eggs and blend well with remaining ingredients.
Fill cooked eggs.
Makes 24 servings.

title: horseradish-jello salad
directions: Mix Jell-O's with boiling water.
When cool, mix rest of the ingredients and chill.

title: breakfast quiche
directions: Mix together eggs, soup, milk and mustard.
Crumble bread in 9 x 13-inch loaf pan.
Sprinkle with cheese and meat pieces.
Pour liquid mixture over the dry mix.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: home pride home style stuffing
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine bread and poultry seasoning; set aside.
Combine soup, water, onion, celery, pepper and butter in saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Pour soup mixture over seasoned bread; mix well and pour in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or fill a 15 to 17 pound turkey before roasting.
For drier stuffing, decrease water 1/4 cup.
For more moist stuffing, increase water 1/4 cup.
Makes 8 servings.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Pour boiling water over jello.
Dissolve marshmallows.
Whip. Add pineapple juice.
Chill.
Do not congeal.
Add pineapple, pecans, cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Fold in whipping cream. Chill.

title: henrietta's hermits
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Drop by teaspoon, 2 inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as instructed on box.
Spread coconut and nuts in bottom of dish 13 x 9.
Pour cake mix over nuts and coconut.
Combine melted margarine, cream cheese and 2 cups of powdered sugar.
Beat until smooth.
Pour over cake batter and bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: brown cow punch
directions: In a punch bowl, combine milk and extract. Add ice cream by scoopfuls and allow to float on top of punch or scoop ice cream into glasses. Combine milk and extract and then pour over ice cream. Makes 3 quarts.

title: dog bones
directions: Mix in a bowl, peanut butter and dry milk.
Add honey.
Mix very well.
Divide dough into 6 pieces.
Mold each piece into the shape of a dog bone.
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs on both sides.

title: chocolate chip pumpkin muffins
directions: In large bowl, mix flour, sugar, pie spice, soda, baking powder and salt.
In a separate bowl, combine eggs, pumpkin and butter; whisk until blended.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Pour over dry ingredients.
Fold with spatula until well mixed.
Spoon batter into greased muffin cups.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Turn onto rack to cool.
Reheat before serving.
Makes 14 muffins.

title: dot's strawberry bavarian(serves 8)
directions: Defrost strawberries and drain.
Measure strawberry juice and add enough cold water to make 1 cup.
Combine gelatin with hot water and stir until gelatin dissolves.
Add strawberry juice and refrigerate until thickened.
Whip until doubled in bulk.
Stir in the strawberries.
Whip the cream and fold into the strawberry mixture.
Pour into serving dish.
Cover with plastic wrap and return to refrigerator.
Chill until firm.

title: mac-n-cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions on box.
Combine all ingredients together except 1 c. cheese.
Place in crock pot.
Top with remaining cheese.
Cook on high for 1 hr. and low for 2 or cook on low for 4 hr.

title: strawberry sherbet
directions: Mix all together with hand mixer.
Pour into ice cream freezer and process.

title: pineapple lime mold
directions: In a bowl, dissolve the lime gelatin in boiling water.
Add the pineapple juice drained from the pineapple.
Chill until syrupy (30 minutes).
In a second bowl, cream the cheese.
Gradually work in the chilled gelatin syrup, blending until smooth.
After each addition, add the crushed pineapple, chopped celery and nuts.
Pour into a 4-cup mold or individual molds.
Chill 2 hours.

title: creole potato wedges
directions: Spray shallow baking pan with cooking spray.
Dredge potato wedges in Creole seasoning.
Place potato wedges in single layer on the baking pan.
Spray with cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream sugar and oil. Add eggs, pumpkin and water. Separately mix flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and cloves. Then add to the other mixture. Add nuts and raisins, if desired. Divide batter into 2 loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Do not grease pans.

title: rye crisps
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients, Cut in butter with pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal. Sprinkle water evenly over surface; stir with a fork until all dry ingredients are moistened. Shape into ball. Roll dough to 1/8 inch thickness on a lightly floured surface. Cut dough into 1 1/2 inch diamonds, and place on ungreased baking sheets. Sprinkle lightly with fennel seeds. Bake 375 degrees for 12 to 14 minutes or until golden brown.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: In large frying pan, saute chopped onion and 1 large green pepper in oil.
Add ground beef and break up meat with a fork. Cook over medium heat until brown and done.
Drain any fat, then place meat in a large bowl.
Add parsley, bread crumbs and salt to taste.
When meat cools, add 2 eggs which were beaten ahead of time.
Blend well.

title: hearty taco dip supreme
directions: Brown onion and ground beef.
Drain off extra oil.
Season with salt and pepper.
Place in the bottom of glass bowl.
Layer tomatoes and avocados on top of ground beef, then layer cheese. Fold in taco sauce.
Spread sour cream on top.
Serve while hot with flavored tortilla chips.
(Men really love this.)

title: easy cheese ring
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except preserves.
Spray a ring mold with Pam spray.
Place mix in mold and refrigerate until firm.
Turn out when ready to serve.
Fill center with strawberry preserves.
Serve with an assortment of crackers.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Grind fruit in food processor or blender.
Add sugar and let stand 2 hours.
Combine jello and water.
Stir to dissolve.
Add to cranberry mixture.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and chill.
Serve with turkey.

title: quick mexican casserole
directions: Line casserole with nacho chips.
Brown meat and drain.
Add other ingredients and pour into casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: barb's baked beans
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; crumble and set aside.
Saut onions in bacon fat; set aside.
In large casserole, combine B&M beans, kidney beans, lima beans and chickpeas.
Add the bacon, onion, brown sugar, dry mustard, vinegar and garlic powder.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: morning glory muffins
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking soda, cinnamon and salt together in large bowl.
Stir in apples, raisins, pecans, coconut and carrots. In a separate bowl, beat eggs, oil and vanilla.
Add to other mixture, stirring until just combined.
Spoon into muffin tins filling 2/3 full.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 35 minutes until golden brown.
Cool in tins on rack for a few minutes before removing and cooling completely on rack.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Oil a 12-cup Bundt pan.
Blend all ingredients except powdered sugar with electric mixer.
Pour into pan.
Bake 45 minutes.
Cool.
Invert onto serving platter; sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: chocolate balls
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together well.
Form in small balls and chill overnight.
Melt chocolate chips with Parowax in double boiler or cooking pot.
Dip balls in chocolate and let cool on wax paper.

title: grandma's tea cakes(lizzie folds)
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Mix well.
Spoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° until brown.

title: hawaiian fruit dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate until serving time. Serve with apple slices or chunk bananas.

title: lazy stroganoff
directions: Brown onion and hamburger.
Add remaining ingredients. Simmer.
Serve over noodles.

title: pancit(from philippines)
directions: Stir-fry (in oil) first 3 ingredients.
Add next 5 ingredients and simmer until cooked (20 minutes).
After this is done, cook rice noodles, as directed on package (about 5 to 10 minutes). Drain.
Add to mixture.
Add shrimp.
Add more soy sauce to taste.

title: felafel
directions: Rinse chickpeas and drain.
Combine all ingredients besides flour in a food processor or bowl.
Mash to a uniform batter.
Add flour, stir thoroughly.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Put in microwavable bowl.
Do not mix.
Microwave for 2 1/2 minutes or until butter melts.

title: salmon mousse
directions: Drain salmon, reserving liquid.
Add water to equal 1/2 cup. Remove skin and bone from salmon and flake.
In small saucepan, combine the salmon liquid and gelatin.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Cook and stir over medium heat until gelatin is dissolved and transfer to a bowl.
Gradually stir in mayonnaise, then the chili sauce, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, dill weed and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Fold in salmon, flaked tuna, chopped eggs, olives and onion.
Turn mousse mix into greased 6-cup mold.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Chill for at least 5 hours or until firm.
Unmold and garnish with sliced olives if desired.

title: cheesy fillets
directions: Cut fish into serving portions. Dip into dressing and roll in cracker crumbs.
Place on greased cookie sheet and drizzle margarine over fish.
Bake at 500° for 12 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: date rolls
directions: Mix
together sugar, margarine, eggs and dates and cook over medium
heat
about
to	10 minutes (until dates have melted). Remove
from heat and add to Rice Krispies, nuts and vanilla. When
cool,
roll in confectioners sugar or coconut. Roll in small rolls.
Better if partially frozen when served.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Allow cream cheese to soften.
Add syrup of fruit to cream cheese and mix until creamy.
Add fruit and sliced bananas.
Pour into ice tray in freezing unit.
When frozen, cut into squares. Serve on lettuce with mayonnaise on top.

title: heavenly chocolate ice cream
directions: Combine candy and sweetened condensed milk in saucepan.
Cook over low heat until candy is melted, stirring constantly.
Add about 1 quart of milk to candy mixture.
Blend well.
Put into freezer can.
Stir in syrup and milk until it reaches the fill line on freezer container.
Make ice cream and enjoy!

title: baked cheesy chili dip
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees.
Mix all ingredients in one quart casserole dish.
Bake 25-30 minutes or until thoroughly heated. Stir before serving.
Serve hot with toasted bread slices or tortilla chips.

title: cracker salad
directions: Crush crackers; put in large bowl. Add all ingredients; mix well. Put in covered bowl; chill for 2 hours before serving.

title: pineapple sheet cake
directions: Cream together sugar and shortening; add other ingredients to form a soft dough.
Press 3/4 of the dough in a cookie sheet going up the sides with the dough.
Spread on any kind of canned pie filling.
I like pineapple.
Make strips with the remaining dough and press across top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: beef stew(slow cooker)
directions: Put beef cubes in a bowl with flour, a little black pepper and garlic salt.
Coat beef cubes.
Brown beef cubes in hot oil on top of stove.
When brown, put beef cubes in slow cooker.
Mix in remaining ingredients; cook on medium-high for 7 hours or on high for 5 hours or until vegetables are tender.
Enjoy with hot French bread.

title: salmon patties
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Additional corn flake crumbs may be needed to make firm.
Refrigerate 25 minutes.
Make patties and fry until brown.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken and peas
directions: Cook chicken until tender in water.
Cool and pull meat from bones and place in casserole.
Cover with English peas, rice and mushroom soup.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: walnut crescents
directions: In large bowl, cream butter, confectioners sugar, vanilla and salt until fluffy.
Stir in flour and walnuts until well blended. Cover and chill 30 minutes or until firm enough to handle.
Break off small dough pieces and on lightly floured surface roll with hands into finger-thick strips.
Cut in 2-inch lengths.
Taper ends, then shape into crescents.
Place 1 inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated oven (300°) for 18 to 20 minutes or until firm to touch.
While warm, roll in granulated sugar. Place on racks to cool.
Store airtight in cool place.
Makes 60.

title: baked corn casserole
directions: Mix all in a 2 1/2-quart dish sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or so, covered with foil.
(Use a cover, it may run over.)

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix together thawed hash browns and 1/2 cup margarine.
Add salt, pepper, undiluted soup, cheese sour cream and onion.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together corn flakes and 1/2 cup margarine.
Put on top of potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: dirt
directions: Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar.
In another bowl, mix pudding, milk and vanilla extract until it resembles pudding texture.
Add to cream cheese mixture.
Fold in Cool Whip. Beginning with Oreo cookies, layer pudding mixture in large flower pot with gummie worms scattered throughout.
End with cookie layer.
Refrigerate.
Before serving, place an artificial flower in dirt.
Serve with a trowel.

title: hamburger barbecue
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Add all other ingredients.
Mix well and cook slowly for 1/2 hour.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: In a saucepan, cook pudding and milk over medium heat until thickened and bubbly.
Remove from the heat and cool slightly.

title: hamburger corn bake
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions and drain.
In a large skillet, cook beef and onion until meat is browned and onion is tender.
Drain off fat.
Stir in soup, sour cream, milk, pimento, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Stir in cooked noodles. Turn mixture in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Toss bread crumbs with melted butter.
Sprinkle atop casserole.
Bake uncovered in a 350° oven about 50 minutes or until heated through.

title: new england roast
directions: Mash beans or put through food chopper.
Mix with other ingredients.
Bake in greased loaf pan at 375° for 30 minutes or until firm and nicely brown.

title: spicy cranberry chutney
directions: Combine cranberries, raisins, sugar, cinnamon, ginger, cloves and water in saucepan.
Cook 15 minutes over medium heat until berries pop and mixture thickens.

title: icebox butter ring(no sugar in dough)
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm milk, add eggs and sour cream. Sift together flour and salt and cut in butter or margarine as for pie dough.
Add yeast mixture.
Mix well and chill overnight. Divide dough in 4 parts.
Roll each to a rectangle, brush with melted butter and sprinkle with a little cinnamon and spread liberally with nuts, raisins and a hand full of brown sugar.
Roll up like jelly roll sealing edge firmly.
Form into a ring sealed side down on greased pan sealing ends.
Brush with melted butter or margarine.
Let rise 2 hours. Cut about 6 gashes in ring to let steam escape during baking. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until done.
Frost with confectioners icing.
Butter rings also are delicious with prepared poppy seed or Solo filling.
Yields 4 rings.

title: kentucky spoon bread
directions: Add cornmeal to milk.
Cook slowly until thick and smooth. Add margarine and well beaten egg yolks (add eggs slowly).
Cover and allow to steam while beating egg whites.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour in greased pan.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes or until brown.
Serve hot with butter.

title: stir-fried rice confetti
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Saute onion 5 minutes. Add remaining ingredients except sunflower seeds.
Heat, uncovered, over medium heat for about 10 minutes until rice is golden. Sprinkle sunflower seeds across the top before serving, if desired.

title: double cheese and zucchini bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish. Melt 1/4 cup butter in heavy skillet.
Add onion and garlic and cook until softened, stirring occasionally, 4 to 5 minutes.
Add zucchini and cook until just tender, about 10 minutes, stirring frequently.
Remove from heat.
Stir in 1 cup Monterey Jack cheese, 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese, 1/4 cup bread crumbs and Italian seasoning.
Season with salt and pepper.
Transfer mixture to prepared dish.
Sprinkle remaining Monterey Jack cheese.
Combine eggs and cream.
Pour over zucchini; sprinkle remaining Parmesan and bread crumbs over.
Dot with remaining 1/4 cup butter.
Bake until golden brown, about 40 minutes.

title: shrimp or crab dip
directions: Blend well and chill.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix everything together in order given.
Form small balls. Dip the top in sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 370° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Don't overbake.

title: heavenly fluff
directions: Dissolve gelatine in cold water.
Heat egg yolks, milk, sugar and salt until it makes a custard.
Pour over gelatine and cool. Add stiffly beaten egg whites and whipped cream.
Grease pan and break cake into small pieces.
Pour the mixture over the cake. Sprinkle with coconut.
Top with maraschino cherries and chill overnight.

title: five minute fudge
directions: Heat together until melted and pour into buttered plate.

title: easy pie crust
directions: Mix flour and Crisco until crumbly.
In measuring cup, add vinegar and egg; mix with fork.
Add enough water to make 1 cup; add to flour.
Can freeze or keep in refrigerator.

title: i can't believe it's a cookie
directions: Mix all ingredients except kisses, drop by teaspoonful onto cookie sheet.
Press chocolate kisses in center of each cookie. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pork and bean bake
directions: Turn beans into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Arrange chops over beans.
Dash with salt and pepper, then lightly spread with mustard.
Sprinkle brown sugar.
Spread with catsup.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Place onions on top of each chop and bake for 15 minutes.
Trim with parsley.
Serves 5 or 6.

title: chili cheese dogs(microwave)
directions: Place hot dogs in buns and arrange them in a paper towel lined dish.
Top each hot dog with 2 tablespoons chili and one piece of cheese.
Microwave at High for 2 to 5 minutes, or until the cheese melts, rotating dish twice during cooking.

title: paradise pumpkin pie
directions: Combine cream cheese, sugar and vanilla, mixing at medium speed on electric mixer until well blended. Blend in egg.
Spread onto bottom of pastry shell. Combine remaining ingredients except syrup and pecans.
Mix well.
Carefully spoon over cream cheese mixture. Bake at 350° for 65 minutes. Cool.
Brush with syrup. Top with pecans.
Makes 8 servings.

title: apple salad
directions: Mix pineapple, flour, sugar, salt and butter. Cook until thick; set aside to cool. Add apples, cut into bite size pieces. Mix cream cheese with Cool Whip and spread on top. Sprinkle with chopped pecans.

title: grated apple pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, cinnamon and apple.
Melt butter and pour over mixture; beat well.
Add 1 whole egg and beat well.
Pour into pie shell and bake 10 minutes at 375°.
Turn oven down to 300° and cook until brown.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Put corn, green beans and peas in a colander to drain.
Let drain while you make the marinade; which is pimentos, green pepper, onion and celery.
Heat oil, vinegar and sugar.
Let this cool.
Pour over vegetables.
Let set in fridge for 12 to 24 hours before serving.

title: mexican meat loaf
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet, stirring until crumbly; drain. Add the next 9 ingredients, mixing well.
Simmer for 5 minutes. Layer 1/2 the tortillas and ground beef mixture in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Arrange small slices of cream cheese over beef mixture.
Top with remaining tortillas, ground beef mixture and grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: missouri cookies
directions: Boil first 5 ingredients for 4 minutes; remove from heat and stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop mixture from teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: senate bean soup
directions: Combine beans,	water
and ham shank in large deep pot. Simmer 1 1/2
hours
or
until
beans
are tender.
Remove ham shank and trim meat off bone.
Return to pot and add remaining ingredients. Simmer
an	additional
20	to 30 minutes, until beans
are tender
and soup has thickened.
Serves 10 (1 cup) portions.

title: lemon sauce
directions: Mix together the sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Stir in water and lemon juice until mixture is smooth.
Add grated lemon rind (if desired).
Cook over medium heat until thick and clear. Remove from heat.
Add butter; stir until melted.
Good over pound cake or gingerbread.

title: banana chip cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter and sugar a Bundt pan.
In small bowl, combine first 4 ingredients.
In large mixing bowl beat butter and sugar until creamy and light.
Beat in eggs, bananas, yogurt and vanilla until combined.
Gradually stir in flour mixture.
Stir in 1/2 cup chips.
Spoon batter into prepared pans.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes or until pick comes out clean.
Cool 15 minutes in pan.
Remove and cool completely.
In small saucepan over low heat, melt remaining chips.
Drizzle over cake.

title: kim's tuna casserole
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese according to package directions. Heat peas and corn in pan together.
Then drain.
In large bowl combine tuna, macaroni and cheese, peas, corn and diced eggs.
Then add about 6 heaping tablespoonfuls of mayonnaise.
Serve with Ritz crackers.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; mix well.
Blend in the remaining. Chill dough for 2 hours.
Heat oven to 400°.
Take 1/3 dough and place on a floured surface.
Roll out.
Cut with cookie cutters. Place 1-inch apart on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Cook 5 to 8 minutes.

title: quail stuffed with sausage
directions: Clean birds, do not split.
For each bird, saute 1/4 pound bulk sausage; add an equal amount of breadcrumbs and stuff birds with mixture.
Rub birds with olive oil and dust with salt and pepper.
Roast in 325° oven.

title: pecan sandies
directions: Cream margarine; blend in flour, sugar and vanilla and add nuts.
Mix well.
Shape in small balls; place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 300° for 25 or 30 minutes, or until lightly browned.
While still warm, roll in powdered sugar.
Cool thoroughly before serving.

title: peanut butter star cookies
directions: Mix together and drop dough from a teaspoon onto ungreased pan.
Press a chocolate star on top of each.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: old-fashioned michigan bean soup
directions: Wash beans thoroughly. Cover with water. Bring to a boil. Boil for 2 minutes. Cover. Remove from heat.
Let stand 1 hour. Add ham, salt and pepper.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 2 1/2 hours.
Remove ham bone and cut off meat.
Add onion, meat and tomatoes.
Mix
well.
Cover and simmer 1 hour longer. Stir in milk.
Heat a few minutes more and serve.

title: west virginia reunion beans
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Mix all ingredients together and cook 4-5 hours in crock-pot, not on high.

title: copper dollars
directions: Slice carrots 1/4-inch thick.
Cook carrots in 1-inch boiling water, covered, until tender (10 to 15 minutes).
Drain and cool. Slice and separate onion into rings.
Slice green pepper into 1/4-inch wide strips.
In a large bowl, place carrots, onion and green pepper along with remaining ingredients; mix well.
Cover and refrigerate 12 hours or longer.
Keeps for several days in refrigerator.
Yield: 8 cups.

title: pork chops and sauerkraut
directions: Brown chops and drain.
In skillet, layer ingredients over chops in order given.
Cover tightly and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: apricot balls(club member: leslie jordan)
directions: Mix apricots, coconut and milk. Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll each in nuts. Let stand 2 hours or until firm.

title: peanut butter swirl bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine peanut butter, butter, brown sugar, sugar.
Beat until creamy.
Add eggs and vanilla, beat until combined.
Add flour, baking powder, salt and beat until blended. Spread into greased 13 x 9 inch pan.
Sprinkle 2 cups chocolate chips over surface.
Bake 5 to 7 minutes (to melt chips).
Remove from oven and run knife through chips until marbleized.
Return to oven to bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Put toothpick in center.
If it comes out clean it is done.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Mix cake mix, sour cream, Wesson oil, sugar and eggs all together, adding eggs one at a time.
Mix raisins, brown sugar and cinnamon in separate bowl.
Pour part of first cake batter into greased 9 x 13-inch pan, then swirl some of dry mix.
Pour remainder of batter, then rest of dry mixture (swirl in).
Bake at 275° or 300° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: cheese roll
directions: Grate Cheddar cheese and soften cream cheese.
Put in other ingredients and mix with electric mixer. Chill overnight and then roll in small rolls; roll in paprika. Chill and slice. Serve on your favorite snack crackers.

title: apricot balls
directions: Cook 15 minutes.
Cool and roll in balls.
Roll balls in coconut or pecans.

title: parmesan chops
directions: Rinse chops and dip in flour--then in eggs--then in bread crumbs.
To a medium to hot frying pan with olive oil in it add the breaded chops and brown.
Place the browned chops in a baking dish and pour Italian tomato sauce over the chops.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over the sauce and bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.
Top with mozzarella cheese after baking while hot.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Add shortening and cut in with pastry blender.
Add unbeaten eggs and vanilla.
Mix well with hands.
Roll out very thin and cut any design.
Bake at 375° about 8 minutes.

title: leftover christmas turkey
directions: Mix turkey, green beans and soup.
Spread in oblong baking dish.
Spread dressing on top. Bake 20 to 25 minutes
or until well heated at 350°.

title: jason's jerky
directions: Mix all spices together.
Trim fat off meat.
Cut into thin strips.
Place meat and spice mix in Ziploc bag.
Let marinate overnight in refrigerator.
Place on broiler pan.
Bake at 200° in oven until tough and dry.
Store in refrigerator for long storage.

title: recipe for happiness
directions: Sprinkle generously with kindness and add plenty of faith. Mix well. Spread over a period of a lifetime and serve to everyone you meet.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: Mix pudding as directed; add 3/4 container Cool Whip and whip well.
Chill for about 1/2 hour.
Garnish with rest of Cool Whip and chocolate chips, if desired.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash, onion and pepper until tender and drain.
(Cook each separately.)
Layer squash, onion and bell pepper in a greased casserole dish; sprinkle with bacon and grated cheese. Beat egg and milk together and pour over casserole.
Top with crushed crackers.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 425° until bubbly and brown.

title: orange congealed salad
directions: Add boiling water to Jell-O and let cool.
Add undrained oranges and pineapple and mix in cream.
Stir well.
Let congeal.

title: belgian waffle or pancake topping
directions: Combine strawberries, sugar, orange juice and rind. Stir until sugar dissolves. Spoon onto waffles or pancakes and top with whipped topping. Makes 4 servings.

title: tuna salad
directions: Drain tuna and combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Serve with 6 to 8 lettuce leaves, potato chips and 1 can English peas.

title: chicken a la king
directions: Mix egg with flour and a little milk.
Mix with chicken and remaining ingredients.
Cook over low heat for about 5 minutes. Serve with rice or toast.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Saute onion, garlic, celery and green pepper in margarine until tender. Remove from heat and add soups and pimento.
Combine soup mixture, spaghetti and chicken.
Mix well.
Place 1/2 in a lightly greased 4-quart baking dish and top with 1/2 of the grated cheese.
Put another layer of spaghetti mixture and top with remaining cheese. Bake at 325° until cheese melts and all is bubbling hot (about 30 minutes).

title: swiss chicken
directions: You can also use American cheese.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Combine butter and peanut butter in a large mixing bowl; cream well.
Add sugar and beat well.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt; gradually add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beating well.
Spoon into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until cake tests done.
When cool, top with frosting and sprinkle peanuts.

title: oriental grilled chicken(lo-fat)
directions: In a bowl, combine all of the marinade ingredients and mix well.

Add the chicken and coat. Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours, turning occasionally. Grill chicken 6-inches away from the hot coals, 30 to 45 minutes. Brush pieces with marinade until the chicken is done and tender, but not dry.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Cook hamburger in skillet until brown; drain.
Place in casserole dish a layer of cabbage, a layer of hamburger.
Sprinkle pepper and onions on top of this.
Put 1/2 cup of rice over mixture.
Add rest of hamburger and a layer of cabbage.
Add the other 1/2 cup rice on mixture.
Add the can of mushroom soup. Bake for 1 hour covered with aluminum foil.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients well and bake in a well-greased pan at 325° for 1 hour or until done.

title: pretzel salad
directions: *Can substitute raspberries and raspberry Jell-O.

title: pudding chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix in pudding, flour, soda and salt.
Add chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: gumdrop fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add beaten egg.
Sift flour, cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves and salt together.
Add to flour mixture the gumdrops, nuts and white raisins.
Add applesauce alternately with flour and fruit mixture.
Dissolve soda in water.

title: chicken a la king
directions: Melt butter; blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Cook over a low heat until smooth and bubbly.
Remove from heat, stir in stock and milk.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Stir in gently balance of ingredients.
Serve on buttered rice, noodles or toast.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Place chicken in Dutch oven.
Cover with both cans of soup. Cook until chicken is done.
Shred chicken.
Tear biscuits into several pieces and lay on top.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.

title: frankie's marinated carrots
directions: Mix all ingredients except carrots and onion.
Pour mixture over carrots and onion and seal in airtight container. Refrigerate overnight.

title: easy drop danish
directions: Mix Bisquick, margarine and sugar until crumbly.
Stir in milk until dough forms; beat 15 strokes.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls about 2 inches apart on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Make a shallow well in center with floured thumb.
Fill with 1 teaspoon of preserves.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes or until golden.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt. Cream butter and add sugar, peanut butter and brown sugar, gradually creaming after each addition until light and fluffy.
Add egg and mix thoroughly.
Add flour mixture gradually beating after each addition until smooth.
Drop mixture one teaspoon at a time and about 2-inches apart onto ungreased baking sheet.
Press with fork until thin, making crisscross marks.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until cookie is brown.
Remove immediately from pan to cool.

title: grammie's blueberry muffins
directions: Sift first 2 ingredients together; set aside.
Beat egg whites stiff.
Cream shortening with sugar.
Add yolks.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Fold in egg whites.
Add vanilla and blueberries.
Drop in foil cupcake liners in muffin pan.
Sprinkle tops with sugar.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix together. Mixture will look like a salad.
Pour into greased and floured pan. Bake for 1 hour and 20 minutes at 325°.

title: calico ham casserole
directions: Melt the 1/2 cup butter in large pan over moderate heat.
Add onion.
Cook until onion is soft.
Add flour and mustard.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring occasionally.
Gradually add milk. Cook, stirring frequently, until mixture thickens.
Add salt and cheese.
Cook, stirring, until cheese melts.
Fold in ham and uncooked vegetables.
Spoon into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cool mixture, slightly at room temperature, then refrigerate, covered, overnight, allowing flavors to blend.
Let stand at room temperature 45 minutes before baking.
Sprinkle top with bread cubes and bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: scrapels
directions: Beat eggs in mixer until light yellow.
Add salt; mix.
Add water; continue mixing.
Add flour slowly, mixing out all lumps. Let batter sit so all foam goes away.
Grease 12-inch frying pan with Crisco and wax paper.
Over medium heat, add about 1/8 cup batter.
Cook until edges loosen from sides of pan.
Turn over and cook other side.
Don't let the crepe brown.
After all have cooled, mix cheese and a little pepper and sprinkle on crepe. Roll tight.
Can be frozen until ready to use.
Makes about 35. Thaw when ready to use.
Lay in soup bowl and pour hot chicken soup over scrapels.

title: cream puffs
directions: In saucepan, boil water.
Add oleo and salt; bring to a boil again.
Remove from heat. Add flour and beat vigorously. When smooth, add eggs, one at a time, and slightly beat.
Drop by tablespoon on baking sheet. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Lower temperature to 300° for 15 minutes. Fill when cooled with whipped cream or other filling.

title: dirt pudding
directions: You will need 9 x 6 x 2-inch pan.

title: impossible to fail coconut pie
directions: In large mixing bowl, beat together eggs, sugar, milk, vanilla, flour and oleo until all ingredients are well combined. Fold in coconut. Turn into 2 greased and floured 9-inch pie pans. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 40 minutes or until golden brown. Crust forms as pies bake.

title: dirt dessert
directions: You will also need 1 new medium flowerpot, 1 new small spade and 1 set artificial flowers.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Microwave caramels with water in 2-cup measure
or
medium
bowl
on High 1 1/2 minutes; stir. Continue to
microwave on High 30 seconds to 1 minute or until sauce
is smooth, stirring every 30 seconds.
Pour immediately over popcorn;
toss
until
well coated.
Spread onto greased cookie sheet
to
form
single layer.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes; break apart.

title: chicken rice, potato and corn soup
directions: Mix chicken, broth, water, onion, and all seasonings in a 5 quart soup pot. Simmer for 1 hour. Add potatoes and corn (I use a pint of frozen corn and 6 - 10 potatoes, depending on their size). Simmer for another hour and then add rice. I usually simmer this soup all day so the flavors mingle together well.

title: olive cheese ball
directions: Combine cream cheese with olives, onions and Tabasco.
Set cheese mixture in refrigerator about 15 minutes.
Shape cheese mixture into a ball.
Roll in chopped parsley.
Return to refrigerator.
Chill 15 to 20 minutes, or more, before serving.

title: seasoned pretzels
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place broken pretzels in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Pour oil over, tossing to coat all of the pretzels.
Sprinkle dry ingredients over pretzels and toss again.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes.
Stir 2 or 3 times during baking.

title: t.a.s. pretzels
directions: Mix dough and divide into approximately 8 pieces.
Roll each piece into long cylinder shapes about 16 inches long and 1 inch in diameter.
Form into pretzel shape (figure 8) and seal ends with wet fingers.
Float in very hot (not boiling) water.
Use a large open pan so you can fit 2 or 3 at a time.
Cook each side about 1 minute and remove to baking pan.
Let air dry, then place pan in 400° oven and bake 5 minutes.
Remove from oven and decrease temperature to 350°.
Coat pretzels with light egg wash (a mixture of egg and water).
Sprinkle pretzels with salt (Kosher salt works best) while dough is still moist, adding additional egg wash if necessary.
Return pan to oven and continue baking until pretzels are brown.

title: microwave chocolate gravy
directions: Mix together the cocoa, sugar, flour and salt.
Add milk. Place in microwave for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add the margarine.
Mix well. This will take the lumps out.

title: super salmon spread
directions: Drain and flake salmon.
Combine salmon, onion, lemon juice, liquid smoke, salt, and hot pepper sauce with cream cheese.
Blend together and chill for several hours.
Shape salmon mixture into a ball and roll in pecans.
Makes about 2 1/2 cups.
Serve as a spread on crackers.

title: texas hash
directions: Cook onions and peppers slowly in hot fat until onions are soft.
Add ground meat.
Cook until brown or it loses its red color.
Add tomatoes, rice, tomato sauce and seasonings.
Mix. Put in large greased casserole.
Cover and bake in 375° oven for 1 hour or until done.

title: parmesan chicken bites
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Bone and skin chicken.
Cut each half into 6 to 8 pieces.
Combine stuffing mix, cheese and parsley. Dip chicken pieces into butter and roll in stuffing mixture. Place in a single layer on a foil-lined baking sheet.
Bake 10 minutes or until tender. Serve hot or cold with picks.
Yields 3 to 4 dozen bites.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook broccoli according to package directions; cook Rice-A-Roni according to package directions.
Mix broccoli and rice together in casserole dish.
Melt cheese and milk over low heat.
Pour cheese over broccoli and rice and bake 7 to 10 minutes in 350° oven.

title: apple dip
directions: Beat
together	cream
cheese
and mayonnaise.	Stir in pineapple, dates and pecans.
Cover
and
refrigerate up to 48 hours.
Serve with tart red and green apples, unpeeled and cut into wedges for dipping.

title: corn scallop
directions: Heat corn and milk.
Gradually stir into eggs.
Add 1 1/2 cups cracker crumbs and onion.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole pan.
Pour melted butter over 1 cup crumbs.
Sprinkle over corn. Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: peach crisp
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Arrange peach slices in an 8-inch square baking dish.
Mix flour, brown sugar and cinnamon in large bowl. Cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in cereal.
Sprinkle over peaches.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve warm.
Makes 8 servings.

title: fruity spritz cookies
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter, sugar, and gelatin powder. Beat in egg and vanilla.
Combine flour and baking powder, gradually add to creamed mixture and mix well.
Using a cookie press fitted with the disk of your choice, press dough 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Decorate as desired with sugar and sprinkles.
Bake at 400 degrees for 6-8 minutes or until set (do not brown).
Remove to wire racks to cool.

title: sourdough bread
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients with starter.
Mix well and let sit out 8 to 12 hours or overnight.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown and drain hamburger.
Add 3/4 cup water and 1 package of Old El Paso seasoning mix.
Put in a long pan.

title: fried tortilla strips
directions: Cut the tortillas into thin strips.
Fry in 360° oil in a skillet or deep fryer until golden brown.
Drain.
Serve with your favorite soup.
May add sour cream and thinly sliced jalapeos to complete this tasty garnish.
Yield:
Variable.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Cook rice.
Saute celery and onion in oleo.
Mix soup and cheese in same pan and let cheese melt. Add water chestnuts, rice and broccoli.
Season to taste with salt, if desired.
Put in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: taco burgers
directions: Combine taco mix, catsup and milk.
Add ground beef.
Shape into burgers.
Cook on charcoal grill.
Serve with lettuce, cheese, tomato and taco sauce.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook macaroni al dente.
Mix rest of ingredients together using only 4 ounces Mozzarella, cubed.
Put mixture into a glass baking dish.
Put the sliced Mozzarella that is remaining on top of casserole.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes or until cheese turns slightly brown.

title: aloha cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed, using pineapple juice instead of water.
Bake on 17 x 11 1/2 x 1-inch cookie sheet or 9 x 13-inch pan, greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Combine pudding, cream cheese and 1 cup milk.
Blend together and spread over cake.
Spread drained pineapple and spread on cake. Frost with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with coconut and chopped nuts.

title: rice krispies squares
directions: Bring the Karo and sugar to a boil; add peanut butter and Rice Krispies.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt in double boiler the chips.
Spread over top.
Cut in squares.

title: african stew(international:  africa)
directions: Brown chicken and onions in oil until completely done, stirring frequently.
Drain chicken.
Retain 2 tablespoons of oil.
Place chicken in oil and remaining ingredients, except flour, in large pot.
Cover the pot and simmer over medium heat for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: ranchero raised biscuits
directions: Combine raisins, milk, sugar, salt, shortening and cornmeal in bowl.
Dissolve yeast in warm water and add to mixture.
Add egg and flour.
Blend well.
Drop by spoonfuls into a well-greased 11-inch oblong baking pan.
Let rise 45 minutes or until doubled in size.
Bake in a preheated oven at 400° for about 20 minutes. Serve hot with butter or jam.

title: german pancakes(breakfast meal)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease and flour 2 pie plates.
Put eggs, granulated sugar, salt, flour, milk and butter in blender and mix until smooth.
Pour even amount in each pie plate.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Turn oven down to 350° and bake another 10 minutes.
Cut in wedges.
Squeeze lemon juice on pancake and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: spinach pie
directions: Thaw spinach.
Beat eggs and add flour, a teaspoon at a time. Add spinach, cheese and cottage cheese, mixing well.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Grease shallow baking dish well with butter. Add mixture, bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour or less.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops; put in casserole dish.
Take drippings and pour on top with mushroom soup and water.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: dump salad
directions: Mix together and refrigerate.

title: pecan kisses
directions: Beat egg white until it stands in soft peaks.
Gradually add sifted sugar and vanilla.
Beat until mixed well.
Next, fold in pecans, making sure each one is covered well.
Place each Pecan Kiss on a greased cookie sheet, about 1-inch apart.
Bake at 250° for 30 minutes.
Cut oven off, leave in oven until cool.

title: pasta picnic salad
directions: Cook tortellini according to package directions; drain and toss in a large bowl with 1 1/2 teaspoons olive oil (makes about 3 cups).
Cool, then add tuna, peas and cheese; set aside.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a 9 inch unbaked pie shell. Bake at 325° for about 50 - 55 minutes.
Delicious!

title: blackberry preserves
directions: With this recipe one does not use Sure-Jell, just fruit and sugar.
To keep berries whole, place berries in pan with sugar on top.
Don't stir unless you want berries to cook apart.
With this recipe, cook about 2 hours.
Boil until syrupy.
To test, place a small amount on spoon and allow to cool.
If it runs, keep testing every 10 minutes.
When thick, can as usual.

title: swiss ham ring around
directions: Combine butter, parsley, onion, mustard and lemon juice. Blend well. Add cheese, broccoli and ham.
Mix lightly and set aside.
Separate dough into 8 triangles.
Arrange on greased sheet into a circle with bases overlapping, points facing out.
Spoon 1/3 cup mixture onto each triangle.
Fold points over and tuck under bases at center. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes until golden brown.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Put sugar and oil in mixer.
Mix at medium speed.
Add 4 eggs and mix well.
Add water and pumpkin and mix well.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour in 3 greased loaf pans and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Let cool before removing from pan.

title: monadnock blueberry cake
directions: Mix altogether, then sprinkle top with sugar before baking. Bake at 350° to 400° for 35 minutes.

title: chicken and noodles
directions: Mix eggs, salt and water in a large bowl.
Add flour and mix with a slotted spoon.
Turn out on well floured board.
Knead lightly to mix in last of flour (add more flour if needed). Divide dough into 2 balls.
Roll each ball into a large circle (like pie crust).
Cover with a light cloth and allow to dry, 4 to 6 hours.
If dough is manageable, roll up like jelly roll and slice into 1/4-inch strips.
Shake out on board and continue drying (2 to 3 hours).

title: pepperoni dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Soften cream cheese in microwave.
Mix all ingredients together, except nuts.
Place in pie plate. Sprinkle nuts on top to cover.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Serve with crackers or bread.

title: hot dog and spaghetti sauce
directions: Gives it a better flavor.

title: hot pecan chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Top with potato chips the last 5 minutes.
Makes 6 generous servings.

title: church supper slaw dressing
directions: Mix ingredients and pour over slaw mixture.
(Can be used in deviled eggs and potato salad.)

title: ambrosia
directions: Drain fruit.
Add whipping cream, marshmallows, sour cream and coconut.
Mix well.
Store in refrigerator.
Stir well before serving.
The coconut can be colored with food coloring for different holidays.

title: peanut butter jelly cookies
directions: Cream together.
Place 1 teaspoon of dough rolled into ball on cookie sheet.
Press a hole in center of imprint fork.
Place jelly if desired.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 325°.

title: fudge-nut brownies
directions: About 2 1/2 hours before serving or early in the day:

title: sutlach(turkish rice pudding)
directions: Precook rice; cool.
In saucepan, mix milk, sugar and lemon peel.
Heat until almost boiling.
Slowly add the cornstarch and milk mix ture and continue to cook and stir until thickened. Remove from heat.
Add beaten egg yolk, vanilla and rice. Mix well and refrigerate.

title: fillets in wine sauce
directions: Sprinkle both sides of fish fillets with salt and pepper. Place fillets in single layer in baking dish.
Arrange tomatoes over top of fillets.
Blend flour into butter and add milk; stir in white wine, add parsley and basil.
Cook until smooth and thick.
Pour sauce over the tomatoes and fish.
Bake at 350° about 25 to 30 minutes, until fish flakes easily with a fork.
Sprinkle with parsley.

title: spiced tomato aspic
directions: Pour 1 cup of tomato juice into medium saucepan; sprinkle with gelatin.
Heat slowly until gelatin dissolves.
Remove from heat; add seasonings and remaining tomato juice.
Pour into 6 individual salad molds or 1 large salad mold.
Chill until set.
Unmold on lettuce; garnish with parsley.
Can add chopped cucumber and onion (if desired) and omit onion powder.

title: margaret's banana pudding cake
directions: Add box of cooked vanilla pudding to cake mix in large mixing bowl and mix as box says, using the butter recipe.
Put cake in oven at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until done.
Let cake cool.

title: forty clove chicken
directions: Place chicken in baking pan; sprinkle ingredients over chicken.
Squeeze lemon.
Pour over chicken.
Cut and sprinkle lemon rind over chicken.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Uncover.
Bake another 15 minutes to brown.

title: kosher dill pickles
directions: Fit the cukes tightly into the glass jar.
Add all other ingredients; fill with cold water.
Seal tight with tape.
Let stand in cellar for 7 days.
Repack into smaller jars if desired. Use same juice and refrigerate.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all together in loaf pan.
Cook, uncovered, in a 350° oven for about 1 hour or done.

title: new orleans pecan pie
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar and flour.
Add syrup and beat well.
Add eggs, vanilla and salt and beat well again.
Add pecans.
Place in unbaked 9-inch pie shell for 15 minutes at 400°, then 30 minutes at 325°.
Yields one 9-inch pie.

title: overnight lasagna
directions: Coat wings with sauce and bake at 350° for 30 or 40 minutes.

title: zesty pasta salad - original
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Drain thoroughly under cold water.
Drain well.
In large bowl, combine pasta and all diced ingredients and crumbled bacon/Prosciutto.
Add salt and pepper to taste and toss with 1/2 cup dressing.
Refrigerate.

title: sour cream corn pancakes
directions: On waxed paper, combine flour, baking powder and salt.
In medium bowl with wire whisk, mix milk, sour cream, eggs and melted margarine or butter until blended.
Whisk in dry ingredients just until mixed.
Stir in corn.
In nonstick 12-inch skillet, heat 1 teaspoon oil over medium heat.
Drop batter by 1/3 cups into skillet, making a few pancakes at a time.
Cook 5 to 7 minutes until tops are bubbly and edges look dry.
Turn pancakes over and cook 3 to 5 minutes, until undersides are golden.
Transfer pancakes to platter; keep warm.
Repeat with remaining batter, using more oil if necessary.
Makes about twelve 4-inch pancakes. Prep: 15 minutes.
Cook:
about 10 minutes per batch.

title: creamy rice pudding
directions: Scald milk in top of double boiler.
Add other ingredients slowly, stirring constantly.
Cook covered over hot water until rice has absorbed the milk, about 1 1/4 hours, stirring frequently.
Serve warm with cream.

title: no-bake chocolate cookies
directions: Put sugar, milk, margarine, cocoa and salt in a large saucepan and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and stir in the oats, vanilla, nuts and coconut.
Drop from teaspoon onto waxed paper. Makes 48 cookies.

title: fluffy rolls
directions: Mix milk, sugar, salt, soda and eggs.
Add oil.
Mix yeast into 2 cups flour and blend well with other ingredients.
Add rest of flour, more or less as needed.
Bake at 350°.

title: lead bellies
directions: Bake baking potato until well done.
(Recommend baking without foil.)
Cut open and fluff potato by pushing it up.
Add butter. Put on a combination of thinly sliced turkey, ham, beef or bacon. Next add sauteed onion and green pepper. Top with slice of Swiss cheese.
Broil until cheese melts.

title: tex-mex rice
directions: In large saucepan over low heat, cook rice, onion and garlic in oil until the rice is lightly browned, stirring frequently. Stir in hot chicken broth, picante sauce and carrot.
Cover and simmer until all liquid is absorbed, about 20 minutes.

title: chocolate fudge icing
directions: Blend butter, vanilla and cocoa in large mixing bowl. Slowly add milk and powdered sugar alternately. Beat until well blended.

title: aunt karen's black forest pie
directions: Put first 5 ingredients in saucepan, cook to boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from stove, add eggs, fold in 1/2 can cherry pie filling.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Chill 1 hour.
Add 2 cups Cool Whip.
Top with the rest of the cherries.
Chill 30 minutes more before serving.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Place cut up chicken in a large boiler.
Cover with water. Bring to a boil.
Let boil over medium heat until done, about 45 minutes.
Take chicken out of broth; let chicken cool.
Cook rice in chicken broth.
Will probably not need all the broth.
Should pour out excess before cooking rice.
When chicken has cooled, remove skin from chicken.
Debone chicken.
Cut chicken into small pieces.
Place in a separate pot with cream of mushroom soup and 3/4 can of water.
Bring to a boil and let simmer a few minutes. Serve rice with butter and put a serving of chicken on top.
It is delicious!

title: carter hill macaroni and cheese
directions: Stir until the macaroni is well coated and add 1 1/2 to 2 cups hot water or milk and one egg.
Stir enough to blend the egg through the mixture.
Cook at low temperature, 250°, to prevent curling.
Sprinkle paprika on top.

title: hash brown potatoes
directions: Place potatoes, salt and pepper in nonstick skillet.
Cook for approximately 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat and add onions, if desired.
Cook potatoes about 30 minutes or until tender.
Spray occasionally with nonstick spray if necessary to keep potatoes from sticking to skillet.
Fold like an omelet and serve.
Makes 4 servings.

title: tuna burgers
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Shape into patties and fry in enough oil to cover bottom of pan until brown on both sides.

title: easy marshmallow five layer bars
directions: Preparation Time: 10 minutes plus cooling.
Cooking Time: 25 minutes.

title: frozen peanut butter pie
directions: Cream the cheese until smooth.
Add milk, powdered sugar and peanut butter.
Stir until well mixed.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into pie shells and freeze.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni as directed and drain.
Place macaroni in a large casserole pan.
Add margarine and cheese.
Crumble crackers on top to cover the macaroni.
Add milk over crackers, pouring slowly.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until crackers are brown.

title: priceless dumplings
directions: Beat
egg
lightly.
Add
all
other ingredients.
Stir until smooth.
Drop by spoonfuls into the boiling broth.	Cook 10 minutes.
These
can be cooked without turning them.
They can be reheated and are light as a feather.

title: chicken delight
directions: Cube 2 slices of bread. Put into a 2-quart dish.
Mix chicken, onion, celery, mayonnaise and green pepper.
Spoon over bread. Trim crusts from the remaining 4 slices of bread.
Place on top of chicken.
Beat eggs; add milk and seasonings.
Pour over bread. Cover and chill overnight.
Spoon soup over casserole in morning. Bake at 325° uncovered for 1 hour.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and bake 20 minutes longer.

title: chicken deluxe
directions: Saute onion and celery.
Mix all ingredients.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: beef marsala
directions: Cut steak into 4-inch pieces.
In small bowl, beat egg with milk.
In another bowl, combine bread crumbs, Parmesan, salt and pepper.
Dip meat in egg mix, then in bread crumb mix.
In large skillet over medium-high heat, melt 2 tablespoons margarine.
Cook garlic and all the meat until lightly browned, using 1/2 cup butter in all.
Remove meat from pan.
In cup, mix water and flour.
Melt remaining butter in skillet.
Add water mixture, Marsala wine, parsley and bouillon.
Cook, stirring, until thickened.
Pour over meat.

title: pecan coconut bars
directions: Cream butter with 1/2 cup brown sugar.
Add 1 cup sifted flour gradually and mix until smooth.
Press and flatten to cover the bottom of an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Beat eggs until light and fluffy.
Add 1 cup brown sugar, vanilla, baking powder, 2 tablespoons flour and salt.
Stir in pecans and coconut.
Spread over baked pastry and return to oven.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes longer or until topping is golden brown.
Cool.

title: japanese pie
directions: Mix sugar, margarine and eggs together.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for about 55 minutes.
Cool until jelled.

title: picnic slaw
directions: In a bowl, combine cabbage, carrots, bacon and onions.
In a jar with tight fitting lid, mix vinegar, oil, sugar and salt; shake well.
Just before serving, pour dressing over cabbage mixture and toss.
Makes 12 to 16 servings.

title: oyster cracker snacks
directions: Mix oil and dry ingredients well.
Place crackers in roaster pan.
Stir crackers while gradually adding oil mixture.
Stir every 15 minutes for 2 hours.
Place in glass containers and store.
Will stay good for a long time.

title: oregano chicken
directions: The day before cooking, place chicken in large freezer bag. Combine oil, lemon juice, garlic, salt, oregano and pepper; pour over chicken.
Tie bag shut and turn bag several times to coat chicken with marinade.
Refrigerate for 24 hours, turning bag occasionally.

title: lentil and brown rice soup
directions: In heavy Dutch oven or stock pot, combine all but salt, pepper and vinegar.
Bring to a boil and simmer, covered, stirring occasionally, 45 minutes to an hour (until lentils and rice are tender).
Discard bay leaf.
Stir in salt and pepper and vinegar to taste.
This is a thick soup that will thicken further upon standing.
It may be thinned, if desired, with additional hot water or vegetable juice.
Serve with a green salad and crusty French bread for a tasty, filling meal.
Keeps well in freezer.

title: hawaiian pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into crust.
Chill until firm.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together butter, sugars, egg and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Stir into creamed mixture.
Add chocolate chips and nuts.
Mix well.
Drop from a teaspoon about 2 inches apart on lightly greased baking sheets. Bake at 375° about 10 minutes.
Makes about 3 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: fried matzoh
directions: *Nyafat can be substituted for oil.

title: potato salad stack-up
directions: Combine potatoes and peas.
Toss tuna with dill weed.
Layer lettuce, potato mixture, tomatoes, tuna mixture and cucumbers in 3 1/2-quart salad bowl.
Top with 1 1/2 cups Dill Sauce.
Cover and chill.
Serve with remaining Dill Sauce.

title: frosty apple shake
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender or mixer.
Mix until frothy.

title: caramel pie
directions: Scald milk with salt, then add remainder of ingredients.
Cook in double boiler.
Brown 1/4 of the sugar before adding mixture.

title: applesauce muffins
directions: Mix all together (applesauce adds moisture, do not add milk or water).
Batter will be medium consistency.
Bake at 350° until golden.

title: easy company chicken
directions: Rinse
chicken
well.
Mix sour cream and Dijon mustard until well
blended.
Batter
chicken
pieces.
Roll battered chicken in Italian bread crumbs.
Place in baking dish (uncovered) for approximately 20 minutes, or until chicken is brown. Turn and bake for 15 more minutes.

title: cranberry sauce
directions: Drain 1 can of	pineapple well ahead.
Add orange juice to pineapple juice to make 2 cups liquid.
Pour in cranberries and sugar and cook.
While
hot,
pour over jello.
When cool, add pineapple, celery, apples and nuts.
Mold.

title: turkey-spaghetti bake
directions: Combine spaghetti, turkey and pimiento.
In a saucepan, combine soup, milk and cheese; heat and stir until the cheese melts.
Add to turkey mixture; mix well.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole; top with chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake at 350° in greased loaf pan for 45 minutes or until done.

title: goulash
directions: Boil macaroni in water until soft.
Brown hamburger, onion and pepper; drain.
Add taco seasoning.
Drain water from macaroni. Mix together.
Add tomato juice and heat until heated through.

title: barbecued ribs
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Place ribs in baking pan, meaty side up. On each piece, place slice of onion and lemon.
Roast for 30 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over ribs. Reduce heat to 350° and bake 1 1/2 hours.
Baste 2 to 3 times. Serves 4.

title: oven roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. In a large plastic bag, add all ingredients. Close bag and shake until potatoes are evenly coated. In a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, arrange potatoes. Bake, uncovered, stirring occasionally 40 minutes or until potatoes are tender and golden brown. Makes 4 servings.

title: cherry salad
directions: Fold ingredients together right before serving (out of respect to the banana).
Serve in a clean bowl.
For individual portions, serve on lettuce leaves and sprinkle with chopped nuts.

title: 7-layer tofu salad
directions: Layer ingredients in the order given.

title: roberta's company casserole
directions: Combine the first six ingredients and shape into balls.
Brown and cook, covered, for 10 minutes.
Place in a 2 1/2-quart casserole (about 2 inches deep).
Combine soups, milk and water. Heat until steaming.
Pour over meatballs.
Top with biscuits.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix the cornstarch, sugar, salt and egg yolks with 1/2 cup of the milk.
Heat remaining 2 cups to boiling.
Add the sugar mixture and cook until thick.
Add coconut and vanilla.
Pour in pie shell.
Whip the three egg whites, adding 6 tablespoons sugar. Bake at 425° for 5 minutes or until brown.

title: coconut cake
directions: Beat sugar and oil together.
Add eggs; mix well.
Add milk and flour; stir until mixed, then add coconut.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour in cake batter; bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
When cake is done, leave in pan.
Mix the last 4 ingredients; boil for 1 minute.
As soon as cake is removed from oven, punch holes all over top with a fork and pour this boiling mixture over it.

title: pumpkin cake bars
directions: Mix eggs, pumpkin, sugar, salt, ginger, cinnamon and cloves together; pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix on top.
Drizzle melted butter over mix; spread chopped nuts over all.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
(Cover with foil loosely to keep from browning too soon the first half of cooking time.)
Cut into squares.
Serve topped with whipped cream.
Makes 24 bars.

title: layered peach delight
directions: Mix flour, margarine and pecans together.
Press in a 9 x 13 pan.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: pasta shells
directions: Boil spinach and let cool.
Add the 2 cheeses and garlic salt. Boil shells according to package directions.
Put 2 teaspoons of mixture into each shell.
Put 1/4 of sauce in bottom of baking dish.
Place filled shells in pan and pour sauce over all.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Cover with foil and bake 30 minutes at 300°.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream eggs, sugar, oil and margarine.
Add salt, soda, cream of tartar and vanilla.
Slowly add flour a little at a time while you are mixing.
Drop by teaspoonfuls.
Bake at 350 degrees for about 12-13 minutes or until they are light brown around the edge.

title: white sauce(for 5 people)
directions: Melt Crisco with flour and salt. Add milk gradually and stir until thick.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Bake cookie mix on a pizza pan as crust.
Mix cream cheese and marshmallow cream together.
Spread on crust.
Arrange various fruit in circles in a colorful design.
Serve.

title: oven brown potatoes
directions: Put butter in baking pan large enough to hold potatoes and put into 350° oven to melt.
Add potatoes and stir to coat with the butter.
Salt and pepper potatoes and bake for one hour until they are golden and tender.

title: "philly" sugars
directions: Cream the cream cheese, butter and sugar.
Add vanilla and flour; blend well.
Cover bowl and chill overnight.
Shape into small balls.
Roll in sugar.
Flatten; cook 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Tangy different taste for dainty white cookies.

title: cherry delight
directions: Melt margarine and work flour and nuts into same.
Press in 9 3/4-inch baking dish and bake until brown.
Mix together the next 3 ingredients with large spoon.
Mix until smooth.
Pour over browned crust.
Add 2 cans of cherry pie filling and spread over top.
Chill for about 1 hour.
Eat and enjoy.

title: marinated beef
directions: Combine all ingredients in one bowl.
Cut 3 to 4 pound beef roast into 1/4 to 1/2-inch slices or use thin sliced steaks.
Pour marinade over meat and work in with hands.
Marinate as long as desired (from 1 hour to overnight).
Cook.
Grilling is best method.

title: spinach cheese casserole
directions: Beat the eggs and flour until smooth.
Mix the other ingredients.
Bake uncovered in a casserole dish 1 hour at 350°. Let stand a few minutes before serving.

title: fudge nougats
directions: In saucepan, add butter, sugar and milk. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Boil 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Take off heat. Stir in chocolate morsels, flour, graham crackers, nuts and vanilla.
Spread in well buttered 12 x 8 or 9 x 9-inch pan. If desired, top with walnut halves. Cut in squares. For richer chocolate flavor, add 1/4 cup cocoa.

title: honey
directions: Wash blossoms; pick off petals.
Add all ingredients and bring to a boil for 1 1/2 minutes.
Strain.
Put into glass jars.

title: working man's soup
directions: Brown onion and drain.
Put in other ingredients.
Cook for 30 minutes.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Mix zucchini, onion and salt; let stand overnight.
In morning, rinse in cold water and drain well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook 20 minutes at boiling point, stirring often. Put in jars and seal.

title: traditional pumpkin pie(makes 9 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In large mixer bowl, combine all ingredients except pastry shell; mix well.
Pour into pastry shell. Bake 15 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 350°; bake 35 to 40 minutes longer or until knife inserted 1 inch from edge comes out clean.
Cool.
Garnish as desired.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Prep time:
10 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Spray bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch glass dish with Pam or Baker's Joy.
Spread pineapple in bottom of dish.
Layer blueberries on pineapple.
Sprinkle sugar on blueberries.
Spread dry cake mix over berries; sprinkle nuts on top of mix.
Drizzle margarine over nuts.
Cook in oven at 350° for 1 hour.
Make slits through cake at 15-minute intervals.

title: stained glass cookies
directions: Melt the chocolate chips and margarine over low heat or in a double boiler until melted well.
Remove from stove.
Put nuts and marshmallows in large bowl.
Pour chocolate mixture over nuts and marshmallows; mix well.
Have 3 (24-inch long) pieces of waxed paper laid out.
Sprinkle papers with finely shredded coconut to all but 2-inches of edges.
Divide mixture into thirds.
Form into rolls and shape.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
Slice 1/4-inch thick.

title: freezer slaw
directions: Chop cabbage and other vegetables.
Mix well with other ingredients.
Seal, label and freeze.
Mix vinegar, salt and sugar together first.
Pour over vegetables.

title: fresh strawberry cake
directions: Add all cake ingredients to cake mix and bake at 350° in three 8-inch round pans until done.

title: nacho dip
directions: Melt in a crock-pot.

title: corn casserole
directions: Drain corn and chili peppers; put in casserole dish.
Melt together cream cheese, butter and milk.
Pour over corn and chili peppers.
Bake at 350° until bubbles over.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Brown onion in butter; add broccoli, right from frozen package to skillet.
