Brown just enough to get separated.
Add soup, mushrooms, almonds, cheese and spices.
Pour into baking dish; cover with bread crumbs.
Put some more almonds on top, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, until bubbly.

title: plantation hot sauce
directions: Blend molasses and prepared mustard.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Heat to boiling.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Brown pepper, celery and onion in butter.
Add soup, water, mushrooms and olives. Add cooked chicken and noodles, then 1/2 the grated cheese.
Put into casserole dish and top with more grated cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 300° until cheese is melted.

title: maple divinity
directions: Boil the syrup without stirring until it reaches 260° on a candy thermometer.
Remove the syrup from the heat.
Beat the egg white and salt until it forms very stiff peaks.
Slowly pour the syrup over the egg white while beating the mixture at the highest speed of an electric mixer.
Continue beating until the mixture forms soft peaks.
Stir in the nuts.
Drop by teaspoons on waxed paper.

title: cran-raspberry and sour cream mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water. Stir in cranberry sauce until dissolved; add pineapple. Chill until partially set. Pour half of mixture into 6 1/2-cup ring mold. Chill until almost firm. Let remaining jello stand at room temperature. Stir sour cream and spread over mixture. Gently pour the rest of mixture over cream. Chill overnight or several hours.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Combine whole kernel corn and 3/4 cup milk or cream-style corn and 1/2 cup milk.
Add bread or cracker crumbs, onion, green pepper and seasonings.
Pour into buttered casserole.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.
May be baked in the microwave or bake until done.

title: mother's refrigerator potato rolls deluxe
directions: Sprinkle yeast in lukewarm water in large bowl.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes until thoroughly dissolved.
Stir up and stir in next 4 ingredients.
Add cold water, salt and enough flour to make a stiff dough.
Grease dough with salad oil and cover with waxed paper and tea towel.	Store in refrigerator 24 hours.
Turn out desired amount onto lightly floured board.	Return rest to refrigerator, will keep 2 to 3 days.
Shape as desired (cloverleaf, parkerhouse, etc.) and place in buttered pan.
Brush tops with salad oil and cover with towel.
Let rise in warm place (80° to 85°) until double in bulk.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly browned and done.
Makes 3 to 5 dozen.
Delicious!

title: baked potato salad
directions: Mix ingredients in bowl and pour into baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until golden brown.
Top with sliced olives and bacon.

title: daddy's catfish stew
directions: Lay bacon in the bottom of a heavy Dutch oven.
Let brown a little to get the grease out.
Leave bacon and layer sliced potatoes, sliced onions, catfish fillets, salt and pepper.
Layer until the pot is full.
Don't forget to salt after each layer.

title: banana huckleberry muffins
directions: Combine sugar and margarine or butter.
Cream together.
Add the eggs and milk (to sour milk, add 1 capful of vinegar to milk). Add bananas and mix well.
Mix the dry ingredients together. Combine with the banana mixture.
Stir the huckleberries in last. Grease muffin tins before filling.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: millionaire pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into cooked pie shells. Store in refrigerator.

title: fried pies
directions: Make biscuit dough with plain flour, a little salt and less shortening than usual for biscuits.
Roll out into circles and add dried fruit, making "moon" shaped pies, pressing top of dough to bottom with fork dipped in flour.

title: low-fat crabcakes
directions: Combine crabmeat, 1/2 cup of the bread crumbs, egg substitute, mayonnaise and rest of ingredients.
Shape into 8 patties.
Place other 1/2 cup bread crumbs in a shallow bowl.
Dip each patty into crumbs to coat.
Refrigerate 30 minutes.
In large skillet coated with nonstick spray, cook patties over medium heat until browned on both sides.

title: pink salad
directions: Heat pineapple and jello.
Whip a can of chilled milk with mixer.
Then fold pineapple and jello into whipped cream, then put in refrigerator and chill.

title: hot pineapple salad
directions: Drain pineapple and save 3 tablespoons juice.
Combine sugar and flour and stir in pineapple juice.
Add cheese and pineapple; mix well.
Pour into 1-quart greased casserole dish.
Combine melted oleo and crumbs; sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: six week bran muffins
directions: Mix cereal and dry ingredients. Blend remaining ingredients and add to dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Store in covered container in the refrigerator until needed.
Batter keeps up to 6 weeks. When ready to bake, spoon batter into greased pans, filling 2/3 full. Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: turkey or chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except half of the noodles.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes, covered.
Add the other half of the noodles to the top; cook for 10 minutes, uncovered.
Bake in glass Pyrex in a pan of water.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl with your hands.
Roll into 1 inch balls.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: squash souffle
directions: Add egg yolks, flour, milk and butter to cooked squash.
Fold in beaten whites.
Put in greased mold and cook in pan of water about 30 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top.

title: chicken spectacular
directions: Mix and top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25-30 minutes.

title: weight watcher pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into pie plate that has been sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° until knife inserted halfway between the center of pie comes out clean.
Cut pie into eighths; each piece equals 1/4 P, 1/3 B and 16 calories.

title: the ultimate chocolate chip cookie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine Crisco, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in a large bowl.
Beat at medium speed of electric mixer until creamy.
Beat egg into creamed mixture.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda and mix into creamed mixture until just blended. Stir in chocolate chips and pecan pieces.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix together and store in closed container.
To use, dissolve 1/3 cup of mix in a mug of hot water.

title: melon salad
directions: Make the dressing by mixing in medium bowl the lime juice, tangerine juice and vanilla.
Cut melon into pieces or use a melon baller to ball.
Add grapes.
Add the dressing and toss gently. Refrigerate about 2 hours.

title: peanut butter-ups
directions: Mix butter and peanut butter in 2-quart bowl.
Microwave on High (100%) for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes or until melted.
Blend well. Mix in crumbs and sugar until very stiff.
Press firmly in buttered 12 x 8-inch or 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Wash berries, add sugar and apples (chopped).
Cover well with water.
Cook until begins to thicken.
Add juice and grated rind of orange.
If not thick enough when cool you may cook some more over low heat, stir occasionally.
This will keep indefinitely in refrigerator.

title: lasagne
directions: Saute onions and mushrooms.
Add meat, brown and drain. Add seasonings to taste.
Stir, add tomatoes and tomato sauce. Simmer until meat is done.
Follow directions to cook lasagne. Layer lasagne,
meat
mixture
and
cheeses
in
baking
dish, topping off with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Process strawberries through blender.
Pour lemonade into punch bowl and stir in strawberries.
Add chilled ginger ale and stir well.
It would be nice to make an ice ring out of another bottle of ginger ale.

title: vichyssoise
directions: Thoroughly rinse leeks to remove sand.
Trim green portion off leeks.
Starting 1/4 inch from root cut in quarters.
Dice onion and peel and dice potatoes.
Melt butter in saucepan and simmer leeks and onions until limp.
Add stock and potatoes.
Add salt, pepper and garlic powder and simmer until potatoes are tender. Pass through food mill.
Return to saucepan.
Add half and half and milk.
Heat almost to the boiling point.
Stir often.

title: roast venison and gravy
directions: Brown meat in pan sprayed with cooking spray.
Place meat in crock-pot.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in boiling water.
Add onion salt and mix well.
Pour over meat.
Add enough water to cover. Cook on high for 6 to 8 hours or slow for 10 to 12 hours.
Remove meat.
Wrap in foil.
Vent for heat to escape.
(Meat will dry and harden if not wrapped.) Reserve 2 cups broth.
Mix cornstarch with cold water.
Mix with broth; heat until thick.
Season to taste. Serve with sliced venison.

title: smoked sausage stew
directions: Preboil smoked sausage to remove a bit of the excess fat and then cut into bite size pieces.
Place sausage pieces in a saucepan.
Fill with water just to cover meat.
Add all other ingredients, except potatoes.
Cook for 1/2 hour, stirring occasionally.
Add potatoes and cook until soft.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Serve with bread.

title: 5 spice chinese chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375F.
Wash chicken under cold water, drain well.
In a large bowl combine soy sauce, onions, garlic and ginger, mix well.
Add chicken in mixture, make sure chicken gets coated well.
Marinate chicken 30-45 minutes.
Place chicken in lightly greased baking dish.
Combine cinnamon, cloves, and pepper, mix well and sprinkle over chicken.
Bake 30 minutes covered, remove cover and bake an additional 10-15 minutes or until chicken is done.

title: brown rice pilaf
directions: Saute almonds in 1 tablespoon butter or margarine until golden brown.
Remove and set aside.

title: swiss chicken
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Place cheese over chicken.
Pour soup over cheese.
Sprinkle stuffing over cheese.
Pour butter over stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with rice pilaf.

title: cream cheese pretzel dip
directions: Whip until creamy. Serve with pretzels.

title: mexican grits casserole (second)
directions: Cook grits, salt and water for 10 minutes.
Cool 1/2 hour. Fold all remaining ingredients into grits.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Bake, uncovered, 1 hour at 350°.
Let set for 20 minutes before serving.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Saut bacon or breakfast sausage and drain. Cover bottom of 9 x 13 casserole with bread cubes. Beat eggs with milk, salt to taste and mustard. Layer sausage over bread, then cheese and pour egg mixture over all. Refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: cabbage hamburger casserole
directions: Layer cabbage and meat.
Cover with soup.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy brownies
directions: Mix all together and bake in a greased 8 x 8-inch pan for 25 minutes in 350° oven.

title: shortbread cookies
directions: Cream softened butter and confectioners sugar together until light. Sift flour and salt together and add to butter/sugar mixture. Add vanilla and blend thoroughly. Gather dough in a bowl; wrap in wax paper and chill 4 to 6 hours. Roll out chilled dough to 5/8-inch thickness. Cut out cookies (hearts or shamrocks are nice). Sprinkle tops with granulated white or colored sugar. Place cutout cookies on ungreased cookie sheet and refrigerate for 45 minutes.

title: vegetable medley
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: seven-up cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes. Use oblong cake pan with cover.

title: grilled shrimp
directions: Take each piece of shrimp and wrap in lean bacon and secure with a toothpick.
Once all shrimp are wrapped, melt butter and stir in Creole seasoning.
When coals on the grill have turned gray, place shrimp onto a sheet of foil.
Wrap shrimp in foil as if making a pocket to hold in juices and steam.
Baste shrimp through out time on grill with butter and seasoning.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Combine 1/2 of the cheese, onion and potatoes in a baking dish, set aside.
Mix the rest of the ingredients except the cheese.
Pour mixture over potatoes.
Top with the rest of the cheese.
Bake on 350 until potatoes are soft.

title: lo-cal banana nut bread
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Combine oil, eggs, sweetener and vanilla.
Add to flour mixture and stir only until flour is moistened.
Fold in mashed bananas and pecans. Place in a greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.
Makes 1 loaf, 12 slices.
One slice equals 135 calories.

title: almond torte
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease 2 (8-inch) round layer pans. Line both with wax paper.

title: squash relish
directions: Use food chopper to chop raw vegetables.
Sprinkle salt over vegetables and let stand overnight.
Next morning, drain well. Combine remaining ingredients in large, heavy pot.
Boil for 15 minutes.
Put in jars and seal.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown meat in butter, remove.
Saute onions in butter.
Return meat to butter and onions.
Add bouillon and simmer about 15 minutes.
Put cornstarch in sour cream and fold into beef mixture. Serve on hot noodles or rice.

title: sugar-free fresh strawberry pie
directions: Mix cornstarch and apple juice.
Cook ingredients until mixture begins to clear, stirring frequently.
Stir in 1 pint of crushed strawberries, flavoring and food coloring.
Line bottom of pie shell with whole strawberries.
Pour crushed strawberry thickened mixture over them.
Refrigerate.

title: cream wafers
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly.
Chill 1 hour.
Roll out 1/8-inch thick.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch rounds.
Coat both sides of cookies in white sugar.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Prick with fork 4 times per cookie.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 10 minutes until slightly puffy, but not brown.
Put 2 cookies together with Creamy Butter Filling.

title: pork chop skillet dinner
directions: Brown pork chops in a small amount of fat in skillet.
Remove chops and pour off most excess fat.
Place onion in skillet and saute until clear; then add washed, raw rice, beef consomme or bouillon and water.
Place pork chops on top of rice mixture, cover and simmer about 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Can be baked in 350° oven 1 hour.
Add more water if needed.
Salt and pepper to taste. Serves 4.

title: baked bean casserole
directions: Saute hamburg with onions.
Cook and crumble bacon.
Mix all ingredients; cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: beef dip
directions: Mix cream cheese (room temperature) with all other ingredients. Serve with veggies and crackers.

title: cold creamed borscht
directions: Cook beets until tender.
Peel and slice beets.
In large pot, put water, cooked beets, parsley, onion and salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer about 1 hour.
Toward end of cooking time, add vinegar and lemon juice.
Remove the onion.
Sieve out the vegetables.
Then process the vegies in a blender with some of the liquid.
Add sour cream.
Combine sour cream and veggies with the rest of the liquid and refrigerate overnight.
Serve cold with small hot new potatoes placed in the bowl of soup and with a dollop of sour cream on top.
Delicious!
Great for a guest luncheon!

title: honey cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line a 9 x 13-inch baking pan with waxed paper.
Set aside.
In a large bowl of an electric mixer combine sugar and eggs; beat for 10 minutes or until light and thick.
Add oil and beat for 1 or 2 minutes.
Add honey; beat 1 minute.
Add orange juice and applesauce; beat 1 minute.
Set aside.
In a separate bowl sift together flour, cinnamon, ginger, salt, baking soda and baking powder.
Add to egg/honey mixture and beat again for 1 or 2 minutes, until well blended and fluffy.
With a spoon or spatula, gently fold 1/2 cup chopped pecans into batter.
Pour batter into prepared pan and smooth the top.
Sprinkle remaining 1/2 cup pecans on top and bake 50 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in center of cake comes out clean.
Cool in pan on a rack. Cut into squares to serve.
Serves 16.

title: easy caramels
directions: In a 2-quart microwave-safe pitcher, combine butter, sugar, milk and salt.
Microwave on High 4 minutes, stirring once after 2 minutes.
When butter is melted, stir well.
Microwave on High for 14 minutes; no stirring needed.
Remove from microwave and stir in vanilla.
Allow to stand for 10 minutes, stirring well several times.

title: sourdough bread
directions: Combine ingredients in a bowl and cover with towel.
Allow this mixture to sit overnight at room temperature.
Next day take out 1 cup of the starter for blending and combine remaining starter with leftover starter.

title: barbecued meat rolls
directions: Mix together ground beef, enough bread crumbs to hold meat together, onions, catsup, egg, salt and pepper.
Form into 4 even rolls.
Place in shallow baking dish and spread tops with mixture of catsup, brown sugar and dry mustard.
Place in oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: quick rolls
directions: Scald milk.
Cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup lukewarm milk.
Add flour; make a soft dough.
Let stand in warm place until double in size.
Make stiff dough.
Pinch off large egg size.
Mash flat.
Let rise again double in size.
Spread butter on top.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until brown.

title: barbecups
directions: Brown beef and drain, then add barbecue sauce and brown sugar. Take biscuits and press into an ungreased muffin pan.
Make sure dough goes to edge of cup.
Spoon meat mixture into cups and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 12 servings.

title: perfectly simple roasted chicken
directions: You will need one large oven cooking bag.

title: cajun-style rice salad
directions: In a mixing bowl, gently stir together rice, green pepper, shrimp, mushrooms, hard-cooked egg and parsley.
Set aside.

title: cowboy beans
directions: Brown ground beef in margarine.
Drain well.
Place beans in crock-pot.
Add onion and pepper and mix well.
Add ground beef on top of mixture.
Top with barbecue sauce.
Do not stir.
Cook on low heat for 2 hours and then on High for 1 hour.

title: chinese salad
directions: Chop cabbage and green onions and mix.
Store several hours or overnight.

title: mama's kidney bean salad
directions: Put drained
beans
in	large
mixing bowl.
Add onion, pickle and eggs; stir to mix.
Fold in mayonnaise gently so as not to break up eggs.
Serve chilled.

title: diabetic milkshake
directions: Combine
all ingredients in blender.
Process at medium speed until smooth.
Serve immediately.
Contains 80 calories per shake. Frozen fruit makes thicker shakes.

title: pecan balls
directions: Cream butter until soft.
Add sugar, vanilla and pecans.
Sift in flour.
Roll in small balls 1/2 inch in diameter.
Place on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.
Remove and roll in powdered sugar while still warm.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: sandies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add water and vanilla.
Mix well. Add flour and pecans.
Chill 3 or 4 hours.
Shape into balls or fingers.
Bake on greased cookie sheet in slow oven (325°) about 20 minutes.
Cool slightly and roll in powdered sugar.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: red lobster hush puppies
directions: Pour oil to a depth of 1/2-inch in a large, shallow skillet, and heat to 400°.
In the meantime, mix dry ingredients together; stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop mixture by spoonfuls into heated oil.
Fry, turning, until brown.
Remove and drain on paper towels.
If needed, keep cooked hush puppies in a 300° oven until serving time.
Makes 20 hush puppies.

title: cracker pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff; beat in sugar and baking powder. Combine saltines, dates, almond extract and pecans; fold in egg whites.
Pour into 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Top with whipped cream and maraschino cherries.
Serves 8.

title: stuffed french toast
directions: Stir together cream cheese, chopped pecans and orange marmalade. Cut a horizontal pocket into top crust of each bread slice. Spoon about 2 teaspoons cream cheese mixture into each pocket. Whisk together eggs, milk and cinnamon. Dip stuffed bread slices into mixture, coating all sides. Melt butter in a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat. Cook stuffed bread slices, in batches, 2 minutes on each side or until golden. Sprinkle with powdered sugar. Serve with your favorite syrup. Makes 8 servings.

title: indian pilaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in skillet.
Add onion and rice; cook and stir until rice is yellow and onion is tender. Stir in rest of ingredients except almonds.
Pour into ungreased 2-quart casserole.
Heat chicken broth to boiling; stir into rice mixture.
Cover tightly; bake 30 to 40 minutes or until liquid is absorbed and rice is tender.
Stir in almonds.
Makes 8 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: clam dip
directions: Mix together all of the ingredients and serve slightly chilled.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole(excellent for a crowd)
directions: *I use fresh broccoli.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix everything together and bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan for 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Bake in 2 greased medium size loaf pans at 325° at least 1 hour.

title: muffins
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Combine egg, milk, and fat.
Add to the dry ingredients all at once, stirring only enough to moisten.
Fill greased muffin pans 2/3-full.
Bake at 400°
(hot oven) about 20 minutes.
Yields: about 12 medium sized muffins.

title: spaghetti skillet
directions: In a skillet over medium heat, cook beef and sausage until no longer pink; drain. Add the remaining ingredients. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 14 to 16 minutes or until spaghetti is tender.
Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: cheese cake
directions: Beat cream cheese, eggs, 1 cup sugar and vanilla until creamy. Set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients and pat in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour cream cheese mixture over it.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.
When cake is cool, top with 2 cups sour cream and 2 tablespoons sugar, mixed.
Refrigerate.

title: chocolate pecan clusters
directions: Melt chocolate chips and add Eagle Brand milk.
Add pecans. Be sure to cover with chocolate.
Drop
by spoonfuls on waxed paper.

title: no salt tuna salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.
Serve on lettuce. Garnish with tomato wedges if desired.

title: breast of chicken dijon
directions: Lightly flatten chicken breasts.
Dip chicken in milk; coat generously with flour.
Saute chicken in oil in skillet until golden brown, about 2 minutes per side.
Remove; drain excess fat.

title: old fashioned egg custard pie
directions: Beat egg yolks well; combine with 3/4 cup sugar and beat until lemon colored.
Pour hot, but not boiling, milk slowly over this mixture, stirring constantly.
Add salt and vanilla flavoring. Dry the unbaked pastry shell slightly before pouring in egg mixture.
Bake 15 minutes at 400° and bake until custard is firm.

title: cherry delight salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Mix milk, Cool Whip and drained pineapple in large mixing bowl.
Stir in cherry pie filling last.
Let set in refrigerator until well chilled.

title: apple pizza
directions: Spread sugar cookie dough on bottom of a 13-inch pizza pan or 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool.
Mix with a beater cream cheese, brown sugar and caramel ice cream topping; beat until smooth.
Spread on COLD crust.
Put apples, sliced thin in lemon juice and drain really well.
Arrange over caramel; sprinkle with mixed nuts or peanuts or a cinnamon/sugar mixture.
Refrigerate for awhile, then cut.

title: tomato and onion salad
directions: Place all ingredients in a salad bowl.
Toss well.
Serve at room temperature.
Serves 4.

title: magic pineapple ring
directions: Drain juice from pineapple, leaving pineapple rings in can. Heat juice to simmering.
Dissolve Jell-O in juice.
Pour over pineapple slices in can.
Chill until set (about 4 hours).
Unmold by dipping can in warm water (about 10 seconds).
Place plate under open end and remove other end of can.
Gently push out mold onto plate and slice.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: rosy strawberry ring
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add berries, stirring occasionally until berries thaw.
Stir in pineapple, bananas, and lemon juice.
Pour into 6 1/2 cup mold.
Chill until firm (about 5 to 6 hours).
Makes 8 servings.

title: honey chicken
directions: Melt butter.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Roll chicken in mixture.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: creamy braised veal shanks
directions: Sprinkle meat with flour, salt and black pepper.
Heat oil in heavy Dutch oven.
Brown meat slowly in oil, turning frequently. Add broth water to cover tomato paste, rosemary, sage and basil. Turn meat to moisten all sides.
Cover and simmer for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
After 1 1/2 hours, add leeks and carrots.
Spoon juices over mixture and finish cooking until meat is tender.

title: pork chops o'brien
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large skillet, heat oil.
Brown pork chops on both sides and drain.
Sprinkle chops with seasoned salt, set aside.
In a large bowl, combine soup, milk, sour cream, pepper and 1/2 tsp. seasoned salt.
Stir in potatoes, 1/2 c. cheese and 1/2 can French fried onions.
Spoon mixture into a 9 x 13 inch baking dish,
arrange pork chops on top.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour or until pork chops are done.
Top chops with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake, uncovered, 5 minutes or until onions are golden brown.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Refrigerate dough until chilled. Roll out, cut into shapes. Bake cookies 8-10 minutes at 350°. Frost.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Mix altogether.
Roll in waxed paper and chill overnight. Slice cookies and cook at 350° until golden brown.
Yields 5 dozen.

title: gooey butter cake(from the parsonage kitchen)
directions: Mix cake mix, butter and 2 eggs.
Pat into greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Mix powdered sugar, cream cheese, 2 eggs and vanilla. Pour on top of batter.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until set.

title: mother's chicken and dumplings
directions: Combine flour and salt with fingers or fork and mix in shortening or lard until well mixed and the texture is a little grainy.
Add water and place on kneading board and work in flour until stiff.
Roll out very thin.
Cut into strips or squares and drop into boiling broth, salted to taste.
Drop one strip or square at a time, stirring gently, to prevent sticking.
Cover with lid and simmer on low heat for a few minutes or until done.

title: sausage cheese puffs
directions: Fry your sausage and chop up very well; drain good.
In bowl mix other ingredients, you may need more water to mix it together well, add sausage and stir good.
Grease mini muffin tins and spoon fill 3/4 full with mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
They don't brown very well, so don't overcook them.
These take the place of sausage balls at our house.
They are much easier to make. Serve with grape jelly or mustard.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: easy and tasty macaroni salad
directions: Cook
macaroni and cool.
Add diced vegetables and pour Italian
dressing on top.
Sprinkle with garlic powder, mayonnaise and Equal and stir.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix melted butter, sugar and flour. Add eggs, one at a time, and mix well.
Add buttermilk and vanilla.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes; decrease oven temperature to 350° and bake for 30 minutes or until center is set, rises and cracks open.
Makes 2 pies.

title: barbecue pork roast
directions: Combine all ingredients; simmer 15 minutes.
Cook roast in crock-pot on low 8 hours or cook in oven at 300° for 2 1/2 hours (wrap well in foil if baked in oven).
Let cool, shred meat removing fat and bone.
Place shredded pork in baking pan, pouring all sauce in mixture; mix well.
Heat for 30 minutes at 300°.

title: chafing dish meatballs
directions: Mix together all ingredients except the chili sauce, grape jelly and shortening. Shape into 1-inch balls. Melt shortening and brown the meatballs. Remove from skillet. Drain fat. Heat chili sauce and jelly in skillet until jelly melts, stirring constantly. Add meatballs. Stir until cooked. Simmer 30 minutes. Serve hot in chafing dish with toothpicks for spears.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in a greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Combine dry ingredients; add melted butter mixing until crumbly.
Sprinkle crumb mixture over apples.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until apples are tender.

title: hot corn bread
directions: Mix well.
Bake in well-greased pan at 375°.
Good with all vegetables.

title: fruit salad
directions: Stir ingredients together and refrigerate.

title: old-fashioned meat loaf
directions: Mix all but steak sauce; put into loaf pan and turn into flat baking dish.
Brush with steak sauce.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: onion pie
directions: Mix crackers and oleo.
Line a casserole dish for crust. Saute onions until clear.
Spread over cracker crust.
Mix beaten eggs, milk and seasonings together.
Pour over onions.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until firm.

title: pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Work butter with spoon until creamy. Add sugar and work until light.
Slowly stir in syrup.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into pie shell and bake for 1 hour.
Let cool before eating.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Measure 3 cups flour into a large bowl. Answer the telephone. Take large bowl off small son's head and sweep floor.
Measure 3 cups flour into large bowl.
Measure 1/4 cup shortening. Answer doorbell.
Wash shortening from small son's hands and face.
Add 1/4 cup shortening to flour.
Mix well. Rock crying baby for 10 minutes. Answer telephone. Put son in tub. Scrub well. Scrape flour and shortening mixture from kitchen floor.
Add enough tears to relieve tension.
Open 1 can of beans and serve with remaining strength.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Bake in a preheated oven at 325° until done.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Add flour to butter, then mix in eggs.
Add in cottage cheese, spinach (thawed and drained) and Cheddar cheese.
Mix all ingredients together, then cook uncovered for 1 hour at 350°.

title: quick and easy chicken wraps
directions: In medium mixing bowl, combine yogurt, garlic and herb. Stir until blended. Salt and pepper to taste. Add chicken breast and stir until well coated. Place lettuce slices and 1/4 of chicken mixture on a whole wheat tortilla and wrap up. Serves 4.

title: spiced corned beef
directions: Combine all ingredients; cover and simmer 3 to 4 hours, allowing 1 hour per pound of meat.

title: old settler beans
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Fry bacon crispy and drain.
Mix meats with rest of ingredients and cook in crock-pot at least 1/2 day.
Do not drain beans.

title: cherry jello mold
directions: Place Jell-O powder in a large bowl. Pour 1 cup reserved cherry juice into bowl. Add 1 cup boiling water; whisk thoroughly until Jell-O is dissolved. Chill until gelatin begins to set, about 15 minutes. Remove from refrigerator and add sour cream. Beat with an electric mixer until smooth. Add cherries. Pour into a 3-quart mold. Refrigerate until firm.

title: pepper relish
directions: Grind peppers and onions; place in large kettle.
Add vinegar, sugar and salt.
Bring to a boil; boil for 5 minutes.
Lower temperature and continue cooking for 30 minutes.
Pour into hot jars and seal.
Makes nine pints.

title: ruth ann's fillets
directions: Salt and pepper fillet lightly and place in glass dish, skin down.
Mix butter, parsley, lemon juice and cracker crumbs. Spread mixture on fish.
Sprinkle 1/2 teaspoon paprika on top. Sprinkle with Old Bay (optional).
Cook on High 5 minutes, covered with Saran.
Rotate 1/2 turn, cook 6 minutes until fillets flake easily.
Let set a few minutes before eating.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt butter in casserole dish. Combine cream-style corn, whole kernel corn and sour cream. Pour into butter.
Sprinkle corn bread mix over corn mixture. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: santa fe chicken
directions: In a large skillet, brown chicken in oil 10 or 15 minutes. Drain.
Salt and pepper to taste. Stir cumin and garlic into tomato sauce.
Pour over chicken.
Add rest of ingredients. Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Uncover and cook on high 10 minutes or until chicken is done. Serve with hot cooked rice.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: fudge pecan pie
directions: Warm milk so that it will mix with remaining ingredients. Pour into uncooked pie shells. Sprinkle top with chopped nuts. Bake for 50-60 minutes at 375°.

title: baked chicken casserole
directions: Add 2 1/2 cups boiling water to soup mix.
Cover and simmer 7 minutes.
In skillet, melt margarine and saute onions.
Remove onions and blend flour into margarine.
Stir in hot soup and cook until thickened.
Grease 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Arrange layers of mixed vegetables, onions and chicken.
Pour sauce over all.
Top with soft bread crumbs mixed with 1 tablespoon margarine.
Bake 15 minutes at 450°.

title: chocolate angel food cake(low-fat)
directions: Combine flour packet from cake mix and cocoa.
Prepare cake according to package directions.
Fold chocolate flavoring into batter.
Bake according to package directions.
Sprinkle cooled cake with powdered sugar; garnish with strawberries.
Yields 32 (1/2-inch) servings.

title: refrigerator gingerbread
directions: Cream together the sugar and shortenings.
Add molasses.
Add eggs, beating well.
Mix flour, baking powder, soda, salt and ginger.
Add dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk.
Store in refrigerator until ready to use.
Make 2 (8 x 8-inch) pans. Will keep in the refrigerator for 2 weeks.
Microwave 5 minutes or until almost done on High.
Let stand 10 minutes directly on countertop (cake will continue to cook).
In regular oven, bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: broccoli supreme
directions: Cook broccoli cuts according to package; drain.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Add sour cream mix to broccoli; toss. Place in casserole.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Store in well sealed container. Use 1 to 2 teaspoons per cup of hot water.

title: crab-stuffed manicotti
directions: Prepare manicotti per package directions; drain.
In a medium bowl, combine Ricotta, 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese and egg.
Mix well. Stir in crabmeat, pimiento, 1 tablespoon of parsley, 1/2 teaspoon of salt and 1/2 teaspoon of pepper.
Fill manicotti with cheese mixture.
Arrange in a 12 x 8-inch baking dish.

title: mystery pie
directions: Beat egg whites with baking powder.
As eggs start to foam, gradually add sugar.
Beat until stiff, but not dry.
Fold in pecans and graham cracker crumbs.
Add vanilla and pour into greased pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: marinated slaw
directions: Slice or shred cabbage, pepper and onion. Boil the dry mustard, celery seed and salt.
Combine all ingredients; sprinkle with sugar and refrigerate overnight.

title: deviled hamburgers
directions: Spread on bread.
Broil for 20 minutes.

title: quick fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter.
Mix all other ingredients, except fruit, to make a smooth batter.
Pour batter over butter; do not stir.
Add fruit and juice; do not stir.
Place in 350° oven for about 35 to 40 minutes or until brown.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: cheese cake
directions: Cream together the cottage cheese and cream cheese.
Gradually add the sugar, eggs, lemon juice and vanilla.
Add cornstarch and flour.
Stir in well until smooth the melted butter and sour cream.
Pour into greased (with margarine) spring pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Let remain in shut off oven for 2 more hours. Chill.
Put on topping just before serving.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Beat eggs and milk.
Gradually mix in flour, sugar, salt and baking powder until smooth.
Hold the opening of a funnel closed with your forefinger.
Fill funnel with batter.
Controlling the flow with finger, dribble into hot oil (375°).
Start at the center of the pan and swirl the batter outward in a circle.
Fry for 2 or 3 minutes or until brown.
Drain on paper towel. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: rice pudding
directions: Mix and bake until it starts to thicken.
Bake in a 350° oven. Stir several times while baking.

title: german meat loaf
directions: Mix beef, egg, milk, crumbs, onion and seasonings to make meat loaf; mold into ring in 2-quart round baking dish.
Parboil cauliflower, place in center of meat loaf.
Mix cheese and milk, pour over cauliflower.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to one hour, last 5 minutes of baking place tomatoes on top of meat loaf. Yields 4 servings.
